<ns0:node id="MCO 3000.17">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MCO 3000.17</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MCO 3000.17 provides guidance on exercise and contingency operations.&lt;SEP&gt;MCO 3000.17 is referenced for maintenance requirements in support of Maritime Prepositioning Ships and programs.&lt;SEP&gt;MCO 3000.17 is a Marine Corps order on shelf life requirements superseded by MCO 4000.58 in specific areas for MCMC.&lt;SEP&gt;MCO 3000.17 is a Marine Corps Order on shelf life and service life management for assets and materiel.&lt;SEP&gt;MCO 3000.17 is the Marine Corps Prepositioning Programs order supplementing the SOW for MCPP requirements.&lt;SEP&gt;MCO 3000.17 is a Marine Corps Order addressing personnel and operational procedures.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8a136ea2c9ab7ea9bb718fd0abd010d4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22de15a10ae9bfba6096cca855d5f78a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f736781b685dec5629d8433e71c666e4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c2bae9a24e71825050f79fc141b2e181&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-432adfa735f19522f81538c1e139e7a3</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841048</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CmdO 4790.1B">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CmdO 4790.1B</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CmdO 4790.1B is a Command Order providing guidance on maintenance administration, inspections, UND delegation, and supply support procedures.&lt;SEP&gt;CmdO 4790.1B is a Command Order referenced extensively for maintenance execution, validations, reconciliations, calibration, modification control, TAV configuration, publication control, equipment availability, PMCS, corrective maintenance, cannibalization, load lifting, corrosion control, ELMP, and UUAM programs.&lt;SEP&gt;CmdO 4790.1B is the Blount Island Command Maintenance Management Standard Operating Procedures governing MCMC maintenance operations.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-a0a00a7bb666b381893da579a6b228c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f736781b685dec5629d8433e71c666e4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89b1a9fa6c0722adcd478e665df09141</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841048</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CDRL">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CDRL</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CDRL is the Contract Data Requirements List identified in Section J of the IDIQ, specifying required reports for the task order.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-f736781b685dec5629d8433e71c666e4</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841048</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="OMMS-NG">
  <ns0:data key="d0">OMMS-NG</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">OMMS-NG is an application within NTCSS providing access to maintenance information, planning, scheduling, and reporting for Navy maintenance.&lt;SEP&gt;OMMS-NG is a module utilized by MCMC for entering and managing PMCS and CM maintenance actions, requiring approved work candidates.&lt;SEP&gt;OMMS-NG is a module used by MCMC for entering maintenance actions, work candidates, and closing out repairs for containers and CESE.&lt;SEP&gt;OMMS-NG is a system for which MCMC provides data entry services for external contractors.&lt;SEP&gt;OMMS-NG is a module used for tracking maintenance actions, PMCS, corrective maintenance, and work candidates for Navy Watercraft, with entries required accurately and close-outs within 30 calendar days.&lt;SEP&gt;OMMS-NG is a module used to document corrective maintenance requests, actions, and completions for Navy Watercraft.&lt;SEP&gt;Organizational Maintenance Management System - Next Generation (OMMS-NG) is utilized for Ground Support Equipment (GSE).&lt;SEP&gt;OMMS-NG is a maintenance management system for which MCMC provides data entry services for external contractors.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-955c2fafc0e5a2a07e97130b42a872b5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d6887833d0f1a6398bb6c8fd6f72d5c8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-85b50b451f72c11f155dc39b516d8dd3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bee5e6b5db1fe2dc611fc5fc2b227a51&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e73c8ab3a0b248cdeedb8496a5c6f8a9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7659b0abfc62a3f8f0edbf4a1fee058e</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841048</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="GSE">
  <ns0:data key="d0">GSE</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">GSE is Ground Support Equipment owned by the Navy and used for MPF mission support, including cranes, hoists, forklifts, and vehicles.&lt;SEP&gt;Ground Support Equipment (GSE) is included in the Organic GFE Status Report and subject to maintenance management.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841048</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Organic GFE Status Report">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Organic GFE Status Report</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Organic GFE Status Report for Material Handling Equipment (MHE), Wheel Handling Equipment (WHE), and Ground Support Equipment (GSE) lists operational, degraded, and nonoperational status of designated Navy Government Furnished Equipment (GFE), equipment discrepancies, and is provided monthly to the Government no later than the fifth day of each month as CDRL 6067 per SOW Attachment C.6-020.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841048</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CDRL 6067">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CDRL 6067</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CDRL 6067 is a monthly Organic GFE Status Report for MHE, WHE, and GSE.&lt;SEP&gt;CDRL 6067 specifies the Organic GFE Status Report requirements.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841048</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="SOW Attachment C.6-020">
  <ns0:data key="d0">SOW Attachment C.6-020</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">SOW Attachment C.6-020 is a Statement of Work attachment for Organic GFE Status Report.&lt;SEP&gt;SOW Attachment C.6-020 details the Organic GFE Status Report.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841048</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MPS">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MPS</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MPS refers to Maritime Prepositioning Ships aboard which materiel is embarked with minimum shelf life requirements.&lt;SEP&gt;MPS refers to Maritime Prepositioning Ships used for prepositioned afloat assets.&lt;SEP&gt;MPS refers to afloat Maritime Prepositioning Ships where Confirmation of Receipt is processed upon physical receipt of materiel.&lt;SEP&gt;MPS refers to Maritime Prepositioning Ships, supported by supply operations, ISO container management, and related programs.&lt;SEP&gt;MPS is the Maritime Prepositioning Ships program involving afloat prepositioned equipment exempt from certain reconciliations.&lt;SEP&gt;MPS refers to Maritime Prepositioning Ships where MCMC personnel operate, providing billeting, services, and prepositioned assets.&lt;SEP&gt;MPS are Maritime Prepositioning Ships where MCMC performs maintenance, inspections, and housekeeping functions.&lt;SEP&gt;MPS refers to Maritime Prepositioning Ships involved in afloat phase operations, offloads, backloads, and logistics services.&lt;SEP&gt;MPS refers to Maritime Prepositioning Ships supported by Class II and Class VII ME and CESE assets for individual prepositioning objectives.&lt;SEP&gt;MPS is Maritime Prepositioning Ships involved in embarkation and debarkation support.&lt;SEP&gt;Maritime Prepositioning Ships (MPS) production period generally lasts 80-110 days and contains an average of 60 Twenty Foot Equivalent Units (TEUs) with 10,000 total containerized line items, involving specialized logistics services such as inspection, inventory, servicing, corrosion control, maintenance, configuration, association, stock rotation, calibration, marking, and labeling.&lt;SEP&gt;MPS refers to Maritime Prepositioning Ships involved in embarkation, backload, and offload operations for Navy Watercraft and ABLTS.&lt;SEP&gt;MPS refers to Maritime Prepositioning Ships used for deployed operations in supply and distribution support.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-f918f57232ad428f5920d4c98f0af702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-abd2ceb311ce78c8a8c1fe38d11ee4f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6b04b67f7f379aa858c2a82b29df69a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-68739860c42b764e52f9649ea16ed702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-65833c099ebcc7aa1fccc5a1d930a7aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c10c3b1cc4c0a5d44aa2c137a52eaf0b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7659b0abfc62a3f8f0edbf4a1fee058e</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841048</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="ISO 9001">
  <ns0:data key="d0">ISO 9001</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">ISO 9001 is a quality management standard to which MCMC auditors must be certified and which is part of the Command's Joint Management Review.&lt;SEP&gt;ISO 9001 is an international standard that delineates processes for providing timely and accurate data within defined systems.&lt;SEP&gt;ISO 9001 is the certification standard (currently 9001:2015) that MCMC must maintain, with inclusion in the Command’s scope.&lt;SEP&gt;ISO 9001 is the International Organization for Standardization quality management standard used by the MCMC for developing local procedures.&lt;SEP&gt;ISO 9001 is an international standard used for developing and implementing local procedures, quality control, risk and performance policies, joint certification, quality and risk control plans, internal audit programs, and continuous process improvement.&lt;SEP&gt;ISO 9001 is an International Standards Organization standard for quality management used in developing local procedures for timely and accurate data.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2edf7351f7d27be2ca8809d7ac16a11d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bee5e6b5db1fe2dc611fc5fc2b227a51&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-432adfa735f19522f81538c1e139e7a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a0a00a7bb666b381893da579a6b228c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841048</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CmdO P5000.11">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CmdO P5000.11</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CmdO P5000.11 outlines management procedures and work instructions for quality management and nonconformities.&lt;SEP&gt;CmdO P5000.11 is a command order for management procedures in data processes.&lt;SEP&gt;CmdO P5000.11 provides management procedures referenced for internal control, production plans, quality control, risk policies, briefings, reviews, audit programs, and continuous process improvement reporting.&lt;SEP&gt;CmdO P5000.11 is the designation for the BICmd Risk and Performance Manual incorporated for quality control alignment and ISO Joint Certification compliance.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2829fe507a5073eafb2e5fb0cc5e85c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bee5e6b5db1fe2dc611fc5fc2b227a51&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841048</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MCPP II">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MCPP II</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MCPP II is Maritime Prepositioning Program Phase II operations using License Plate ISO 18000-7 tags.&lt;SEP&gt;MCPP II encompasses maintenance requirements including Care of Supplies in Storage (COSIS) and repair activities directed by the Ship’s Planning Considerations Letter.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841048</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Ships Planning Considerations Letter">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Ships Planning Considerations Letter</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Ship’s Planning Considerations Letter is produced by the Government per CmdO 4850.1 and directs production plans and schedules for MCPP II maintenance requirements.&lt;SEP&gt;Ship’s Planning Considerations Letter is produced by the Government to direct production plans and schedules for MCPP II maintenance and COSIS.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841048</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CmdO 4850.1">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CmdO 4850.1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CmdO 4850.1 provides guidance for production planning considerations produced by the Production Planning and Execution Team.&lt;SEP&gt;CmdO 4850.1 is a command order for production plans and schedules.&lt;SEP&gt;CmdO 4850.1 governs the production of the Ship’s Planning Considerations Letter.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-bee5e6b5db1fe2dc611fc5fc2b227a51&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841048</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MS Project Production Plan">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MS Project Production Plan</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MS Project Production Plan serves as a baseline for Navy Construction Equipment Support Equipment (CESE) and containerized assets per MCPIC plans and requirements, provided for Government approval, and maintained with change control per CmdO 5202.1.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841048</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CmdO 5202.1">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CmdO 5202.1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CmdO 5202.1 outlines change control processes, sustainment operations planning, and maintenance requirements.&lt;SEP&gt;CmdO 5202.1 is referenced for KPI reporting processes.&lt;SEP&gt;CmdO 5202.1 identifies the change control process for production plans.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-bee5e6b5db1fe2dc611fc5fc2b227a51&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-432adfa735f19522f81538c1e139e7a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841048</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Navy CESE">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Navy CESE</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Navy CESE encompasses construction equipment standard equipment assets subject to maintenance requirements, including specific tests and services.&lt;SEP&gt;Navy CESE is Navy Civil Engineer Support Equipment included in the Calibration Control Program established by the MCMC.&lt;SEP&gt;Navy Construction Equipment Support Equipment (CESE) is planned evenly and distributed throughout the baseline project production plan, balanced with USMC ground tactical equipment to ensure servicing and completion within the schedule.&lt;SEP&gt;Navy CESE consists of authorized equipment temporarily loaned by MCMC to operating forces in support of exercises or contingencies, with adjustments to the Consolidated Asset Listing (CAL).&lt;SEP&gt;Navy CESE refers to Navy construction equipment supported in supply chain and maintenance requirements.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-6b04b67f7f379aa858c2a82b29df69a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c10c3b1cc4c0a5d44aa2c137a52eaf0b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a0a00a7bb666b381893da579a6b228c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e73c8ab3a0b248cdeedb8496a5c6f8a9</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841048</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Letter of Non-Conformance">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Letter of Non-Conformance</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Letter of Non-Conformance is submitted to COR for deviations from schedule, non-completion of tasks, or items not meeting milestones within 5 business days of identification.&lt;SEP&gt;Letter of Non-Conformance is submitted for each item not completed and ready for Fully Mission Capable (FMC) by the baseline finish date.&lt;SEP&gt;Letter of Non-Conformance is required from MCMC for any FAB functional areas not achieving Full Mission Capable status at the end of Phase D Stage 4.&lt;SEP&gt;Letter of Non-Conformance is issued by MCMC detailing efforts to produce capability sets meeting task order delivery requirements for non-FMC functional areas at the end of Phase D Stage 4.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-85b50b451f72c11f155dc39b516d8dd3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e73c8ab3a0b248cdeedb8496a5c6f8a9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7659b0abfc62a3f8f0edbf4a1fee058e</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841048</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="eQMS">
  <ns0:data key="d0">eQMS</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">eQMS is a module of the Enterprise QMSS assisting with quality management and nonconformance reporting.&lt;SEP&gt;Electronic Quality Management System (eQMS) is utilized within MCPIC for internal quality inspections, responding to Government Non-Conformance Reports (NCRs), tracking non-conforming products/services, and handling communications for non-conformances.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93752a7bd8aca85ef0ce5fea3701dc32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841048</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="NCR">
  <ns0:data key="d0">NCR</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Non-Conformance Report (NCR) is initiated in eQMS by Government Quality Assurance (QA), acknowledged within 12 work hours, and resolved by the due date.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841048</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="FAR 52.246-11">
  <ns0:data key="d0">FAR 52.246-11</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">FAR 52.246-11 is a regulation for providing quality control of products and services.&lt;SEP&gt;FAR 52.246-11 provides requirements for quality control of products and services.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-432adfa735f19522f81538c1e139e7a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841048</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Q&amp;RCP">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Q&amp;RCP</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Quality and Risk Control Plan (Q&amp;RCP) draft is developed and submitted within 30 calendar days of contract award, final version within 60 days for Government approval, complies with ISO 9001:2015 and CmdO P5000.11, contains quality control and risk performance levels for deliverables and internal Key Performance Indicators (KPIs), and is updated for semi-annual third-party audits.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841048</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="ANAB">
  <ns0:data key="d0">ANAB</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">American National Accreditation Board (ANAB) is an accrediting body for third-party auditors validating ISO 9001:2015 certification.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841048</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="RAB">
  <ns0:data key="d0">RAB</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Registrar Accreditation Board (RAB) is an accrediting body for third-party auditors validating ISO 9001:2015 certification.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841048</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Quality KPI Control Charts">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Quality KPI Control Charts</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Quality Key Performance Indicator (KPI) control charts are provided quarterly for internal quality control elements supporting the Q&amp;RCP per CmdO P5000.11 and CmdO 5201.1, subject to Government analysis.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841048</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Risk KPI Control Charts">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Risk KPI Control Charts</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Risk Key Performance Indicator (KPI) control charts are provided quarterly for internal risk control elements supporting the Q&amp;RCP per CmdO P5000.11 and CmdO 5230.1, subject to Government analysis.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841048</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CmdO 5201.1">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CmdO 5201.1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CmdO 5201.1 details rating methodologies for management effectiveness, including KPIs for production and sustainment operations.&lt;SEP&gt;CmdO 5201.1 is referenced for KPI reporting processes and participation in briefings.&lt;SEP&gt;CmdO 5201.1 governs quality key performance indicators, ship’s kick-off briefings, end-of-ship reviews, and internal audit programs.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-bee5e6b5db1fe2dc611fc5fc2b227a51&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-432adfa735f19522f81538c1e139e7a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841048</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CmdO 5230.1">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CmdO 5230.1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CmdO 5230.1 governs risk key performance indicators.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841048</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Ships Kick-Off Briefing">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Ships Kick-Off Briefing</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">event</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Ship’s Kick-Off Briefing requires MCMC participation to present projected cost, schedule, conformance, and risk baselines for each ship’s MMC.&lt;SEP&gt;Ship’s Kick-Off Briefing requires MCMC participation per CmdO P5000.11 and CmdO 5201.1 to present projected cost, schedule, conformance, and risk baseline for each ship’s maintenance management cycle (MMC).</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-432adfa735f19522f81538c1e139e7a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841048</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="End-of-Ship MCMC Performance Review">
  <ns0:data key="d0">End-of-Ship MCMC Performance Review</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">event</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">End-of-Ship (EOS) MCMC Performance Review requires MCMC participation per CmdO P5000.11 to review variations in cost, schedule, conformance, and risk from the Ship’s Kick-Off Briefing, and lessons learned for Continuous Process Improvement (CPI) initiatives.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841048</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="ISO 9001:2015 Internal Audit Program">
  <ns0:data key="d0">ISO 9001:2015 Internal Audit Program</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">requirement</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">ISO 9001:2015 Internal Audit Program is maintained annually by MCMC, with a rolling three-year schedule submitted for approval.&lt;SEP&gt;ISO 9001:2015 Internal Audit Program is maintained annually per ISO 9001:2015, CmdO P5000.11, and CmdO 5201.1, with schedules submitted for Government approval by the second week in September for the next fiscal year, records kept for 3 years, and updates provided at Business Process and Quality Review Board (BPQRB) meetings.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-432adfa735f19522f81538c1e139e7a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841048</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CPI">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CPI</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Continuous Process Improvement (CPI) is reported per CmdO P5000.11 using industry best practices for data collection and analysis, with Government approval for implementation when required, and a summary brief provided at every six-month Quality/Risk Management Review Board.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841048</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="QCP">
  <ns0:data key="d0">QCP</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Quality Control Plan (QCP) is provided annually no later than 1 November, detailing surveillance and verification of Statement of Work (SOW) performance requirements, including communication procedures, performance levels, defect prevention, surveillance procedures, complaint resolution, and file maintenance available to the Contracting Officer’s Representative (COR).</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841048</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Navy Mobile Load Requirements">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Navy Mobile Load Requirements</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">section</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Navy Mobile Load Requirements section (6.P) outlines downloading, inventorying, providing, preparing, labeling, associating, and loading mobile loads including SL-3 per TM 4790-14/2, Government-approved schedules, maintenance/production Planning Considerations Letters (PCLs), and MCPIC plans.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841048</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="TM 4790-14/2">
  <ns0:data key="d0">TM 4790-14/2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">TM 4790-14/2 is a technical manual on maintenance and operations for prepositioning programs.&lt;SEP&gt;TM 4790-14/2 is a technical manual used for sourcing SAC 1 and 3 Military Equipment.&lt;SEP&gt;TM 4790-14/2 is referenced for maintenance requirements in support of Maritime Prepositioning Ships and programs.&lt;SEP&gt;TM 4790-14/2 is a technical manual for downloading, unpacking, and inventorying containers and mobile loads.&lt;SEP&gt;TM 4790-14/2 is a technical manual referenced for supply operations, container packing, P3&amp;M, and preservation procedures.&lt;SEP&gt;TM 4790-14/2 provides guidance for inventorying mobile loads including SL-3.&lt;SEP&gt;TM 4790-14/2 provides standards for physical inventory management, maintenance, and accountability of Navy MPE/S during the afloat phase.&lt;SEP&gt;TM 4790-14/2 provides specifications for general maintenance management, quality control, supply, and other afloat phase operations.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22de15a10ae9bfba6096cca855d5f78a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd3a05bb896b89de7fd366c654ad4a6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-432adfa735f19522f81538c1e139e7a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e73c8ab3a0b248cdeedb8496a5c6f8a9</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MCPIC">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MCPIC</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MCPIC is a system for prepositioning planning, including Detailed Ship Plans and package IDs, used to identify disparities with GCSS-MC.&lt;SEP&gt;MCPIC is a net-centric system providing planning data for Marine Corps prepositioning programs, including reports and plans posted through MMC production.&lt;SEP&gt;MCPIC is an information management system used for posting, reviewing, and managing squadron level plans and data in prepositioning programs.&lt;SEP&gt;MCPIC is the Marine Corps Prepositioning Integrated Catalog providing data for asset listings and validation.&lt;SEP&gt;MCPIC contains detailed plans, mobile load association plans, and is used for data entry and discrepancy reporting.&lt;SEP&gt;MCPIC is the Marine Corps Prepositioning Integrated Command system containing embarkation records and ship planning data.&lt;SEP&gt;MCPIC provides detailed plans with spreads based on Prepositioning Objective for equipment requirements across ships and ashore sites.&lt;SEP&gt;MCPIC is a web-based IT tool used for managing plans, data, embarkation, and transportation related to MPF processes.&lt;SEP&gt;MCPIC is used for associating IUID and RFID tags in compliance with MCO 4410.28.&lt;SEP&gt;MCPIC oversees plans and requirements for production, maintenance, eQMS utilization, and mobile load association.&lt;SEP&gt;MCPIC is a system where ship’s detailed plans are posted, data is updated, and container production projects are provided for approval.&lt;SEP&gt;MCPIC is an automated information system used for capturing storage locations of portable fire extinguishers and embarkation data.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-955c2fafc0e5a2a07e97130b42a872b5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-abd2ceb311ce78c8a8c1fe38d11ee4f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8efbcbadad92a347ffdc7b5c1e34b2f7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22de15a10ae9bfba6096cca855d5f78a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38be7e49aefd10e870f45cb648f7d79d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd3a05bb896b89de7fd366c654ad4a6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bee5e6b5db1fe2dc611fc5fc2b227a51&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CmdBul 3162">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CmdBul 3162</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Command Data Summary Standards Letter (CmdBul) 3162 standards are used for marking and packing equipment/supplies in MCPIC.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Navy WHE Program">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Navy WHE Program</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">requirement</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Navy Weight Handling Equipment (WHE) Program (section 6.Q) establishes and maintains programs for WHE and rigging gear per NAVFAC P-307, NAVFAC P-300, and Navy Consolidated Memorandum Receipt (CMR) via Defense Property Accountability System (DPAS) for pre-positioning assets (PO).</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="NAVFAC P-307">
  <ns0:data key="d0">NAVFAC P-307</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">NAVFAC P-307 is a Naval Facilities publication governing maintenance of Non-Tactical Vehicles.&lt;SEP&gt;NAVFAC P-307 outlines requirements for crane operations, rigging gear, critical lifts, destructive weather plans, and material handling equipment used by MCMC.&lt;SEP&gt;NAVFAC P-307 outlines requirements for crane services, rigging equipment, weight handling, and maintenance standards.&lt;SEP&gt;NAVFAC P-307 is a Naval Facilities Engineering Command publication outlining safety, operation, and qualification standards for cranes, rigging, and weight handling equipment.&lt;SEP&gt;NAVFAC P-307 is a Naval Facilities Engineering Command publication specifying procedures for maintaining weight handling equipment.&lt;SEP&gt;NAVFAC P-307 is a Naval Facilities Engineering Command manual for load bearing parts and safety devices.&lt;SEP&gt;NAVFAC P-307 provides certification and testing procedures for CESE load-lifting assets.&lt;SEP&gt;NAVFAC P-307 provides requirements for designating WHE personnel, training, maintenance, inspection, test, certification, repair, alteration, operation, use of WHE, critical lifts, accidents, near misses, and destructive weather plans.&lt;SEP&gt;NAVFAC P-307 provides guidelines for establishing maintenance records and history files for Navy CESE.&lt;SEP&gt;NAVFAC P-307 states standards for Weight Handling Equipment operators.&lt;SEP&gt;NAVFAC P-307 outlines requirements and procedures for investigating weight handling equipment accidents and near misses, including compliance for crane operations.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-955c2fafc0e5a2a07e97130b42a872b5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9fdacd5fbf292ea850730c0c323f0873&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b825754de20bbf2c5befd6a79730280e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-070bdd3969938da07f8e836e32dfa592&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4ef5ed78269155f4369ff9bd9b69ddc8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-27cca63c94e6ea85e547a26e12b48a3c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd3a05bb896b89de7fd366c654ad4a6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c10c3b1cc4c0a5d44aa2c137a52eaf0b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="NAVFAC P-300">
  <ns0:data key="d0">NAVFAC P-300</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">NAVFAC P-300 is a Naval Facilities Engineering Command manual for maintenance and corrosion control.&lt;SEP&gt;NAVFAC P-300 supports the Navy WHE Program for inspection, testing, and certification.&lt;SEP&gt;NAVFAC P-300 provides guidelines for load banking generators, condition inspections, and maintenance records for Navy CESE.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-955c2fafc0e5a2a07e97130b42a872b5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CMR">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CMR</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CMR is the Consolidated Memorandum Receipt used for reconciliations and validating accountability, signed by the Responsible Officer.&lt;SEP&gt;CMR is Consolidated Memorandum Receipt managed via DPAS for Navy GFE.&lt;SEP&gt;Navy Consolidated Memorandum Receipt (CMR) is managed via DPAS for pre-positioning assets (PO) in the WHE program.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="DPAS">
  <ns0:data key="d0">DPAS</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">DPAS is utilized for accountability of non-tactical vehicles, non-standard military equipment, and SAC 1 CBRN equipment.&lt;SEP&gt;DPAS is the Defense Property Accountability System utilized by MCMC for asset accountability.&lt;SEP&gt;DPAS is a Department of Defense property management system serving as the Accountable Property System of Record, with modules for accountability, maintenance, and warehouse management.&lt;SEP&gt;Defense Property Accountability System (DPAS) is used to account for Government-owned Garrison Fabricated Tools.&lt;SEP&gt;DPAS is the Defense Property Accountability System into which the MCMC accounts for Government-owned Garrison Fabricated Tools in accordance with specified orders.&lt;SEP&gt;DPAS is the Defense Property Accountability System used for accounting certain assets not in GCSS-MC.&lt;SEP&gt;DPAS is Defense Property Accountability System used for Navy Consolidated Memorandum Receipt.&lt;SEP&gt;Defense Property Accountability System (DPAS) is used for managing CMR in the Navy WHE Program.&lt;SEP&gt;DPAS is a record-keeping system for which historical records are provided by the incumbent during phase-out.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b6f17f0fbf6c678da23e588ab57f6900&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-68739860c42b764e52f9649ea16ed702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd3a05bb896b89de7fd366c654ad4a6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89b1a9fa6c0722adcd478e665df09141&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bee5e6b5db1fe2dc611fc5fc2b227a51&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a0a00a7bb666b381893da579a6b228c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Weight Handling Program Manager">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Weight Handling Program Manager</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">person</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Weight Handling Program Manager for Navy WHE is nominated in writing for Government approval and signature per CDRL 6068, appointed by the Commanding Officer (CO) of BICmd within 30 calendar days of contract award or personnel change, with requirements in NAVFAC P-307.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CDRL 6068">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CDRL 6068</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CDRL 6068 specifies appointment letters for Weight Handling Program Manager, Licensing Official, Certifying Official, and Load Test Director.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Licensing Official">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Licensing Official</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">person</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Licensing Official for Navy WHE is nominated in writing for Government approval and signature per CDRL 6068, appointed by the Commanding Officer of BICmd within 30 calendar days of contract award or personnel change, with requirements in NAVFAC P-307.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Certifying Official">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Certifying Official</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">person</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Certifying Official for Navy WHE is nominated in writing for Government approval and signature per CDRL 6068, appoints Load Test Director and other personnel, with requirements in NAVFAC P-307.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Load Test Director">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Load Test Director</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">person</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Load Test Director for Navy WHE is appointed in writing by the Certifying Official per CDRL 6068, submitted to Navy COR within 30 calendar days of contract award or personnel change.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="DWP">
  <ns0:data key="d0">DWP</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Destructive Weather Plan (DWP) addresses NAVFAC P-307 and CmdO 3440 requirements for Navy-owned cranes including Crawler Crane, Rough Terrain Crane, and Mobile Boat Hoists, with a current copy maintained in each crane operator’s cab.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CmdO 3440">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CmdO 3440</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CmdO 3440 provides requirements for destructive weather plans for Navy-owned cranes.&lt;SEP&gt;CmdO 3440 sets requirements for destructive weather plans addressing Navy-owned cranes.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Crane Metrics Report">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Crane Metrics Report</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Crane Metrics Report (CDRL 6071 per SOW Attachment C.6-042) is provided to Navy COR no later than the 5th business day of each month, including WHE inventory, accidents, near misses, unplanned occurrences, crane reliability, and maintenance costs.&lt;SEP&gt;Crane Metrics Report is submitted monthly under section 6.Q.1.m for X002.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aa9424078fa723e2caaae8aa59fb4397</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CDRL 6071">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CDRL 6071</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CDRL 6071 is the Crane Metrics Report provided monthly to the Navy COR, including metrics on WHE inventory, accidents, near misses, unplanned occurrences, crane reliability, and maintenance costs.&lt;SEP&gt;CDRL 6071 specifies the Crane Metrics Report.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="SOW Attachment C.6-042">
  <ns0:data key="d0">SOW Attachment C.6-042</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">SOW Attachment C.6-042 details the Crane Metrics Report.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="OEM">
  <ns0:data key="d0">OEM</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">OEM refers to original equipment manufacturer standards and recommendations for maintenance, inspections, and certifications.&lt;SEP&gt;OEM is Original Equipment Manufacturer providing manuals and parts for maintenance.&lt;SEP&gt;Original Equipment Manufacturer (OEM) supplies all WHE load bearing parts, load controlling parts, or operational safety devices per NAVFAC P-307.&lt;SEP&gt;OEM refers to Original Equipment Manufacturer, whose specifications and recommendations guide maintenance, repairs, and services for vehicles and equipment.&lt;SEP&gt;OEM is Original Equipment Manufacturer, source for procuring WHE load bearing parts, load controlling parts, and operational safety devices.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-070bdd3969938da07f8e836e32dfa592&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-27cca63c94e6ea85e547a26e12b48a3c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Critical Lift Plans">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Critical Lift Plans</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Critical Lift Plans, including rigging sketches where required, are completed prior to critical lifts as defined in NAVFAC P-307 section 10, maintained in a unique binder for government review.&lt;SEP&gt;Critical Lift Plans (CDRL 6072 per SOW Attachment C.6-040) including rigging sketches are completed for loads meeting critical lift requirements per section 10 of NAVFAC P-307.&lt;SEP&gt;Critical Lift Plans detail procedures for heavy lifts using cranes and are required prior to conducting all critical lifts for X002 under section 6.Q.3.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aa9424078fa723e2caaae8aa59fb4397</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CDRL 6072">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CDRL 6072</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CDRL 6072 refers to Critical Lift Plans as part of SOW Attachment C.6-040.&lt;SEP&gt;CDRL 6072 specifies Critical Lift Plans.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="SOW Attachment C.6-040">
  <ns0:data key="d0">SOW Attachment C.6-040</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">SOW Attachment C.6-040 details Critical Lift Plans.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Accident Investigation Report">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Accident Investigation Report</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Accident Investigation Report (CDRL 6069) is submitted accurately and completely within seven calendar days of a WHE or rigging gear accident occurrence, following initial notification within two hours per NAVFAC P-307.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CDRL 6069">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CDRL 6069</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CDRL 6069 specifies the Accident Investigation Report.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Near Miss Report">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Near Miss Report</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Near Miss Report (CDRL 6070) for near misses and unplanned occurrences involving WHE/rigging gear is submitted accurately and completely within seven calendar days of occurrence, following initial notification within four hours per NAVFAC P-307.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CDRL 6070">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CDRL 6070</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CDRL 6070 consists of accurate and complete Near Miss Reports for near misses and unplanned occurrences, submitted within seven calendar days of occurrence.&lt;SEP&gt;CDRL 6070 specifies the Near Miss Report.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MHE">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MHE</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MHE is Material Handling Equipment requiring personnel training, testing, and licensing for use in materiel/cargo handling operations.&lt;SEP&gt;MHE is Material Handling Equipment, coordinated with MSC staff for operations aboard T-AKE ships.&lt;SEP&gt;MHE refers to Material Handling Equipment that requires maintenance, inspections, testing, and certification.&lt;SEP&gt;MHE refers to Material Handling Equipment, including cranes and related items that require qualified operators, rigging support, and compliance with safety standards.&lt;SEP&gt;MHE refers to Material Handling Equipment included in the equipment support and management program.&lt;SEP&gt;Material Handling Equipment (MHE) is included in the Organic GFE Status Report, listing operational, degraded, and nonoperational status along with equipment discrepancies.&lt;SEP&gt;MHE is Material Handling Equipment used to lift suspended loads, required to meet NAVFAC P-307 standards.&lt;SEP&gt;MHE is Material Handling Equipment included in the monthly Organic GFE Status Report.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-abd2ceb311ce78c8a8c1fe38d11ee4f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9fdacd5fbf292ea850730c0c323f0873&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4ef5ed78269155f4369ff9bd9b69ddc8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-27cca63c94e6ea85e547a26e12b48a3c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-65833c099ebcc7aa1fccc5a1d930a7aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="WHE">
  <ns0:data key="d0">WHE</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">WHE refers to Weight Handling Equipment including cranes that requires maintenance, inspections, testing, and certification.&lt;SEP&gt;WHE refers to Weight Handling Equipment, including cranes and lifting devices that must meet load test requirements, operator qualifications, and incident reporting protocols.&lt;SEP&gt;WHE includes Weight Handling Equipment such as cranes, requiring certified operators and management oversight.&lt;SEP&gt;Weight Handling Equipment (WHE) is included in the Organic GFE Status Report and subject to the Navy WHE Program for establishment, maintenance, inspection, testing, certification, operation, and reporting.&lt;SEP&gt;WHE refers to Weight Handling Equipment, including cranes and rigging gear, subject to metrics reporting, procurement from OEM, and program assessments.&lt;SEP&gt;WHE is Wheeled Heavy Equipment included in the monthly Organic GFE Status Report.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9fdacd5fbf292ea850730c0c323f0873&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4ef5ed78269155f4369ff9bd9b69ddc8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-27cca63c94e6ea85e547a26e12b48a3c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MMCT">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MMCT</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MMCT is Maximum Maintenance Cycle Time set at 30 days for Navy GSE with provisions for extensions.&lt;SEP&gt;MMCT is a threshold or metric that cannot be circumvented by intentionally postponing or delaying maintenance actions or closing work orders.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="TEU">
  <ns0:data key="d0">TEU</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">TEU is the Twenty-Foot Equivalent Unit, a measure for container capacity in ship loading plans.&lt;SEP&gt;TEU is Twenty Foot Equivalent Unit containing containerized line items in MPS production.&lt;SEP&gt;Twenty Foot Equivalent Units (TEU) are container units in each MPS production period, averaging 60 units containing 10,000 total containerized line items.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="COSIS">
  <ns0:data key="d0">COSIS</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">COSIS is a condition of supply inspection service performed on Class II and VII ME and CESE assets in open storage, with 90-day intervals for MCPP-PHIL PO assets stored indoors.&lt;SEP&gt;COSIS is Care of Supplies in Storage involving surveillance, inspections, and maintenance to preserve materiel condition.&lt;SEP&gt;COSIS involves providing custody, maintenance, and preparation of prepositioned materiel while forward deployed for exercises and campaigns.&lt;SEP&gt;COSIS is Care of Supplies in Storage, included in baseline production plans created by the MCMC for MCPP activities.&lt;SEP&gt;COSIS is Care of Supplies in Storage, involving specific maintenance actions like filter replacements during PMCS by MCMC.&lt;SEP&gt;COSIS is performed by MCMC on CESE, limited to replacing hydraulic and air system filters during corrective maintenance needs.&lt;SEP&gt;Care of Supplies in Storage (COSIS) is a maintenance requirement included in MCPP II production plans and schedules.&lt;SEP&gt;COSIS is Care of Supplies in Storage, a maintenance requirement included in MCMC production plans for MCPP II.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-955c2fafc0e5a2a07e97130b42a872b5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-13a4841aefad66042f059edb023e607b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93752a7bd8aca85ef0ce5fea3701dc32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a0a00a7bb666b381893da579a6b228c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="USMC">
  <ns0:data key="d0">USMC</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">USMC is the United States Marine Corps, involved in prepositioning programs for equipment and supplies aboard MPS.&lt;SEP&gt;The USMC maintains prepositioned equipment in Norway for MCPP-N including all classes of supply and crew served weapons.&lt;SEP&gt;USMC is the United States Marine Corps, associated with maintenance shop spaces and personnel assigned to MCMC.&lt;SEP&gt;USMC is the United States Marine Corps, responsible for audits, evaluations, and oversight of NTVE, MHE, and WHE records.&lt;SEP&gt;USMC is United States Marine Corps, supported by prepositioning operations.&lt;SEP&gt;The USMC provides baseline parameters for hardware and software configurations and complies with cyber security regulations and directives.&lt;SEP&gt;United States Marine Corps (USMC) ground tactical equipment is balanced with Navy CESE in the production planning process to ensure steady flow and completion within the baseline schedule.&lt;SEP&gt;USMC is the United States Marine Corps, involved in shipboard personnel staffing and technical proposals.&lt;SEP&gt;USMC is referenced in technical methodologies and ACRNs for the Marine Corps Prepositioning Program.&lt;SEP&gt;USMC is the United States Marine Corps, serving as the point of contact for questionnaire submissions and involved in ACRN funding.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-939c604b9027c9cc38a7fb31f4c86c29&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f918f57232ad428f5920d4c98f0af702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9fdacd5fbf292ea850730c0c323f0873&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22de15a10ae9bfba6096cca855d5f78a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b912387d0abf83a18f9cd19906dc41e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f121013aeb8c98e8b0609d68d89b74e5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="FMC">
  <ns0:data key="d0">FMC</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">FMC is Full Mission Capable status declared for equipment after production, including data accuracy.&lt;SEP&gt;FMC refers to full mission capable status targeted for all craft systems and components.&lt;SEP&gt;Fully Mission Capable (FMC) is the operational status that Navy CESE and USMC equipment must achieve by the baseline project finish date, with Letters of Non-Conformance submitted for non-compliant items.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e73c8ab3a0b248cdeedb8496a5c6f8a9</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="BPQRB">
  <ns0:data key="d0">BPQRB</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">event</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Business Process and Quality Review Board (BPQRB) receives updates from MCMC regarding the internal audit schedule.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Quality/Risk Management Review Board">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Quality/Risk Management Review Board</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">event</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Quality/Risk Management Review Board occurs every six months and receives CPI summary briefs from MCMC.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="SL-3">
  <ns0:data key="d0">SL-3</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">SL-3 refers to supply level components including SSRI, UURI, inventory, shelf life criteria, and portable fire extinguishers associated with ME and CESE.&lt;SEP&gt;SL-3 is Supporting List 3 associated with ME, retained or transferred during changes of custody.&lt;SEP&gt;SL-3 establishes standards for component stock levels, inventories, and deficiency reporting for military equipment and SKOTs.&lt;SEP&gt;SL-3 refers to supply liaison data maintained for materiel during transfers and repairs.&lt;SEP&gt;SL-3 refers to unit responsibility items and equipment that MCMC inventories annually during PMCS and stores securely.&lt;SEP&gt;SL-3 Stock Lists are reviewed annually for Using Unit Responsibility Items and updates are requested within 21 days of changes.&lt;SEP&gt;SL-3 refers to equipment parts lists used in inventory and maintenance services.&lt;SEP&gt;SL-3 refers to configuration changes requiring servicing and certification of portable fire extinguishers during MMC production.&lt;SEP&gt;SL-3 refers to associated equipment included in the configuration of TAMCN-controlled Principle End Items.&lt;SEP&gt;SL-3 refers to supply components associated with military equipment, including portable fire extinguishers, requiring specific recording and maintenance.&lt;SEP&gt;SL-3 is a component of mobile loads that must be downloaded and inventoried per TM 4790-14/2 and government-approved schedules.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-955c2fafc0e5a2a07e97130b42a872b5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-abd2ceb311ce78c8a8c1fe38d11ee4f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-13a4841aefad66042f059edb023e607b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8efbcbadad92a347ffdc7b5c1e34b2f7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8a136ea2c9ab7ea9bb718fd0abd010d4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22de15a10ae9bfba6096cca855d5f78a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-68739860c42b764e52f9649ea16ed702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-432adfa735f19522f81538c1e139e7a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="PCL">
  <ns0:data key="d0">PCL</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Planning Considerations Letters (PCLs) are government-provided documents used for downloading, inventorying, and maintaining mobile loads per MCPIC plans.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="PO">
  <ns0:data key="d0">PO</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Pre-positioning Operations (PO) assets are managed through the Navy WHE Program using CMR via DPAS.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CO">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CO</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">person</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Commanding Officer (CO) of BICmd appoints the Weight Handling Program Manager, Licensing Official, and Certifying Official for the Navy WHE Program.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CmdO 4035.1">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CmdO 4035.1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CmdO 4035.1 is a command order on handling containerized hazardous materials.&lt;SEP&gt;CmdO 4035.1 outlines procedures for label replacement and adherence to detailed ships plans.&lt;SEP&gt;CmdO 4035.1 provides instructions for set assembly marking of component parts of disassembled items prior to production completion.&lt;SEP&gt;CmdO 4035.1 provides instructions for labeling assemblies, blocks, containers, packing lists, iMark labels, and placards that MCMC shall adhere to.&lt;SEP&gt;CmdO 4035.1 provides guidance for preparing and labeling mobile loaded equipment and supplies for MPS backload at the conclusion of production cycles.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-22de15a10ae9bfba6096cca855d5f78a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c2bae9a24e71825050f79fc141b2e181&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89b1a9fa6c0722adcd478e665df09141&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="UURI/AAL">
  <ns0:data key="d0">UURI/AAL</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">UURI/AAL is a report that must be submitted within 90 calendar days after contract award and annually no later than March 31, accurate in accordance with equipment SL-3/TM and complete in accordance with GCSS-MC property records.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="SL-3 Stock Lists">
  <ns0:data key="d0">SL-3 Stock Lists</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">SL-3 Stock Lists are reviewed by MCMC, with updates requested via UURI/AAL Authorization Letter in accordance with CmdO 4790.1 within 21 calendar days of changes.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CmdO 4790.1">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CmdO 4790.1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CmdO 4790.1 governs the process for requesting updates to the UURI/AAL Authorization Letter based on SL-3 changes.&lt;SEP&gt;CmdO 4790.1 is a command order on maintenance operations and accountability.&lt;SEP&gt;CmdO 4790.1 is referenced for conducting inventories and requisitioning SL-3 deficiencies.&lt;SEP&gt;CmdO 4790.1 is a command order providing guidance on supply, maintenance management, and commodity reconciliations.&lt;SEP&gt;CmdO 4790.1 provides guidance for garrison special tool allowances and UURI/AAL authorization.&lt;SEP&gt;CmdO 4790.1 (MMSOP) guides Preventive Maintenance Checks and Services (PMCS) and Corrective Maintenance (CM) for Organic Government Furnished Equipment (GFE).&lt;SEP&gt;CmdO 4790.1 is a Command Order that the MCMC Training Program must follow.&lt;SEP&gt;CmdO 4790.1, also known as MMSOP, is used for capturing maintenance requirements as tasks on GCSS-MC Service Requests.&lt;SEP&gt;CmdO 4790.1, also known as MMSOP, provides guidelines for maintenance procedures, including PMCS levels, equipment exercise, and special maintenance actions.&lt;SEP&gt;CmdO 4790.1 governs the conduct and documentation of supply and maintenance management commodity reconciliations.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-955c2fafc0e5a2a07e97130b42a872b5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-13a4841aefad66042f059edb023e607b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8efbcbadad92a347ffdc7b5c1e34b2f7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22de15a10ae9bfba6096cca855d5f78a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2edf7351f7d27be2ca8809d7ac16a11d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-68739860c42b764e52f9649ea16ed702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e151c7682b4ed7c6cd2fcdc2e29ec22&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-432adfa735f19522f81538c1e139e7a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Annual Spend Plan">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Annual Spend Plan</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Annual Spend Plan identifies anticipated GCSS-MC supply system buys required to support MMC and sustainment operations throughout the upcoming fiscal year, developed and submitted by MCMC.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="GCSS-MC">
  <ns0:data key="d0">GCSS-MC</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">GCSS-MC is a supply system used for processing confirmations of receipt, requisitions, issuances, and maintaining audit trails.&lt;SEP&gt;GCSS-MC is a system used for uploading PMCS records, managing supply accounts, and supporting property records and inventory management.&lt;SEP&gt;GCSS-MC is a supply and accounting system used by MCMC for requisitions, obligations, and accountability functions.&lt;SEP&gt;GCSS-MC is a system used by the MCMC for managing min-max inventories, data entry, user accounts, and equipment records.&lt;SEP&gt;GCSS-MC is the Global Combat Support System-Marine Corps used for documenting services, inventory recording, and financial ledger management.&lt;SEP&gt;GCSS-MC is the Global Combat Support System-Marine Corps used for processing adjustments, transactions, and inventory management.&lt;SEP&gt;GCSS-MC is a system used for tracking assets, records, and discrepancies in inventory management.&lt;SEP&gt;GCSS-MC is a system used for service requests, entering NDT results, recording inspections, and uploading PMCS records for equipment maintenance.&lt;SEP&gt;GCSS-MC is an Enterprise Resource Planning system for retail supply and field-level maintenance, integrating logistics, financial, and maintenance functions for the Marine Corps.&lt;SEP&gt;GCSS-MC is an Automated Information System used for updating based on SOUM and MAM, managing DSI inventories, and validating parts.&lt;SEP&gt;GCSS-MC is the system used for recording maintenance tasks, service requests, and documentation for managed equipment.&lt;SEP&gt;GCSS-MC is a supply system used for property records, creating requisitions, and managing approvals, with MCMC handling operations while Government retains the approver role.&lt;SEP&gt;GCSS-MC is the Global Combat Support System - Marine Corps used for accountability, transactions, sub-inventories, and temporary loan status.&lt;SEP&gt;GCSS-MC is a system used for uploading inventory lists for auditability and accountability.&lt;SEP&gt;GCSS-MC is the system used by the MCMC to identify SECREP condition codes, submit disposition requests, and manage inventory adjustments.&lt;SEP&gt;GCSS-MC is a system used by MCMC to record services, tasks, and SL-3 components for CESE maintenance.&lt;SEP&gt;GCSS-MC is a system used for updating equipment status and managing maintenance listings.&lt;SEP&gt;GCSS-MC is a system where MCMC records PMCS service requests and maintenance tasks.&lt;SEP&gt;GCSS-MC is the system utilized to document maintenance services on TAMCN IT assets, including LTI, PM, CM, MI, and SL-3 inventories, in accordance with UM 4000-125 and CmdO 4790.2.&lt;SEP&gt;GCSS-MC is a logistics information system used by MCMC for recording PMCS actions, service requests, equipment status updates, and deferred maintenance.&lt;SEP&gt;GCSS-MC is a record-keeping system for which historical records, including vendor lists, are provided by the incumbent during phase-out.&lt;SEP&gt;GCSS-MC is the system used for documenting quarterly recoil exercises via service requests and M777 Gun Book, and recording PMCS and fuel filter services.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-955c2fafc0e5a2a07e97130b42a872b5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-abd2ceb311ce78c8a8c1fe38d11ee4f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b6f17f0fbf6c678da23e588ab57f6900&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf666a8ded534eb47b7eede4412a01f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-68739860c42b764e52f9649ea16ed702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-65833c099ebcc7aa1fccc5a1d930a7aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89b1a9fa6c0722adcd478e665df09141&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c10c3b1cc4c0a5d44aa2c137a52eaf0b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8a136ea2c9ab7ea9bb718fd0abd010d4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22de15a10ae9bfba6096cca855d5f78a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a0a00a7bb666b381893da579a6b228c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-13a4841aefad66042f059edb023e607b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38be7e49aefd10e870f45cb648f7d79d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e73c8ab3a0b248cdeedb8496a5c6f8a9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8efbcbadad92a347ffdc7b5c1e34b2f7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-30ad74540c8224cf4aff1f3de36d3780&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd3a05bb896b89de7fd366c654ad4a6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bee5e6b5db1fe2dc611fc5fc2b227a51&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="LOGCOM">
  <ns0:data key="d0">LOGCOM</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">LOGCOM coordinates and funds services with Marine Depot Maintenance Command Albany at the request of the MCMC for SECREPs.&lt;SEP&gt;LOGCOM provides funding plans and coordinates with Government for equipment sourcing and asset management.&lt;SEP&gt;LOGCOM performs maintenance and repair services on weapons downloaded from MPF during MMC.&lt;SEP&gt;LOGCOM leads annual RIP recomputations, provides funding plans, and conducts on-site SECREP recomputations with MCMC support.&lt;SEP&gt;LOGCOM is the Marine Corps Logistics Command involved in internal testing and audit support.&lt;SEP&gt;LOGCOM is involved in coordinated SECREP management and lateral support for replenishment.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-abd2ceb311ce78c8a8c1fe38d11ee4f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8efbcbadad92a347ffdc7b5c1e34b2f7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22de15a10ae9bfba6096cca855d5f78a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c2bae9a24e71825050f79fc141b2e181&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-65833c099ebcc7aa1fccc5a1d930a7aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="HQMC">
  <ns0:data key="d0">HQMC</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">HQMC funds Transportation of Things shipping and provides oversight for fiscal management through LPC and LPD.&lt;SEP&gt;HQMC provides budget ceilings as part of the annual funding plan for GCSS-MC expenditures.&lt;SEP&gt;HQMC mandates the use of FMIS for Non-Tactical Vehicles equipment management.&lt;SEP&gt;HQMC is the Headquarters Marine Corps directing equipment transfers in certain situations.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-432adfa735f19522f81538c1e139e7a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-30ad74540c8224cf4aff1f3de36d3780&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Supply/Maintenance Annual Spend Plan">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Supply/Maintenance Annual Spend Plan</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Supply/Maintenance Annual Spend Plan (CDRL 5011) identifies anticipated GCSS-MC supply buys and funding requirements for the upcoming Fiscal Year.&lt;SEP&gt;Supply/Maintenance Annual Spend Plan is a CDRL 5011 deliverable submitted no later than 15 business days after receipt of the Government-provided annual funding plan, identifying projected funding requirements by Class of Supply phased by month.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8efbcbadad92a347ffdc7b5c1e34b2f7</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CDRL 5011">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CDRL 5011</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CDRL 5011 is the designation for the Supply/Maintenance Annual Spend Plan.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Federal Acquisition Regulation (FAR)">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Federal Acquisition Regulation (FAR)</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Federal Acquisition Regulation (FAR) is referenced for developing the Supply/Maintenance Annual Spend Plan.&lt;SEP&gt;Federal Acquisition Regulation (FAR) is referenced for retaining all supply documents.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-a9aba44b05f751488f4a50faebf206cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841049</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="DoD 7000.14-R (FMR)">
  <ns0:data key="d0">DoD 7000.14-R (FMR)</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">DoD 7000.14-R (FMR) is a financial management regulation used in developing the Supply/Maintenance Annual Spend Plan.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MCO 7300.21">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MCO 7300.21</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MCO 7300.21 is a Marine Corps order governing financial management aspects of the Supply/Maintenance Annual Spend Plan.&lt;SEP&gt;MCO 7300.21 outlines Marine Corps orders for financial management in spend planning.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8efbcbadad92a347ffdc7b5c1e34b2f7</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Quarterly Spend Plan Updates">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Quarterly Spend Plan Updates</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Quarterly Spend Plan Updates are CDRL 5012 submissions due no later than December 20 for the second quarter, March 20 for the third quarter, and June 20 for the fourth quarter, revising the Annual Spend Plan with updated forecasts.&lt;SEP&gt;Quarterly Spend Plan Updates (CDRL 5012) are submitted for the 2nd, 3rd, and 4th quarters to reflect changes in projected funding requirements.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8efbcbadad92a347ffdc7b5c1e34b2f7</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CDRL 5012">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CDRL 5012</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CDRL 5012 is the designation for Quarterly Spend Plan Updates.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="SAC 1 and 3 Military Equipment">
  <ns0:data key="d0">SAC 1 and 3 Military Equipment</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">requirement</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">SAC 1 and 3 Military Equipment must be procured and sourced by MCMC in accordance with MCO 4400.201 (Vol 3 &amp; Vol 6), UM 4000-125, TM 4790-14/2, and MCO 4400.16, utilizing excess inventory before requisitioning.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MCO 4400.16">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MCO 4400.16</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MCO 4400.16 governs procurement, sourcing, and time standards for repair parts and maintenance supplies.&lt;SEP&gt;MCO 4400.16 establishes time standards for requisition submissions of repair parts and maintenance supplies.&lt;SEP&gt;MCO 4400.16 outlines policies for acquisition and management of commercial transportation services.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-30ad74540c8224cf4aff1f3de36d3780&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-68739860c42b764e52f9649ea16ed702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="BICmd DoDAACs">
  <ns0:data key="d0">BICmd DoDAACs</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">BICmd DoDAACs are accounts between which equipment redistributions are processed to eliminate deficiencies, requiring Government approval.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Inherently Governmental Function (IGF)">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Inherently Governmental Function (IGF)</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Inherently Governmental Function (IGF) refers to obligating Government funds, which is avoided by MCMC through Government approval in GCSS-MC.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MMV222">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MMV222</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">other</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MMV222 is an account for which MCMC submits requisitions for Military Equipment no later than 60 calendar days prior to production periods.&lt;SEP&gt;MMV222 is the Future Ashore account with equipment requirements based on spreads in detailed plans within MCPIC.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8efbcbadad92a347ffdc7b5c1e34b2f7</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MMV333">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MMV333</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">other</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MMV333 is the Maritime Prepositioning Force account with established allowances based on Prepositioning Objective.&lt;SEP&gt;MMV333 is an account specific to which MCMC submits requisitions for Military Equipment based on production requirements.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8efbcbadad92a347ffdc7b5c1e34b2f7</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MCPP-PHIL (MMV777)">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MCPP-PHIL (MMV777)</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">other</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MCPP-PHIL (MMV777) is an account where all ME T/E and PO allowances must be on hand, on order, or recorded as unfunded deficiencies.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MCPP-N (MMV420)">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MCPP-N (MMV420)</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">other</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MCPP-N (MMV420) is an account managing ME T/E and PO allowances similar to MCPP-PHIL.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="APSR">
  <ns0:data key="d0">APSR</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">APSR is an Accountable Property System of Record used for maintaining materiel accountability, including GCSS-MC and DPAS.&lt;SEP&gt;APSR is the Automated Property System Record used for inventory management, adjustments, and property records.&lt;SEP&gt;APSR is the Automated Property System of Record into which requests for disposition are entered by the MCMC within 20 calendar days of Government approval.&lt;SEP&gt;APSR is the Accountable Property System of Record where property records are maintained and adjusted based on inventory results.&lt;SEP&gt;APSR is a property records system used for submitting requisitions for SAC 3 ME shortfalls.&lt;SEP&gt;APSR is the Accountable Property System of Record in which the MCMC transacts data, incorporating RPAs for efficiency.&lt;SEP&gt;APSR is the respective system of record used for documenting actions on equipment and supplies in the MCPP.&lt;SEP&gt;APSR is the Accountable Property System of Record used for maintaining property records, adjustments, and reconciliations.&lt;SEP&gt;APSR is the Accountability Property System of Record for completing transactions on weapons shipped to and from repair facilities.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22de15a10ae9bfba6096cca855d5f78a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93752a7bd8aca85ef0ce5fea3701dc32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-68739860c42b764e52f9649ea16ed702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c2bae9a24e71825050f79fc141b2e181&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-65833c099ebcc7aa1fccc5a1d930a7aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd3a05bb896b89de7fd366c654ad4a6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a0a00a7bb666b381893da579a6b228c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="SL-3 Assets">
  <ns0:data key="d0">SL-3 Assets</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">requirement</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">SL-3 Assets are procured and sourced by MCMC as deficiencies emerge, in accordance with multiple Marine Corps orders and manuals.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="SSRI Deficiencies">
  <ns0:data key="d0">SSRI Deficiencies</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">requirement</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">SSRI Deficiencies for newly fielded or legacy assets are coordinated by Government with LOGCOM upon MCMC notification.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="General Account (GA) (MMV200)">
  <ns0:data key="d0">General Account (GA) (MMV200)</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">other</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">General Account (GA) (MMV200) is sourced for demand-based consumables on a quarterly basis following Government approval of stock levels.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="SECREPs">
  <ns0:data key="d0">SECREPs</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">requirement</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">SECREPs are sensitive equipment requiring operational and serviceability checks, carried within the MMFAU1 RIP account and subfloats, with accurate condition codes in GCSS-MC.&lt;SEP&gt;SECREPs are managed by MCMC for the MMFAU1 account, sourcing guided by cost avoidance criteria including lateral support and repair.&lt;SEP&gt;SECREPs are Secure Reports or Consolidated Asset Listings for prepositioned equipment accountability.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-65833c099ebcc7aa1fccc5a1d930a7aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MMFAU1">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MMFAU1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">other</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MMFAU1 is the main float account for which SECREPs are sourced to established allowance levels.&lt;SEP&gt;MMFAU1 is the main float location for carcass exchanges and SECREP replenishment.&lt;SEP&gt;MMFAU1 is the account code for RIP where SECREPs are carried and checked.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-abd2ceb311ce78c8a8c1fe38d11ee4f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MMFAQ9">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MMFAQ9</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">other</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MMFAQ9 is an account from which SECREP repair and returns are processed.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Logistics Integrated Support (LIS) Triangle Project">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Logistics Integrated Support (LIS) Triangle Project</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">other</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Logistics Integrated Support (LIS) Triangle Project is utilized by MCMC for F condition SECREPs managed by MPB, involving requests for FTA Buy approval.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MPB">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MPB</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MPB manages F condition SECREPs through the LIS Triangle Project, shipping A condition items if in stock.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="FTA Buy">
  <ns0:data key="d0">FTA Buy</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">requirement</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">FTA Buy is requested by MCMC for approval to ship F condition SECREPs to MPB.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Global CAL">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Global CAL</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Global CAL is reviewed to identify excesses at other RIPs for filling MMFAU1 deficiencies.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="LOGCOM Centralized SECREP Management (CSM)">
  <ns0:data key="d0">LOGCOM Centralized SECREP Management (CSM)</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">LOGCOM Centralized SECREP Management (CSM) office coordinates with MCMC for SECREP lateral support.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="GFE Procurement Requests">
  <ns0:data key="d0">GFE Procurement Requests</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">GFE Procurement Requests are CDRL 5016 submissions for non-T/E allowance items, requiring Government approval prior to procurement.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CDRL 5016">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CDRL 5016</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CDRL 5016 is the designation for GFE Procurement Requests.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Supply Discrepancy Reports (SDR)">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Supply Discrepancy Reports (SDR)</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Supply Discrepancy Reports (SDR) are reports prepared and submitted by the MCMC for variations in received goods, including condition, quantity, and documentation issues, via PDREP or DLA Customer Service Help Desk.&lt;SEP&gt;Supply Discrepancy Reports (SDR) are prepared and submitted via PDREP for variations in received goods.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e151c7682b4ed7c6cd2fcdc2e29ec22</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="PDREP">
  <ns0:data key="d0">PDREP</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">PDREP is the Product Data Reporting and Evaluation Program used for submitting SDRs.&lt;SEP&gt;PDREP is the Product Data Reporting and Evaluation Program used for submitting Supply Discrepancy Reports.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-c2bae9a24e71825050f79fc141b2e181&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Sourced CBRN Equipment Discrepancy Report">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Sourced CBRN Equipment Discrepancy Report</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Sourced CBRN Equipment Discrepancy Report is a CDRL 5017 submission within 5 business days of receiving CBRN equipment to identify discrepancies.&lt;SEP&gt;Sourced CBRN Equipment Discrepancy Report is CDRL 5017 under X002 and X003, due as required, referencing SOW 4.B.5.b.(ii).</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CDRL 5017">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CDRL 5017</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CDRL 5017 is the designation for Sourced CBRN Equipment Discrepancy Report.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CBRN Equipment">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CBRN Equipment</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">requirement</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CBRN Equipment receipt management complies with TI 10010-OR and related manuals, with discrepancies reported via CDRL 5017.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="IUID">
  <ns0:data key="d0">IUID</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Item Unique Identification (IUID) involves placing and registering unique tags on items upon receipt at DMO and associating them using MCPIC applications.&lt;SEP&gt;IUID is Item Unique Identification used for asset visibility, accountability, management, and reporting of materiel via the DoD IUID registry.&lt;SEP&gt;IUID is Item Unique Identification applied to all ME upon receipt at DMO.&lt;SEP&gt;IUID is Item Unique Identification, with tags placed and registered on items in IMARK upon receipt at DMO.&lt;SEP&gt;IUID is Item Unique Identification applied to ground equipment in compliance with MCO 4410.28.&lt;SEP&gt;IUID is Item Unique Identification applied to all ground equipment by MCMC for tracking, legibility, and government acceptance prior to staging.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38be7e49aefd10e870f45cb648f7d79d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-65833c099ebcc7aa1fccc5a1d930a7aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89b1a9fa6c0722adcd478e665df09141&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="pRFID">
  <ns0:data key="d0">pRFID</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Passive Radio Frequency Identification (pRFID) tags are affixed to items using ISO standards and registered in IMARK prior to government acceptance.&lt;SEP&gt;pRFID is passive Radio Frequency Identification used for tagging items and registering in IMARK upon receipt at DMO.&lt;SEP&gt;pRFID is passive Radio Frequency Identification tags placed on all ME upon receipt.&lt;SEP&gt;pRFID is passive Radio Frequency Identification tags placed on items for identification and tracking.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89b1a9fa6c0722adcd478e665df09141&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="DMO">
  <ns0:data key="d0">DMO</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">location</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">DMO is the location where IUID and pRFID tags are applied to ME upon receipt.&lt;SEP&gt;DMO is the Distribution Management Office integrated with warehouse operations for receipt management.&lt;SEP&gt;DMO is the point of receipt for items where the MCMC places and registers IUID and pRFID tags in accordance with MCPIC Data Standards.&lt;SEP&gt;DMO is the receipt location for prepositioned items where IUID and pRFID tags are applied and registered per data standards.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-c2bae9a24e71825050f79fc141b2e181&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89b1a9fa6c0722adcd478e665df09141</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Confirmation of Receipt (COR)">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Confirmation of Receipt (COR)</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Confirmation of Receipt (COR) is processed by MCMC in GCSS-MC at the time of issuing materiel or physical receipt for various accounts.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MPF Maintenance Cycle">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MPF Maintenance Cycle</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">event</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">The MPF Maintenance Cycle involves logistics efforts accomplished aboard ships, in port areas, and at the Blount Island facility.&lt;SEP&gt;The MPF Maintenance Cycle is a time-constrained process lasting approximately 6 months for MPS maintenance, encompassing sustainment and refurbishment.&lt;SEP&gt;MPF Maintenance Cycle production involves processing COR in GCSS-MC when issuing materiel to on-island maintenance commodities.&lt;SEP&gt;MPF Maintenance Cycle involves phase Bravo surveys for Navy watercraft and ABLTS at locations like WDC-I.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-73f90f99a53e4953f841f6b0275ecb2f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93752a7bd8aca85ef0ce5fea3701dc32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MMC">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MMC</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">event</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MMC is a designated production period during which MCMC performs maintenance tasks on ME and CESE assets.&lt;SEP&gt;MMC is the production period during which the MCMC conducts supply operations, inventories, and backloads for ships.&lt;SEP&gt;MMC is supported by GCSS-MC supply system buys and involves production periods, sustainment operations, and maintenance activities.&lt;SEP&gt;MMC is the maintenance management command where normal modifications are deferred and equipment is prepared for offload.&lt;SEP&gt;MMC is the Maritime Prepositioning Ships Maintenance Cycle that involves equipment offload, maintenance production, and preparation activities coordinated by MCMC.&lt;SEP&gt;MMC is the site for on-island operations, supply production, and maintenance activities.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-13a4841aefad66042f059edb023e607b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6b04b67f7f379aa858c2a82b29df69a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22de15a10ae9bfba6096cca855d5f78a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38be7e49aefd10e870f45cb648f7d79d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="P-75 Attainment Deficiency Report">
  <ns0:data key="d0">P-75 Attainment Deficiency Report</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">P-75 Attainment Deficiency Report requires Government approval, after which requisitions are submitted within 10 calendar days for MMV222 and MMV333 accounts.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Unfunded Deficiency List">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Unfunded Deficiency List</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Unfunded Deficiency List records SAC 1 ME shortfalls for applicable accounts as an alternative to submitting requisitions within 30 calendar days.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841050</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MCO 4400.200A">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MCO 4400.200A</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MCO 4400.200A governs SECREP repair and returns and lateral support coordination.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841051</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MCO 4790.2">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MCO 4790.2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MCO 4790.2 is a Marine Corps Order related to maintenance management and commodity reconciliations.&lt;SEP&gt;MCO 4790.2 governs issuance of consumable/expendable stocks and secondary reparable support during MPF exercises.&lt;SEP&gt;MCO 4790.2 is a Marine Corps Order detailing maintenance management functional areas, including administration, records, publications, and supply support.&lt;SEP&gt;MCO 4790.2 specifies recording and reporting requirements for maintenance and supply efforts using GCSS-MC.&lt;SEP&gt;MCO 4790.2 provides guidance on maintenance and custody for equipment in repair, upgrade, and modification programs.&lt;SEP&gt;MCO 4790.2 covers maintenance management, requisition validations, receipt processing, and SECREP handling.&lt;SEP&gt;MCO 4790.2 is a Marine Corps Order providing detailed procedures for maintenance management, validations, reconciliations, inventory control, calibration, modification, equipment records, training, and other programs.&lt;SEP&gt;MCO 4790.2 defines field-level maintenance management policy, known as the Field-Level Maintenance Management Program (FLMMP).&lt;SEP&gt;MCO 4790.2 supports preventive and corrective maintenance requirements for Organic GFE.&lt;SEP&gt;MCO 4790.2 is a Marine Corps Order that the MCMC Training Program must follow.&lt;SEP&gt;MCO 4790.2 provides procedures for maintenance, including SUR, CM, C3, and cannibalization.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-955c2fafc0e5a2a07e97130b42a872b5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-abd2ceb311ce78c8a8c1fe38d11ee4f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-13a4841aefad66042f059edb023e607b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-30e4e078d2ff5ac82b96140f8c79e3f2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2edf7351f7d27be2ca8809d7ac16a11d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-68739860c42b764e52f9649ea16ed702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89b1a9fa6c0722adcd478e665df09141&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bee5e6b5db1fe2dc611fc5fc2b227a51&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a0a00a7bb666b381893da579a6b228c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841051</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="SECNAVINST 4355.18">
  <ns0:data key="d0">SECNAVINST 4355.18</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">SECNAVINST 4355.18 is a Secretary of the Navy instruction outlining procedures for supply discrepancy reports and receipt validations.&lt;SEP&gt;SECNAVINST 4355.18 specifies timelines for submitting Supply Discrepancy Reports.&lt;SEP&gt;SECNAVINST 4355.18 is a Secretary of the Navy instruction on supply discrepancy reporting timelines and procedures.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-c2bae9a24e71825050f79fc141b2e181&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e151c7682b4ed7c6cd2fcdc2e29ec22</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841051</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="NAVSOP-3683C">
  <ns0:data key="d0">NAVSOP-3683C</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">NAVSOP-3683C provides guidance on preparing and following up on Supply Discrepancy Reports.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841051</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="DASF">
  <ns0:data key="d0">DASF</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">DASF is the Due in and Status File used to identify variations in receipts against expected data.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841051</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Unliquidated Obligations (ULO)">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Unliquidated Obligations (ULO)</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Unliquidated Obligations (ULO) involve validations to ensure proper obligations or de-obligations for cancellations, receipts, and requisitions.&lt;SEP&gt;Unliquidated Obligations (ULO) are validated by MCMC to ensure proper obligation or de-obligation for cancellations, receipts, and new requisitions.&lt;SEP&gt;Unliquidated Obligations (ULO) are reconciled and validated by the MCMC against receipts, cancellations, and new requisitions to ensure proper obligation or de-obligation.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-68739860c42b764e52f9649ea16ed702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e151c7682b4ed7c6cd2fcdc2e29ec22</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841051</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Proof of Delivery (POD)">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Proof of Delivery (POD)</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Proof of Delivery (POD) file validations are part of receipt validations by the MCMC.&lt;SEP&gt;Proof of Delivery (POD) file validations are part of receipt validations conducted by MCMC.&lt;SEP&gt;Proof of Delivery (POD) file validations are conducted by the MCMC as part of receipt validations.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-68739860c42b764e52f9649ea16ed702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e151c7682b4ed7c6cd2fcdc2e29ec22</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841051</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="IGC/ITV/WEBVLIPS">
  <ns0:data key="d0">IGC/ITV/WEBVLIPS</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">IGC/ITV/WEBVLIPS are systems researched during receipt validations for reconciliation and tracer actions.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841051</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MCO 4855.10">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MCO 4855.10</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MCO 4855.10 governs receipt management and processing procedures.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841051</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="TI 10010-OR">
  <ns0:data key="d0">TI 10010-OR</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">TI 10010-OR is complied with for CBRN equipment receipt management.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841051</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MCO 4450.12">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MCO 4450.12</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MCO 4450.12 is followed for hazardous materials receipt management.&lt;SEP&gt;MCO 4450.12 provides guidance on storage and warehousing operations for Government-owned property.&lt;SEP&gt;MCO 4450.12 governs the management of radioactive materials within Marine Corps operations.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b825754de20bbf2c5befd6a79730280e</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841051</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="SOW Attachment C.4-2">
  <ns0:data key="d0">SOW Attachment C.4-2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">SOW Attachment C.4-2 provides the format for the Sourced CBRN Equipment Discrepancy Report.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
