<ns0:node id="LOGCOM CBRN Consolidated Storage Program (CSP)">
  <ns0:data key="d0">LOGCOM CBRN Consolidated Storage Program (CSP)</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">LOGCOM CBRN Consolidated Storage Program (CSP) is the source from which CBRN equipment is received, with discrepancies reported.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841051</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Section C.2">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Section C.2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">section</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Section C.2 outlines requirements for supply and maintenance commodity reconciliations.&lt;SEP&gt;Section C.2 of the SOW addresses requirements related to Continuous Process Improvement.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d89c19e067243fa311d34bfc3fa99c70</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841051</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Norway">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Norway</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">location</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Norway hosts the Marine Corps Prepositioning Program – Norway with equipment stored in caves and hangars for global support.&lt;SEP&gt;Norway hosts MCPP-N operations, where recertification is managed by host nation authorities and equipment transport requires prior approval from NJHQ.&lt;SEP&gt;Norway hosts MCPP-N equipment, requiring annual plans for COMM/ELEC PMCS submitted via PPC tool.&lt;SEP&gt;Norway is the location hosting MCPP-N assets, including COMM/ELEC equipment for maintenance.&lt;SEP&gt;Norway hosts prepositioned equipment for MCPP-N including crew served weapons managed by the MCMC.&lt;SEP&gt;Norway hosts the Marine Corps Prepositioning Program Norway.&lt;SEP&gt;Norway is the location for MCPP-N where Confirmation of Receipt is processed upon physical receipt.&lt;SEP&gt;Norway is one of the overseas locations where the MCMC requires access for program operations and exercises.&lt;SEP&gt;Norway is the specific location for annual maintenance, calibration, replenishment, and every third year refresh of MCPP-N AMALs.&lt;SEP&gt;Norway is referenced for joint semi-annual inventories of COMSEC material in off-island land-based local elements.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-f918f57232ad428f5920d4c98f0af702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a9aba44b05f751488f4a50faebf206cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-30e4e078d2ff5ac82b96140f8c79e3f2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22de15a10ae9bfba6096cca855d5f78a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-30ad74540c8224cf4aff1f3de36d3780&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2edf7351f7d27be2ca8809d7ac16a11d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-73f90f99a53e4953f841f6b0275ecb2f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bee5e6b5db1fe2dc611fc5fc2b227a51&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c10c3b1cc4c0a5d44aa2c137a52eaf0b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841051</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Quarterly GA Recommended Stock Levels Report">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Quarterly GA Recommended Stock Levels Report</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Quarterly GA Recommended Stock Levels Report (CDRL 5005) provides recommended stocking levels for consumable materials in the General Account.&lt;SEP&gt;Quarterly GA Recommended Stock Levels Report is proposed by MCMC and requires Government approval for conducting quarterly replenishment buys for the General Account.&lt;SEP&gt;Quarterly GA Recommended Stock Levels Report is CDRL 5005 under X002 and X003, due quarterly, referencing SOW 4.A.2.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8efbcbadad92a347ffdc7b5c1e34b2f7</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841051</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="S-6">
  <ns0:data key="d0">S-6</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">S-6 is the military staff role that authorizes overtime, hardware and software installations, maintenance procedures, and oversees IT operations and procurement.&lt;SEP&gt;S-6 is the communications and information systems staff section providing direction for IT operations, approvals, and support notifications.&lt;SEP&gt;The S-6 authorizes hardware and software installations, provides notifications for maintenance, approves overtime and repairs, and offers regulatory guidance for IT procurements.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-0395bdbad90a448875b2a66efe14f948&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf666a8ded534eb47b7eede4412a01f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841051</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Remedy IT Service Management Suite">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Remedy IT Service Management Suite</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Remedy IT Service Management Suite is the Government-provided software for recording Help Desk calls and service requests.&lt;SEP&gt;Remedy IT Service Management Suite is the government-provided software used for recording help desk calls, service requests, and special projects, subject to potential changes with enterprise architecture.&lt;SEP&gt;Remedy IT Service Management Suite is the current government-provided software product used by the MCMC for recording help desk calls, service requests, and special projects.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-0395bdbad90a448875b2a66efe14f948&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf666a8ded534eb47b7eede4412a01f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841051</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Video Teleconferencing">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Video Teleconferencing</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Video Teleconferencing is an audio/visual system supported by MCMC, including facility coordination, setup, testing, and operation for requests.&lt;SEP&gt;Video Teleconferencing involves facility coordination, setup, testing, and operation for audio/visual information systems, excluding MASS Notification and Installation Surveillance Systems.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-cf666a8ded534eb47b7eede4412a01f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841051</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CmdO 2620.1">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CmdO 2620.1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CmdO 2620.1 outlines preventive maintenance procedures, requirements, authorization processes, and maintenance windows for video and data service delivery equipment.&lt;SEP&gt;CmdO 2620.1 is a Command Order that outlines preventive maintenance procedures, requirements, authorization processes, and maintenance windows for voice, video, and data service delivery equipment.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-cf666a8ded534eb47b7eede4412a01f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841051</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="DISA">
  <ns0:data key="d0">DISA</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">DISA issues Security Technical Implementation Guidelines (STIGs) applicable to hardware and software configurations.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841051</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="STIGs">
  <ns0:data key="d0">STIGs</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">STIGs are Security Technical Implementation Guidelines used for configuring hardware and software in accordance with manufacturer's instructions and USMC baseline parameters.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841051</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="DADMS">
  <ns0:data key="d0">DADMS</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">DADMS is the Department of the Navy Application Database Management System used to verify approved software products prior to installation.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841051</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="COTS">
  <ns0:data key="d0">COTS</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">COTS refers to Commercial Off-the-Shelf products included in hardware and supporting software installations performed by the MCMC.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841051</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="GOTS">
  <ns0:data key="d0">GOTS</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">GOTS refers to Government Off-the-Shelf products included in hardware and supporting software installations and accountability maintained by the MCMC.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841051</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="FAR">
  <ns0:data key="d0">FAR</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">FAR is the Federal Acquisition Regulations that govern directive authority and contract administration.&lt;SEP&gt;FAR is the Federal Acquisition Regulation, requiring documentation of maintenance and testing records for portable fire extinguishers.&lt;SEP&gt;FAR is the Federal Acquisition Regulation followed for IT procurement requests, including preparation of Determinations and Findings forms.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-abd2ceb311ce78c8a8c1fe38d11ee4f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93752a7bd8aca85ef0ce5fea3701dc32</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841051</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="NIST SP 800 Series">
  <ns0:data key="d0">NIST SP 800 Series</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">NIST SP 800 Series provides standards for Information Assurance (IA) certifications that the MCMC must prove annually.&lt;SEP&gt;NIST SP 800 Series establishes standards for Information Assurance certifications that MCMC must prove annually.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-cf666a8ded534eb47b7eede4412a01f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841051</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="DoD 8140">
  <ns0:data key="d0">DoD 8140</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">DoD 8140 is the Cybersecurity Workforce Qualification and Management Program under which the MCMC provides annual proof of IA certifications.&lt;SEP&gt;DoD 8140 is a Department of Defense directive governing minimum qualifications for the Information Assurance Workforce, requiring level II technical certification for IT support positions.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-cf666a8ded534eb47b7eede4412a01f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841051</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="ANSI/ISO 9001:2015">
  <ns0:data key="d0">ANSI/ISO 9001:2015</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">requirement</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">ANSI/ISO 9001:2015 is a quality standard that the contractor must comply with and be certified to within nine months of contract award.&lt;SEP&gt;ANSI/ISO 9001:2015 is a higher-level quality standard that the contractor must comply with and achieve certification within nine months of contract award.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2829fe507a5073eafb2e5fb0cc5e85c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841051</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="52.246-2 Inspection Of Supplies --Fixed Price">
  <ns0:data key="d0">52.246-2 Inspection Of Supplies --Fixed Price</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">clause</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">52.246-2 is a clause incorporated by reference for inspection of supplies under fixed-price contracts.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841051</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Section 11.A">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Section 11.A</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">section</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Section 11.A details MCMC's responsibilities for operating a Help Desk, providing scheduled and unscheduled support, recording service requests using Remedy IT Service Management Suite, supporting audio/visual systems, and maintaining consumable supplies inventory.&lt;SEP&gt;Section 11.A details requirements for after-hours, weekend, and emergency maintenance support by the MCMC, including notification timelines and overtime authorizations.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-cf666a8ded534eb47b7eede4412a01f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841051</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Section 11.B">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Section 11.B</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">section</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Section 11.B specifies MCMC's duties for installing and maintaining accountability of data service delivery hardware and software, including COTS and GOTS products, in compliance with S-6 authorizations, DISA STIGs, and DADMS.&lt;SEP&gt;Section 11.B outlines the MCMC's responsibilities for installation and accountability of data service delivery hardware and software.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-cf666a8ded534eb47b7eede4412a01f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841051</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Section 11.C">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Section 11.C</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">section</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Section 11.C describes MCMC's maintenance responsibilities for video and data service delivery hardware, including documentation in GCSS-MC, preventive maintenance per CmdO 2620.1, and troubleshooting with immediate reporting to S-6.&lt;SEP&gt;Section 11.C specifies maintenance procedures for voice, video, and data service delivery hardware, including preventive maintenance and troubleshooting.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-cf666a8ded534eb47b7eede4412a01f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841051</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Section 11.D">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Section 11.D</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">section</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Section 11.D outlines MCMC's software maintenance tasks, including upgrades, IAVA/STIG implementations, and troubleshooting, in accordance with CmdO 2620.1 and USMC cyber security regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;Section 11.D covers maintenance on voice, video, and data service delivery software, including upgrades, patches, and troubleshooting.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-cf666a8ded534eb47b7eede4412a01f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Section D - Packaging and Marking">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Section D - Packaging and Marking</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">section</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Section D addresses packaging and marking requirements, incorporating clauses for inspection and quality standards.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="252.211-7003 Item Unique Identification and Valuation">
  <ns0:data key="d0">252.211-7003 Item Unique Identification and Valuation</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">clause</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">252.211-7003 is a clause requiring unique item identification for delivered items, including definitions and marking procedures using data matrix symbology.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MCPP">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MCPP</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MCPP refers to the Maritime Prepositioning Program supported by Navy equipment, services, and product delivery under the contract.&lt;SEP&gt;MCPP encompasses exemptions, waivers, and specific maintenance requirements for prepositioned equipment during afloat phases.&lt;SEP&gt;MCPP is the Marine Corps Prepositioning Program that involves multifaceted operations for equipment and supply readiness.&lt;SEP&gt;MCPP encompasses maritime prepositioning ship maintenance cycles, including activities in Norway and Philippines, supported by various systems and plans.&lt;SEP&gt;MCPP refers to Maritime Prepositioning programs, including MCPP-N and MCPP-PHIL, involving specific maintenance periods and asset management.&lt;SEP&gt;MCPP is the Maritime Prepositioning Program, encompassing portable fire extinguishers management and ISO container programs for various locations.&lt;SEP&gt;MCPP is the contract encompassing operations, projection, program management, and afloat/OCONUS activities for which transition tasks are performed.&lt;SEP&gt;MCPP is the mission context for shipboard requirements, watercraft maintenance, and production planning services.&lt;SEP&gt;MCPP is the operational entity supported by the MCMC for voice, video, and data service delivery systems, including network administration and life cycle management recommendations.&lt;SEP&gt;MCPP is the program encompassing requirements for USMC tactical ground equipment, logistics operations, maintenance, supply, distribution, and Navy support elements including CESE, CAPSETs, organic assets, and watercraft.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-13a4841aefad66042f059edb023e607b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-abd2ceb311ce78c8a8c1fe38d11ee4f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6b04b67f7f379aa858c2a82b29df69a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b6f17f0fbf6c678da23e588ab57f6900&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93752a7bd8aca85ef0ce5fea3701dc32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f121013aeb8c98e8b0609d68d89b74e5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b8875a30a8284afacba5893b8971b2b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bee5e6b5db1fe2dc611fc5fc2b227a51&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c10c3b1cc4c0a5d44aa2c137a52eaf0b</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="3rd Network Battalion">
  <ns0:data key="d0">3rd Network Battalion</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">The 3rd Network Battalion receives reports on software failures affecting distribution or server architecture from the MCMC.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Department of the Navy">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Department of the Navy</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">The Department of the Navy maintains the Application Database Management System (DADMS) for verifying approved software products.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Section C.4 Supply">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Section C.4 Supply</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">section</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Section C.4 Supply governs the accountability and disposition of data service delivery hardware, network server hardware, and IT equipment by the MCMC.&lt;SEP&gt;Section C.4 Supply outlines procedures for MCMC to maintain accountability and dispose of data service delivery hardware, network server hardware, and excess IT equipment.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-cf666a8ded534eb47b7eede4412a01f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Section P">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Section P</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">section</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Section P addresses Hazardous Material requirements for the disposition of excess and unserviceable IT equipment.&lt;SEP&gt;Section P addresses Hazardous Material requirements in the disposition of unserviceable IT equipment by MCMC.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-cf666a8ded534eb47b7eede4412a01f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Consumable Supplies">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Consumable Supplies</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Consumable Supplies include items such as printer cartridges, toner, audio visual cables, surge protectors, uninterruptible power supplies, mouse pads, DVDs/CDs, and toolsets for communications support, maintained in inventory by the MCMC.&lt;SEP&gt;Consumable Supplies for Government consumption include printer cartridges, toner, audio visual cables, surge protectors, uninterruptible power supplies, mouse pads, DVDs/CDs, and toolsets, with MCMC maintaining inventory and reporting quarterly when levels drop below 30%.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-cf666a8ded534eb47b7eede4412a01f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Quarterly Inventory Report">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Quarterly Inventory Report</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">The Quarterly Inventory Report details available and consumed consumable supplies for voice, video, and data services, submitted by the MCMC no later than the 5th business day of each quarter.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="IAVA">
  <ns0:data key="d0">IAVA</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">IAVA refers to Information Assurance Vulnerability Assessments implemented as part of software maintenance by the MCMC.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="EULA">
  <ns0:data key="d0">EULA</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">EULA stands for End User Licensing Agreements, which the MCMC complies with during software maintenance and configuration.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Domain Administration">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Domain Administration</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Domain Administration encompasses tasks associated with network administration services performed by the MCMC in support of MCPP operations.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Life Cycle Management">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Life Cycle Management</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Life Cycle Management involves recommendations by the MCMC for hardware, software approaching End of Life or End of Support, or alternative IT solutions supporting the MCPP mission.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Determinations and Findings Form">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Determinations and Findings Form</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">The Determinations and Findings Form is prepared and submitted by the MCMC to the S-6 for all IT procurement requests in accordance with acquisition procedures.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="SOW Attachment C.11-1">
  <ns0:data key="d0">SOW Attachment C.11-1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">annex</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">SOW Attachment C.11-1 contains the Determinations and Findings form used for IT procurement requests.&lt;SEP&gt;SOW Attachment C.11-1 is the Determinations and Findings form that MCMC prepares and submits for all IT procurement requests.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-cf666a8ded534eb47b7eede4412a01f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CmdO 5000.11">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CmdO 5000.11</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CmdO 5000.11 is a command order incorporated by reference into the contract for quality standards.&lt;SEP&gt;CmdO 5000.11 is a Command Order incorporated into the contract, requiring compliance alongside ANSI/ISO 9001:2015 quality standards.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2829fe507a5073eafb2e5fb0cc5e85c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="American Society of Quality">
  <ns0:data key="d0">American Society of Quality</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">American Society of Quality is an organization that recognizes Lean Six Sigma standards.&lt;SEP&gt;The American Society of Quality recognizes Lean Six Sigma principles, concepts, and practices as standards employed by the contractor for quality control.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2829fe507a5073eafb2e5fb0cc5e85c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="52.246-3 Inspection Of Supplies Cost-Reimbursement">
  <ns0:data key="d0">52.246-3 Inspection Of Supplies Cost-Reimbursement</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">clause</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">52.246-3 Inspection Of Supplies Cost-Reimbursement is a clause incorporated by reference dated MAY 2001.&lt;SEP&gt;52.246-3 is a clause incorporated by reference for inspection of supplies under cost-reimbursement contracts.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2829fe507a5073eafb2e5fb0cc5e85c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="52.246-4 Inspection Of Services --Fixed Price">
  <ns0:data key="d0">52.246-4 Inspection Of Services --Fixed Price</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">clause</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">52.246-4 is a clause incorporated by reference for inspection of services under fixed-price contracts.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="52.246-5 Inspection Of Services Cost-Reimbursement">
  <ns0:data key="d0">52.246-5 Inspection Of Services Cost-Reimbursement</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">clause</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">52.246-5 Inspection Of Services Cost-Reimbursement is a clause incorporated by reference dated APR 1984.&lt;SEP&gt;52.246-5 is a clause incorporated by reference for inspection of services under cost-reimbursement contracts.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2829fe507a5073eafb2e5fb0cc5e85c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="52.246-16 Responsibility For Supplies">
  <ns0:data key="d0">52.246-16 Responsibility For Supplies</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">clause</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">52.246-16 Responsibility For Supplies is a clause incorporated by reference dated APR 1984.&lt;SEP&gt;52.246-16 is a clause incorporated by reference addressing responsibility for supplies.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2829fe507a5073eafb2e5fb0cc5e85c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="52.246-11 Higher-Level Contract Quality Requirement">
  <ns0:data key="d0">52.246-11 Higher-Level Contract Quality Requirement</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">clause</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">52.246-11 Higher-Level Contract Quality Requirement is a clause incorporated by full text dated DEC 2014 requiring compliance with higher-level quality standards.&lt;SEP&gt;52.246-11 is a clause incorporated by full text requiring compliance with higher-level quality standards, including certification and flow-down to subcontracts.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2829fe507a5073eafb2e5fb0cc5e85c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Data Matrix">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Data Matrix</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Data Matrix is a two-dimensional matrix symbology used for marking unique item identifiers on items, arranged with modules and perimeter finder pattern per ISO/IEC 16022 ECC200 specification.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Item Unique Identification">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Item Unique Identification</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Item Unique Identification is defined by the acronym IUID.&lt;SEP&gt;Item Unique Identification is a system for marking items delivered to DoD with globally unique and unambiguous identifiers, including concatenated data elements for serialization and traceability.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-46778545759b6a3b0240557a9acb9577&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="DoD Item Unique Identification Registry">
  <ns0:data key="d0">DoD Item Unique Identification Registry</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">DoD Item Unique Identification Registry is a registry where unique item identifiers are marked or registered by the contractor.&lt;SEP&gt;The DoD Item Unique Identification Registry is the system where unique item identifiers are registered to avoid duplication by contractors.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-282e59d5d28c9bf1f8c358524d50c08c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Shelf Life Report">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Shelf Life Report</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Shelf Life Report is a quarterly report submitted as CDRL 6015 on the last day of every quarter for Navy shelf life assets.&lt;SEP&gt;Shelf Life Report is submitted quarterly under section 6.C.4.b for X002.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-c2bae9a24e71825050f79fc141b2e181&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aa9424078fa723e2caaae8aa59fb4397</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Shelf Life/Service Life Management Program">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Shelf Life/Service Life Management Program</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">requirement</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Shelf Life/Service Life Management Program is a program developed and executed for managing Navy shelf life assets and materiel in storage areas.&lt;SEP&gt;Shelf Life/Service Life Management Program is developed and executed by the MCMC for all shelf life assets and materiel in possession, in accordance with specified DoD and Marine Corps instructions.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-c2bae9a24e71825050f79fc141b2e181&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-65833c099ebcc7aa1fccc5a1d930a7aa</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="General Account (GA)">
  <ns0:data key="d0">General Account (GA)</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">General Account (GA) is a Navy-specific account established by COSAL type, maintained within high and low inventory levels using a provided template.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-c2bae9a24e71825050f79fc141b2e181</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="COSAL">
  <ns0:data key="d0">COSAL</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">COSAL is the Coordinated Shipboard Allowance List used to structure sub-inventories in RSupply for different Navy elements.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-c2bae9a24e71825050f79fc141b2e181</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Quarterly Shelf Life/Service Life Expiration Reports">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Quarterly Shelf Life/Service Life Expiration Reports</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Quarterly Shelf Life/Service Life Expiration Reports are accurate reports submitted as CDRL 6016 on the first business day of each quarter.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-c2bae9a24e71825050f79fc141b2e181</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Navy Weekly Status Report">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Navy Weekly Status Report</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Navy Weekly Status Report is a weekly report submitted as CDRL 6017 each Monday by 11:59 am, tracking requisitions and providing recommendations.&lt;SEP&gt;Navy Weekly Status Report is submitted weekly under section 6.C.13 for X002.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-c2bae9a24e71825050f79fc141b2e181&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aa9424078fa723e2caaae8aa59fb4397</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Key Supporting Documents (KSDs)">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Key Supporting Documents (KSDs)</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Key Supporting Documents (KSDs) are documents supporting equipment transfers, audits, and property accountability, uploaded into systems like GCSS-MC and RSupply.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-c2bae9a24e71825050f79fc141b2e181</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Financial Improvement and Audit Readiness (FIAR)">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Financial Improvement and Audit Readiness (FIAR)</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Financial Improvement and Audit Readiness (FIAR) is a framework for audit compliance, including maintaining files of required KSDs and ensuring receipt compliance.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-c2bae9a24e71825050f79fc141b2e181</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Financial Liability Investigation of Property Loss (FLIPL)">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Financial Liability Investigation of Property Loss (FLIPL)</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Financial Liability Investigation of Property Loss (FLIPL) is a process initiated for inventory adjustments related to lost, damaged, or destroyed property.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-c2bae9a24e71825050f79fc141b2e181</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Depot Level Repair (DLR)">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Depot Level Repair (DLR)</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">requirement</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Depot Level Repair (DLR) involves processing returns and requisitions for repair parts, including one-for-one exchanges with DLA and obtaining government approval.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-c2bae9a24e71825050f79fc141b2e181</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Supply Discrepancy Report (SDR)">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Supply Discrepancy Report (SDR)</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Supply Discrepancy Report (SDR) is a report prepared and submitted for discrepancies in receipts, with specific timelines and identifiers.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-c2bae9a24e71825050f79fc141b2e181</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Care of Supplies in Storage (COSIS)">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Care of Supplies in Storage (COSIS)</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Care of Supplies in Storage (COSIS) is a maintenance procedure performed on stored supplies in accordance with supply manuals.&lt;SEP&gt;Care of Supplies in Storage involves preventive and corrective maintenance, modifications, preservation, and management of government assets by MCMC.&lt;SEP&gt;COSIS outlines watercraft monitoring requirements essential during Phase Charlie to prevent progressive damage due to length, environmental conditions, and complexity.&lt;SEP&gt;COSIS involves procedures for equipment configuration and storage care as part of maintenance services.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-c2bae9a24e71825050f79fc141b2e181&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-432adfa735f19522f81538c1e139e7a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c12bdd730383e0d5968b0354d37c6d8a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b8875a30a8284afacba5893b8971b2b3</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="DoD 4140.27-M">
  <ns0:data key="d0">DoD 4140.27-M</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">DoD 4140.27-M is a Department of Defense manual governing materiel management and receipt processing.&lt;SEP&gt;DoD 4140.27-M provides standards for shelf life management of materiel.&lt;SEP&gt;DoD 4140.27-M is a Department of Defense manual referenced for managing short shelf-life material.&lt;SEP&gt;DoD 4140.27-M is a Department of Defense manual referenced for shelf-life management of hazardous material and materiel.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-c2bae9a24e71825050f79fc141b2e181&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a9aba44b05f751488f4a50faebf206cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-65833c099ebcc7aa1fccc5a1d930a7aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e151c7682b4ed7c6cd2fcdc2e29ec22</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="ICART">
  <ns0:data key="d0">ICART</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">ICART is the Internal Controls and Audit Readiness Team involved in inventory testing.&lt;SEP&gt;ICART is the Internal Controls and Audit Readiness Team that receives support from MCMC for sample requirements and validations.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-c2bae9a24e71825050f79fc141b2e181&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-68739860c42b764e52f9649ea16ed702</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="COMNAVFAC">
  <ns0:data key="d0">COMNAVFAC</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">COMNAVFAC is the Naval Facilities Engineering Command involved in internal testing and audit support.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-c2bae9a24e71825050f79fc141b2e181</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="DLA">
  <ns0:data key="d0">DLA</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">DLA is the Defense Logistics Agency to which unserviceable Depot Level Repair items are turned in for exchange.&lt;SEP&gt;DLA is the Defense Logistics Agency that participates in the Rations PBA Annex with I&amp;L (LF) for shelf life management of rations.&lt;SEP&gt;DLA coordinates replenishment of Class I/MRE stocks after T-AKE exercises.&lt;SEP&gt;DLA is Defense Logistics Agency supporting procurement of parts for GSE/GFE.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-c2bae9a24e71825050f79fc141b2e181&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-65833c099ebcc7aa1fccc5a1d930a7aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-abd2ceb311ce78c8a8c1fe38d11ee4f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MILSTRIP">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MILSTRIP</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MILSTRIP is the Military Standard Requisitioning and Issue Procedures used for documenting and processing requisitions.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-c2bae9a24e71825050f79fc141b2e181</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="SECNAVINST 4440.33A">
  <ns0:data key="d0">SECNAVINST 4440.33A</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">SECNAVINST 4440.33A is a Secretary of the Navy instruction on accountable property management and compliance.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-c2bae9a24e71825050f79fc141b2e181</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="SECNAVINST 5200.42">
  <ns0:data key="d0">SECNAVINST 5200.42</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">SECNAVINST 5200.42 is a Secretary of the Navy instruction related to supply chain and accountability processes.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-c2bae9a24e71825050f79fc141b2e181</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="IMDG Code">
  <ns0:data key="d0">IMDG Code</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">IMDG Code is the International Maritime Dangerous Goods Code referenced for container inspections and shipping.&lt;SEP&gt;IMDG Code is the International Maritime Dangerous Goods code for identifying, packaging, and loading hazardous materials.&lt;SEP&gt;IMDG Code governs inspections and recertification of ISO freight containers.&lt;SEP&gt;IMDG Code is the international regulation for the safe transport of dangerous goods by sea, applied to container packing operations.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-c2bae9a24e71825050f79fc141b2e181&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22de15a10ae9bfba6096cca855d5f78a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-abd2ceb311ce78c8a8c1fe38d11ee4f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-30ad74540c8224cf4aff1f3de36d3780</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="DoD 4160.21-M">
  <ns0:data key="d0">DoD 4160.21-M</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">DoD 4160.21-M is a Department of Defense manual referenced for disposition services of equipment and consumables.&lt;SEP&gt;DoD 4160.21-M is a Department of Defense manual on the disposition of materiel and assets.&lt;SEP&gt;DoD 4160.21-M regulates the redistribution, rollback, or disposition of unserviceable, obsolete, or excess materiel.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-c2bae9a24e71825050f79fc141b2e181&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a9aba44b05f751488f4a50faebf206cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-65833c099ebcc7aa1fccc5a1d930a7aa</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MCO 5530.14">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MCO 5530.14</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MCO 5530.14 outlines standards for AA&amp;E access, key control, and custodian nominations that MCMC must adhere to.&lt;SEP&gt;MCO 5530.14 is a Marine Corps Order that governs situations requiring MLSR reporting.&lt;SEP&gt;MCO 5530.14 is a Marine Corps Order on reporting missing, lost, stolen, or damaged government-owned assets.&lt;SEP&gt;MCO 5530.14 provides instructions on markings and identification for materiel.&lt;SEP&gt;MCO 5530.14 outlines standards for access, key control, and handling of AA&amp;E in armory facilities.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-abd2ceb311ce78c8a8c1fe38d11ee4f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22de15a10ae9bfba6096cca855d5f78a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c2bae9a24e71825050f79fc141b2e181&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd3a05bb896b89de7fd366c654ad4a6b</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MCBUL 4440.4">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MCBUL 4440.4</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MCBUL 4440.4 is a Marine Corps Bulletin referenced for inventory adjustment procedures.&lt;SEP&gt;MCBUL 4440.4 is a Marine Corps Bulletin on the Financial Liability Investigation of Property Loss process.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-c2bae9a24e71825050f79fc141b2e181&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd3a05bb896b89de7fd366c654ad4a6b</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MOV">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MOV</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">requirement</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MOV is the Materiel Obligation Validation process conducted quarterly to validate outstanding requisitions and obligations.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-c2bae9a24e71825050f79fc141b2e181</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="SECNAVINST 4855.3">
  <ns0:data key="d0">SECNAVINST 4855.3</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">SECNAVINST 4855.3 is a Secretary of the Navy instruction related to supply management and discrepancy reporting.&lt;SEP&gt;SECNAVINST 4855.3 is a Secretary of the Navy instruction on receipt processing and validation.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-c2bae9a24e71825050f79fc141b2e181&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e151c7682b4ed7c6cd2fcdc2e29ec22</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="ULO">
  <ns0:data key="d0">ULO</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">ULO is Unliquidated Obligations reconciled during receipt validations against outstanding commitments.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-c2bae9a24e71825050f79fc141b2e181</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841052</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="POD">
  <ns0:data key="d0">POD</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">POD is Proof of Delivery validated in receipt processing to confirm shipments.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-c2bae9a24e71825050f79fc141b2e181</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841053</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Navy COR">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Navy COR</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">person</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Navy COR is the Contracting Officer's Representative who receives and completes sections of DD Form 200 for property investigations.&lt;SEP&gt;Navy COR coordinates warranties, receives reports, and approves plans for Navy prepositioning operations.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-c2bae9a24e71825050f79fc141b2e181&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38be7e49aefd10e870f45cb648f7d79d</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841053</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="252.225-7042">
  <ns0:data key="d0">252.225-7042</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">clause</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">252.225-7042 is an authorization to perform applicable to solicitations with performance in foreign countries.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-752a3887d9e623b57dee7c9de056ce5b</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841053</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="252.225-7049">
  <ns0:data key="d0">252.225-7049</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">clause</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">252.225-7049 is a prohibition on acquisition of certain foreign commercial satellite services representations, applicable to satellite service acquisitions.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-752a3887d9e623b57dee7c9de056ce5b</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841053</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="252.225-7050">
  <ns0:data key="d0">252.225-7050</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">clause</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">252.225-7050 is a disclosure of ownership or control by a state sponsor of terrorism, applicable to contracts of $150,000 or more.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-752a3887d9e623b57dee7c9de056ce5b</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841053</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="252.229-7012">
  <ns0:data key="d0">252.229-7012</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">clause</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">252.229-7012 is a tax exemptions representation for Italy, applicable to performance in Italy.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-752a3887d9e623b57dee7c9de056ce5b</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841053</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="252.229-7013">
  <ns0:data key="d0">252.229-7013</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">clause</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">252.229-7013 is a tax exemptions representation for Spain, applicable to performance in Spain.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-752a3887d9e623b57dee7c9de056ce5b</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841053</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="252.209-7002">
  <ns0:data key="d0">252.209-7002</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">clause</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">252.209-7002 is a disclosure of ownership or control by a foreign government, indicated as applicable by the contracting officer.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-752a3887d9e623b57dee7c9de056ce5b</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841053</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="252.225-7000">
  <ns0:data key="d0">252.225-7000</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">clause</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">252.225-7000 is a Buy American Balance of Payments Program certificate, indicated as applicable.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-752a3887d9e623b57dee7c9de056ce5b</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841053</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="252.225-7035">
  <ns0:data key="d0">252.225-7035</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">clause</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">252.225-7035 is a Buy American Free Trade Agreements Balance of Payments Program certificate, indicated as applicable.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-752a3887d9e623b57dee7c9de056ce5b</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841053</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="252.223-7999">
  <ns0:data key="d0">252.223-7999</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">clause</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">252.223-7999 is a clause ensuring adequate COVID-19 safety protocols for federal contractors, implementing Executive Order 14042.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-752a3887d9e623b57dee7c9de056ce5b</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841053</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Executive Order 14042">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Executive Order 14042</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Executive Order 14042 ensures adequate COVID-19 safety protocols for federal contractors, dated September 9, 2021.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-752a3887d9e623b57dee7c9de056ce5b</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841053</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Safer Federal Workforce Task Force">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Safer Federal Workforce Task Force</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Safer Federal Workforce Task Force publishes guidance on COVID-19 protocols for contractor workplaces.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-752a3887d9e623b57dee7c9de056ce5b</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841053</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Italy">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Italy</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">location</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Italy is a location for contract performance where specific tax exemption representations apply.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-752a3887d9e623b57dee7c9de056ce5b</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841053</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Spain">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Spain</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">location</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Spain is a location for contract performance where specific tax exemption representations apply.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-752a3887d9e623b57dee7c9de056ce5b</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841053</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="252.225-7043">
  <ns0:data key="d0">252.225-7043</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">clause</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">252.225-7043 is an antiterrorism/force protection policy for defense contractors outside the United States.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-752a3887d9e623b57dee7c9de056ce5b</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841053</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Overseas Security Advisory Council">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Overseas Security Advisory Council</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Overseas Security Advisory Council is an entity that U.S. contractors must affiliate with when performing outside the United States.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-752a3887d9e623b57dee7c9de056ce5b</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841053</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="252.232-7007">
  <ns0:data key="d0">252.232-7007</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">clause</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">252.232-7007 is a limitation on the government's obligation for incrementally funded contract line items.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-752a3887d9e623b57dee7c9de056ce5b</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841053</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="252.237-7023">
  <ns0:data key="d0">252.237-7023</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">clause</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">252.237-7023 is a continuation of essential contractor services clause defining requirements during crisis situations.&lt;SEP&gt;252.237-7023 requires a plan for continuation of essential contractor services during crises.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-939c604b9027c9cc38a7fb31f4c86c29&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-752a3887d9e623b57dee7c9de056ce5b</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841053</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Essential Contractor Service">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Essential Contractor Service</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Essential Contractor Service is a service supporting DoD mission-essential functions that must continue during crises.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-752a3887d9e623b57dee7c9de056ce5b</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841053</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Mission-Essential Functions">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Mission-Essential Functions</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Mission-Essential Functions are organizational activities that must be performed under all circumstances to achieve DoD missions.&lt;SEP&gt;Mission-essential functions are defined in clause 252.237-7023 and addressed in the offeror's continuity plan.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-752a3887d9e623b57dee7c9de056ce5b</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
