<ns0:node id="CLIN">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CLIN</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CLIN refers to Contract Line Item Number used in task orders for describing work, quantities, prices, and fees.&lt;SEP&gt;CLIN is Contract Line Item Number, with allocations and funding provided by the Government for exercise support.&lt;SEP&gt;CLIN refers to all contract line items under the contract for which the offeror must plan continuation of essential services during crises.&lt;SEP&gt;CLIN refers to Contract Line Item Number, used for pricing and summarizing costs in Schedule B and proposal summaries.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-d89c19e067243fa311d34bfc3fa99c70&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b912387d0abf83a18f9cd19906dc41e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-752a3887d9e623b57dee7c9de056ce5b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022</ns0:data>
