</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="31 U.S.C. 1342">
  <ns0:data key="d0">31 U.S.C. 1342</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">31 U.S.C. 1342 is a statute prohibiting acceptance of voluntary services, referenced to clarify no authorization in the funding clause.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-752a3887d9e623b57dee7c9de056ce5b</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Destructive Weather Plan">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Destructive Weather Plan</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Destructive Weather Plan (DWP) is an NAV-P approved plan created and executed by MCMC for preparing Navy Watercraft and LARCs against hurricanes or major weather events, reviewed annually NLT 1 May.&lt;SEP&gt;Destructive Weather Plan addresses NAVFAC P-307 and CmdO 3440 requirements for Navy-owned cranes, including crawler cranes, rough terrain cranes, and mobile boat hoists, with a current copy maintained in each operator's cab.&lt;SEP&gt;Destructive Weather Plan is defined by the acronym DWP.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-46778545759b6a3b0240557a9acb9577&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7659b0abfc62a3f8f0edbf4a1fee058e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="WHE Program">
  <ns0:data key="d0">WHE Program</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">program</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">WHE Program involves weight handling equipment operations, including internal self-assessments reported annually and support for government-led assessments.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CDRL 6073">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CDRL 6073</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CDRL 6073 is the monthly WHP Monitoring Observation Report, including observations of weight handling evolutions, maintenance inspections, load testing, and deficiencies per NAVFAC P-307 section 2.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="NAVSEA Standard Items">
  <ns0:data key="d0">NAVSEA Standard Items</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">NAVSEA Standard Items, per NAVSEAINST 9070.1, guide surveys, statements of work, and maintenance for Navy watercraft, ABLTS, and lighterage.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Navy Watercraft">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Navy Watercraft</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Navy Watercraft are vessels requiring organizational level maintenance, corrosion control, cleaning, and protection measures to ensure operational readiness and compliance with military standards.&lt;SEP&gt;Navy Watercraft includes vessels requiring structural, mechanical, electronics, electrical, deck drain, and coating systems surveys during MPF Maintenance Cycle.&lt;SEP&gt;Navy Watercraft includes various vessels such as MPFUB, LCM-8, INLS WT, CFPMs, BMs, and CCS that require maintenance, fueling, and certification as per production schedules.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-7659b0abfc62a3f8f0edbf4a1fee058e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d6887833d0f1a6398bb6c8fd6f72d5c8</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="ABLTS">
  <ns0:data key="d0">ABLTS</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">ABLTS is Amphibious Bulk Liquid Transfer System, a prioritized NSE force module covered in attainment reports and service life data.&lt;SEP&gt;ABLTS are lighterage systems maintained by MCMC, involving coating systems, cleaning, and preparation for embarkation, with specific requirements for custody transfer and operational checks.&lt;SEP&gt;ABLTS are landing craft included in reporting requirements for craft status and mitigation efforts.&lt;SEP&gt;ABLTS refers to Amphibious Bulk Liquid Transfer Systems supported in surveys and maintenance as part of Navy watercraft operations.&lt;SEP&gt;ABLTS is a type of Navy Watercraft and associated rigging gear requiring maintenance, trials, and scheduling per milestones.&lt;SEP&gt;ABLTS are all-terrain lighterage systems requiring load testing, maintenance, rigging inspections, and fueling by MCMC.&lt;SEP&gt;ABLTS is a type of Navy watercraft for which MCMC performs maintenance at the WMC.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-955c2fafc0e5a2a07e97130b42a872b5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d6887833d0f1a6398bb6c8fd6f72d5c8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-85b50b451f72c11f155dc39b516d8dd3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7659b0abfc62a3f8f0edbf4a1fee058e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e73c8ab3a0b248cdeedb8496a5c6f8a9</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CDRL 6074">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CDRL 6074</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CDRL 6074 is the Corrosion Survey Report included in the Detailed Report of Findings from Navy Watercraft and ABLTS surveys, provided within 60 calendar days of MPS offload.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CDRL 6075">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CDRL 6075</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CDRL 6075 provides individual and descriptive scopes of work for repair requirements identified in initial surveys of Navy Watercraft and amphibious systems, serialized with unique identifiers.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CDRL 6076">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CDRL 6076</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CDRL 6076 is an itemized cost estimate for Navy repairs identified in scopes of work, provided within 10 business days per FAR Subpart 15.4.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CDRL 6077">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CDRL 6077</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CDRL 6077 is a detailed and descriptive Statement of Work for recurring support tasks, MRP standard work items, or services for Navy lighterage and ABLTS, provided within 10 business days.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Repair Log">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Repair Log</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Repair Log, as CDRL 6081, tracks Navy Corrective Maintenance with details on MPS assignment, serial numbers, completion status, and work descriptions, updated weekly.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Marine Corps Order 5100.29">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Marine Corps Order 5100.29</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Marine Corps Order 5100.29 sets safety and occupational health requirements that MCMC must comply with.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="SECTION C.7">
  <ns0:data key="d0">SECTION C.7</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">section</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">SECTION C.7 delineates activities for shipboard and exercise support during the Afloat Phase of the MPF Program, including surveillance, maintenance, and logistics for MPE/S.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MPE/S">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MPE/S</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MPE/S are Maritime Prepositioned Equipment and Supplies managed for physical inventory and accountability.&lt;SEP&gt;MPE/S encompasses non-expendables/ME and expendables/consumables/sustainment blocks, with disparities identified between GCSS-MC and MCPIC.&lt;SEP&gt;MPE/S refers to Marine Prepositioned Equipment and Supplies that require visual inspections every 30 days, corrective maintenance, and validation during exercises.&lt;SEP&gt;MPE/S includes Maritime Prepositioning Equipment and Supplies, such as military equipment, containers, CESE, aviation support equipment, and communication end items, subject to surveillance and maintenance.&lt;SEP&gt;MPE/S is Maritime Prepositioning Equipment and Supplies deployed in support of USMC/USN Operating Forces.&lt;SEP&gt;MPE/S is the Maritime Prepositioning Equipment/Supplies Continuum supported by MCMC maintenance services during MPS phases.&lt;SEP&gt;MPE/S refers to Maritime Prepositioned Equipment and Supplies validated, checked, and issued by MCMC during exercises and operations.&lt;SEP&gt;MPE/S refers to Maritime Prepositioning Equipment and Supplies that are repaired, validated, and managed by MCMC to ensure mission capability and compliance with operational plans.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-f918f57232ad428f5920d4c98f0af702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-abd2ceb311ce78c8a8c1fe38d11ee4f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38be7e49aefd10e870f45cb648f7d79d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="PMCS">
  <ns0:data key="d0">PMCS</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">requirement</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">PMCS refers to Preventive Maintenance Checks and Services procedures necessary for equipment exposed to harsh environments, including annual checks during regeneration and reconstitution.&lt;SEP&gt;PMCS refers to Preventive Maintenance Checks and Services conducted on ME, CESE, and GFE assets in accordance with applicable TMs and rosters.&lt;SEP&gt;PMCS is Preventive Maintenance Checks and Services performed by MCMC on Navy CESE, including NCE, NSE, and Expeditionary Medical Facility equipment, using OMMS-NG.&lt;SEP&gt;PMCS refers to Preventive Maintenance Checks and Services performed as part of COSIS corrective actions.&lt;SEP&gt;PMCS involves Operator Level Preventive Maintenance Checks and Services on MPE/S assets per equipment manuals, performed every six months or after backloads.&lt;SEP&gt;PMCS encompasses preventive maintenance checks and services performed on downloaded weapons by LOGCOM.&lt;SEP&gt;PMCS is Preventive Maintenance Checks and Services performed on Navy GSE and GFE according to OEM manuals.&lt;SEP&gt;PMCS is Preventive Maintenance Checks and Services performed by MCMC on Navy CESE using OMMS-NG.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-955c2fafc0e5a2a07e97130b42a872b5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-13a4841aefad66042f059edb023e607b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8efbcbadad92a347ffdc7b5c1e34b2f7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22de15a10ae9bfba6096cca855d5f78a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Battery Maintenance">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Battery Maintenance</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">requirement</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Battery Maintenance includes testing, servicing, charging, and replacement of lead-acid, hold-up, and UPS batteries for ME and CESE assets.&lt;SEP&gt;Battery Maintenance involves testing, servicing, and maintaining Navy equipment batteries for square loaded MPE/S.&lt;SEP&gt;Battery Maintenance requires regular testing and charging of batteries to maintain SOC, with specific plans for MCTAGS, THHRs, and M777A2 systems during afloat phase.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-c10c3b1cc4c0a5d44aa2c137a52eaf0b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e73c8ab3a0b248cdeedb8496a5c6f8a9</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Stock Checks">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Stock Checks</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">requirement</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Stock Checks involve visual inspections of MPE/S every 30 days for safety, security, fuel levels, and defects, with weekly checks on refrigerated containers.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="300 Ton Crawler Crane">
  <ns0:data key="d0">300 Ton Crawler Crane</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">300 Ton Crawler Crane is a type of crane that licensed operators must be qualified to operate per NAVFAC P-307.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="65 Ton Rough Terrain Crane">
  <ns0:data key="d0">65 Ton Rough Terrain Crane</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">65 Ton Rough Terrain Crane is a type of crane for which operators must be licensed IAW NAVFAC P-307.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Critical Lift">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Critical Lift</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Critical Lift is defined per section 10 of NAVFAC P-307, requiring specific plans prior to execution.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CDRL 6078">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CDRL 6078</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CDRL 6078 is an itemized cost estimate for recurring support tasks or services IAW the scope of work, provided within 10 business days.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CDRL 6079">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CDRL 6079</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CDRL 6079 is a Statement of Work IAW NAVSEA Standard Items for government identified maintenance tasks in support of organic lighterage, serialized with unique identifiers, provided within 10 business days.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CDRL 6080">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CDRL 6080</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CDRL 6080 is an itemized cost estimate for repairs to organic equipment supporting Navy mission requirements IAW the statement of work, provided within 10 business days.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Detailed Report of Findings">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Detailed Report of Findings</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Detailed Report of Findings from the Navy Watercraft and ABLTS Survey includes the Corrosion Survey Report and MCMC recommended Corrective Maintenance Memo, provided within 60 calendar days of MPS offload.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Corrective Maintenance Memo">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Corrective Maintenance Memo</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Corrective Maintenance Memo is MCMC recommended actions based on survey findings, provided to NAV-P within 60 calendar days of MPS offload.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="FAR Subpart 15.4">
  <ns0:data key="d0">FAR Subpart 15.4</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">FAR Subpart 15.4-Contract Pricing governs the format and requirements for itemized cost estimates provided by MCMC.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="LARC">
  <ns0:data key="d0">LARC</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">LARC is a type of Navy watercraft maintained by MCMC at the dedicated LARC Maintenance Facility within the WMC.&lt;SEP&gt;LARC is a type of Navy Watercraft requiring organizational level maintenance, selective intermediate maintenance, and specific facility support.&lt;SEP&gt;LARC is Navy Watercraft included in structural, mechanical, electronics, electrical, deck drain, and coating systems surveys during Phase Bravo of MPF Maintenance Cycle.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-955c2fafc0e5a2a07e97130b42a872b5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-85b50b451f72c11f155dc39b516d8dd3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="WDC-I">
  <ns0:data key="d0">WDC-I</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">location</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">WDC-I is a typical location for MPS offload where surveys and reports are initiated during MPF Maintenance Cycle.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="29 CFR 1910">
  <ns0:data key="d0">29 CFR 1910</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">29 CFR 1910 is a regulatory standard referenced for fire extinguisher inspections, fire warden designations, evacuation routes, fire drills, and various safety programs.&lt;SEP&gt;29 CFR 1910 is a Code of Federal Regulations section establishing occupational safety and health standards for general industry.&lt;SEP&gt;29 CFR 1910 is part of safety and occupational health requirements that MCMC must comply with IAW Marine Corps Order 5100.29.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-070bdd3969938da07f8e836e32dfa592&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b825754de20bbf2c5befd6a79730280e</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="29 CFR 1915">
  <ns0:data key="d0">29 CFR 1915</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">29 CFR 1915 is part of safety and occupational health requirements applicable to MCMC operations.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="NFPA Codes">
  <ns0:data key="d0">NFPA Codes</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">NFPA Codes and standards are applicable to MCMC for safety and occupational health compliance IAW Section 10.B.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Afloat Phase">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Afloat Phase</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">event</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Afloat Phase for MPF waives monthly and annual inspections for portable fire extinguishers.&lt;SEP&gt;Afloat Phase is the operational phase of the MPF Program involving shipboard surveillance, maintenance, and logistics for MPE/S aboard MPS.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-abd2ceb311ce78c8a8c1fe38d11ee4f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MPF Program">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MPF Program</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MPF Program involves prepositioning assets with timelines driven by shipyard requirements for afloat programs and flexibility for ashore sites.&lt;SEP&gt;MPF Program is the Maritime Prepositioning Force program that utilizes squadron and ship level plans developed over an 18-month planning process.&lt;SEP&gt;MPF Program is the Maritime Prepositioning Force Program encompassing afloat phase activities, maintenance cycles, and exercise support.&lt;SEP&gt;MPF Program is the Maritime Prepositioning Force Program involving Navy watercraft and assets assigned for prepositioning support.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-6b04b67f7f379aa858c2a82b29df69a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38be7e49aefd10e870f45cb648f7d79d</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MCO P3000.17">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MCO P3000.17</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MCO P3000.17 governs surveillance, maintenance, and logistics services to be accomplished by MCMC for Navy equipment during the afloat phase.&lt;SEP&gt;MCO P3000.17 delineates activities required during the Afloat Phase, including surveillance, maintenance, and logistics services.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e73c8ab3a0b248cdeedb8496a5c6f8a9</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MCPP Contract">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MCPP Contract</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MCPP Contract governs shipboard logistics services aboard MPS, performed in accordance with the afloat phase surveillance schedule.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Maintenance Support Team">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Maintenance Support Team</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Maintenance Support Team is defined by the acronym MST.&lt;SEP&gt;Maintenance Support Team (MST) supports scheduled and unscheduled downloads during MPS operations as directed by the Government.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-46778545759b6a3b0240557a9acb9577&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="ME">
  <ns0:data key="d0">ME</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">ME refers to Military Equipment that requires various maintenance services including fuel filtration, washing, lubrication, corrective maintenance, and COSIS.&lt;SEP&gt;ME is management effectiveness valued in mission areas like production operations and sustainment, scored on a scale from -18 to +18 based on KPIs.&lt;SEP&gt;ME refers to Major End Items managed for accountability, transfers, and chain of custody in prepositioning programs.&lt;SEP&gt;ME refers to Marine Equipment subject to calibration control, operational status reporting, and maintenance programs managed by the MCMC.&lt;SEP&gt;ME is Prepositioned Military Equipment subject to afloat phase surveillance by MCMC.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-13a4841aefad66042f059edb023e607b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bee5e6b5db1fe2dc611fc5fc2b227a51&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a0a00a7bb666b381893da579a6b228c9</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CESE">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CESE</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CESE refers to assets that undergo fuel filtration, washing, lubrication, corrective maintenance, SL-3 inventory, and modification instructions similar to ME.&lt;SEP&gt;CESE refers to Construction Equipment Support Equipment for the Navy, subject to various maintenance procedures such as PMCS, SUR, and fuel filtration.&lt;SEP&gt;CESE encompasses Navy civil engineering support equipment subject to maintenance, inspections, PMCS, and other services by MCMC.&lt;SEP&gt;CESE is Civil Engineer Support Equipment assets not resident in GCSS-MC.&lt;SEP&gt;CESE is Construction Equipment Support Equipment included in all NSE and NCE assets issued and managed by MCMC.&lt;SEP&gt;CESE is Civil Engineering Support Equipment included in MPE/S surveillance during the afloat phase.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-955c2fafc0e5a2a07e97130b42a872b5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-13a4841aefad66042f059edb023e607b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38be7e49aefd10e870f45cb648f7d79d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="SASU">
  <ns0:data key="d0">SASU</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">event</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">SASU is Semi-Annual Start-Ups for square loaded rolling and non-rolling stock, during which operator PMCS are performed.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="TM 9-6140-200-13">
  <ns0:data key="d0">TM 9-6140-200-13</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">TM 9-6140-200-13 specifies testing, servicing, and maintenance for equipment lead-acid batteries.&lt;SEP&gt;TM 9-6140-200-13 outlines procedures for testing, servicing, and maintaining Navy equipment lead-acid batteries.&lt;SEP&gt;TM 9-6140-200-13 provides guidance on battery testing and maintenance, requiring batteries at 12.1 volts or higher for SOC of 35% or more.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-955c2fafc0e5a2a07e97130b42a872b5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c10c3b1cc4c0a5d44aa2c137a52eaf0b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="ATO">
  <ns0:data key="d0">ATO</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">ATO is Authority to Operate for Tactical Communications Systems and associated equipment, affected by modifications coordinated by MCMC.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="ATC">
  <ns0:data key="d0">ATC</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">ATC is Authority to Connect for Tactical Communications Systems to Marine Corps Tactical Networks, requiring modification coordination.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MCTAGS">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MCTAGS</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MCTAGS is a technology installed on MTVR and LVSR platforms according to specific detailed plans.&lt;SEP&gt;MCTAGS batteries are installed and maintained in prepositioned tactical motor transport vehicles, with accountability and tracking procedures between island and shipboard personnel.&lt;SEP&gt;MCTAGS batteries are installed in tactical vehicles like ECV FOV, MTVR FOV, LVSR FOV, and JLTV FOV, with effective battery plans for mobile loaded or containerized systems.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="THHRs">
  <ns0:data key="d0">THHRs</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">THHRs are Tactical Hand Held Radios maintained IAW GEI-24-SAPS and equipment TMs, kept in SAPS with primary batteries when not in use.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="SAPS">
  <ns0:data key="d0">SAPS</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">SAPS is Stay Alive Power Systems used to maintain THHRs and batteries during afloat phase.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841054</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="M777A2">
  <ns0:data key="d0">M777A2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">M777A2 howitzer requires quarterly recoil exercises every 90 days after backload, documented in GCSS-MC, and battery removal/maintenance with notification to Operation Department.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841055</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="TI 10407C-OR/3">
  <ns0:data key="d0">TI 10407C-OR/3</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">TI 10407C-OR/3 provides instructions for quarterly recoil exercises on M777A2.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841055</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="UM 4000.125">
  <ns0:data key="d0">UM 4000.125</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">UM 4000.125 is the Retail Supply and Maintenance Execution Procedures referenced for MCMC's supply operations.&lt;SEP&gt;UM 4000.125 guides documentation of quarterly recoil exercises in GCSS-MC for M777A2.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-8a136ea2c9ab7ea9bb718fd0abd010d4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841055</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Operation Department Shipboard Branch">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Operation Department Shipboard Branch</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Operation Department Shipboard Branch is notified by MCMC upon removal of M777A2 batteries during afloat phase.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841055</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="DD1149">
  <ns0:data key="d0">DD1149</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">DD1149 is a form completed by MCMC to generate requests for fuel issue from ship's masters.&lt;SEP&gt;DD1149 is the form completed by MCMC to generate requests for fuel issue from ship's masters for maintaining MPE/S fuel levels.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841055</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="SITREP">
  <ns0:data key="d0">SITREP</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">SITREP is the monthly report to which MCMC adds refrigerated container discrepancies observed during weekly checks.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841055</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="EBFL">
  <ns0:data key="d0">EBFL</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">EBFL is an Extended Boom Fork Lift that requires lubricity fuel filter replacements every 250 hours or 6 months.&lt;SEP&gt;EBFL is Extended Boom Fork Lift requiring replacement of lubricity fuel filters every 250 hours or 6 months, marked with change date and recorded in GCSS-MC.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841055</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Refrigerated Containers">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Refrigerated Containers</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Refrigerated Containers store Supply Class I, II, IV, and VIII items and require weekly temperature monitoring by MCMC.&lt;SEP&gt;Refrigerated Containers holding Supply Class I, II, IV, and VIII items are checked weekly for temperature, with readings maintained at specified levels and abnormalities reported.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841055</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Section C-2">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Section C-2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">section</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Section C-2 outlines requirements for supply and maintenance management reconciliations.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-68739860c42b764e52f9649ea16ed702</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841055</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MMV200 General Account">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MMV200 General Account</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MMV200 General Account serves as the primary source of supply for consumables supporting maintenance operations of prepositioning assets.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-68739860c42b764e52f9649ea16ed702</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841055</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CDRL 5018">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CDRL 5018</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CDRL 5018 is the deliverable for the annual Physical Inventory Control Plan submission.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-68739860c42b764e52f9649ea16ed702</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841055</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CDRL 5019">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CDRL 5019</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CDRL 5019 is the deliverable for draft GCSS-MC Item Master Organization Load Requests.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-68739860c42b764e52f9649ea16ed702</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841055</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="DLA-E">
  <ns0:data key="d0">DLA-E</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">DLA-E is the Defense Logistics Agency Energy responsible for capitalized fuel facilities.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-68739860c42b764e52f9649ea16ed702</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841055</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MARCORLOGCOMO 4440.1">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MARCORLOGCOMO 4440.1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MARCORLOGCOMO 4440.1 is an order providing guidance on Physical Inventory Control Plans.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-68739860c42b764e52f9649ea16ed702</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
