</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Past Performance Questionnaire">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Past Performance Questionnaire</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Past Performance Questionnaire is S-Attachment #3 pertaining to the solicitation.&lt;SEP&gt;Past Performance Questionnaire is Solicitation Attachment #3 to be completed by offerors and assessors for evaluation.&lt;SEP&gt;Past Performance Questionnaire consists of Sections I and II to be completed by offerors for each relevant contract and emailed to assessors within 7 days after solicitation issuance.&lt;SEP&gt;Past Performance Questionnaire is a component of Volume V, limited to 10 pages, for gathering performance data.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-6b04b67f7f379aa858c2a82b29df69a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f121013aeb8c98e8b0609d68d89b74e5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b912387d0abf83a18f9cd19906dc41e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841059</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Non-Disclosure Agreement">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Non-Disclosure Agreement</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Non-Disclosure Agreement is S-Attachment #4 pertaining to the solicitation.&lt;SEP&gt;The Non-Disclosure Agreement must be completed and executed by offerors to receive the Contract Reference Library.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-33458028830a7ae0043a51d8a7a1e726&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841059</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Contract Data Requirements List">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Contract Data Requirements List</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Contract Data Requirements List outlines various deliverables under CLINs, including appointment letters, schedules, reports, and plans with specific frequencies and references to the Statement of Work.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841059</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Maintenance Management Office Manager Appointment Letter">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Maintenance Management Office Manager Appointment Letter</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Maintenance Management Office Manager Appointment Letter is CDRL 1003 under X001, due NLT 10 business days after contract award and thereafter NLT 5 business days after personnel changes, referencing SOW 2.B.1.a.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841059</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="UND Delegation of Authority Letter">
  <ns0:data key="d0">UND Delegation of Authority Letter</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">UND Delegation of Authority Letter is CDRL 1004 under X001, due within 10 business days of contract award and new hires, and NLT 10 business days after 1 January and 1 July annually, referencing SOW 2.B1.c.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841059</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Assessment/Inspection Schedule">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Assessment/Inspection Schedule</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Assessment/Inspection Schedule is CDRL 1005 under X001, due within 21 business days of contract award, with changes, and 5 business days after 1 July annually, referencing SOW 2.B.1.e.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841059</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Internal Inspection Results">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Internal Inspection Results</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Internal Inspection Results is CDRL 1006 under X001, due within 10 business days of completing inspection, referencing SOW 2.B.1.f.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841059</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Plan of Corrective Action">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Plan of Corrective Action</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Plan of Corrective Action is CDRL 1007 under X001, due within 21 business days after inspection conclusion, referencing SOW 2.B.1.g.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841059</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="General Services Administration">
  <ns0:data key="d0">General Services Administration</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">General Services Administration is defined by the acronym GSA.&lt;SEP&gt;General Services Administration is referenced in ordering procedures for supply schedules and nonmandatory contracts.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-46778545759b6a3b0240557a9acb9577&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841059</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Department of Labor">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Department of Labor</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Department of Labor provides the Wage Determination WD-15-4539 as Attachment #2.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841059</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Essential Contractor Services">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Essential Contractor Services</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Essential Contractor Services refers to services the contractor must perform during crisis situations as directed, including planning, notification, and continuity measures.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841059</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="252.237-7023 Continuation of Essential Contractor Services">
  <ns0:data key="d0">252.237-7023 Continuation of Essential Contractor Services</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">clause</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">252.237-7023 is the clause providing definitions for essential contractor service and mission-essential functions, referenced in the solicitation.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841059</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="252.237-7024 Notice of Continuation of Essential Contractor Services">
  <ns0:data key="d0">252.237-7024 Notice of Continuation of Essential Contractor Services</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">clause</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">252.237-7024 is the provision dated OCT 2010 requiring the offeror to provide a plan for essential contractor services during crises.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841059</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="252.251-7000 Ordering from Government Supply Sources">
  <ns0:data key="d0">252.251-7000 Ordering from Government Supply Sources</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">clause</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">252.251-7000 is the clause dated AUG 2012 outlining ordering procedures from government supply sources.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841059</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="FAR 52.228-5 Insurance - Work on a Government Installation">
  <ns0:data key="d0">FAR 52.228-5 Insurance - Work on a Government Installation</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">clause</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">FAR 52.228-5 requires contractors to provide and maintain insurance during the entire period of the contract.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841059</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="I-1 Minimum Insurance Requirements">
  <ns0:data key="d0">I-1 Minimum Insurance Requirements</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">section</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">I-1 specifies the kinds and minimum amounts of insurance required, referencing FAR 52.228-5.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841059</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Federal Supply Schedules">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Federal Supply Schedules</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Federal Supply Schedules are schedules under which contractors place orders, following applicable terms and authorizations.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841059</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Personal Property Rehabilitation Price Schedules">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Personal Property Rehabilitation Price Schedules</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Personal Property Rehabilitation Price Schedules are schedules for ordering, requiring inclusion of authorizations and specific statements.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841059</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Enterprise Software Agreements">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Enterprise Software Agreements</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Enterprise Software Agreements are agreements issued under Federal Supply Schedules, with price reductions and governance rules specified.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841059</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="GSA Form 1948-A">
  <ns0:data key="d0">GSA Form 1948-A</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">GSA Form 1948-A is the Retail Services Shopping Plate used when ordering from GSA Self-Service Stores.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841059</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Defense Logistics Management System">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Defense Logistics Management System</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">DLMS is used for electronic transactions in submitting requisitions and acknowledging receipts on a non-reimbursable basis.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841059</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="General Liability Insurance">
  <ns0:data key="d0">General Liability Insurance</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">requirement</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">General Liability Insurance requires the MCMC to maintain bodily injury liability insurance in the minimum limits of $500,000 per occurrence.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841059</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Automobile Liability Insurance">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Automobile Liability Insurance</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">requirement</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Automobile Liability Insurance requires the MCMC to maintain coverage of $20,000 per occurrence for property damage, $200,000 per person and $500,000 per occurrence for bodily injury.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841059</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Worker's Compensation and Employer's Liability">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Worker's Compensation and Employer's Liability</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">requirement</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Worker's Compensation and Employer's Liability requires compliance with Federal and State statutes, with at least $100,000 employer's liability, except in monopolistic state funds.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841059</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Exhibit A">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Exhibit A</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">section</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Exhibit A details the Contract Data Requirements List (CDRLs) for various CLINs, including descriptions, SOW references, and frequencies.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841059</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="DSI Authorization Letters">
  <ns0:data key="d0">DSI Authorization Letters</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">DSI Authorization Letters is CDRL 1008 under X001, due within 21 business days after contract award and NLT five business days after award of each applicable TO, with specific shipboard timelines, referencing SOW 2.B.2.e.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Special Tool Allowance Letter">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Special Tool Allowance Letter</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Special Tool Allowance Letter is CDRL 1009 under X001, due NLT 21 business days after contract award and annually NLT 5 business days after 1 July, referencing SOW 2.b.2.f.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Reconciliation Schedule">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Reconciliation Schedule</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CDRL 1011 is a schedule submitted by the MCMC for weekly validations and reconciliations, provided after contract award and annually.&lt;SEP&gt;Reconciliation Schedule is CDRL 1011 under X001, due NLT 5 business days after 1 July, referencing SOW 2.B.3.b.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-a0a00a7bb666b381893da579a6b228c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Weekly On-Island Equipment Status Report">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Weekly On-Island Equipment Status Report</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Weekly On-Island Equipment Status Report is CDRL 1012 under X001, due NLT COB each Tuesday, referencing SOW 2.B.3.c.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Annual Calibration Inventory Letter">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Annual Calibration Inventory Letter</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Annual Calibration Inventory Letter is CDRL 1013 under X001, due NLT 21 business days after contract award and thereafter NLT 30 business days after award of applicable TO, referencing SOW 2.B.3.d.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Locally Tracked Calibration Detail Report">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Locally Tracked Calibration Detail Report</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CDRL 1014 is a report generated by the MCMC for assets not resident in GCSS-MC, submitted within 5 business days after the start of each fiscal year quarter.&lt;SEP&gt;Locally Tracked Calibration Detail Report is CDRL 1014 under X001, due NLT 5 business days after start of each FY quarter per applicable TO, referencing SOW 2.B.3.d(i).</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-a0a00a7bb666b381893da579a6b228c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Baseline MMC MS Project w/COSIS">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Baseline MMC MS Project w/COSIS</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Baseline MMC MS Project w/COSIS is CDRL 1022 under X001, due as directed in the PCL, referencing SOW 2.C.1.b.(ii).a.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MS Project Change Control">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MS Project Change Control</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MS Project Change Control is CDRL 1023 under X001, referencing SOW 2.C.1.b(ii).</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Production Status Charts">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Production Status Charts</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Production Status Charts is CDRL 1024 under X001, due weekly, referencing SOW 2.C.1.a.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Annual LST COMM/ELEC PMCS Plan">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Annual LST COMM/ELEC PMCS Plan</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">The Annual LST COMM/ELEC PMCS Plan is submitted by MCMC using the PPC tool for all PO COMM/ELEC equipment located in Norway within 30 calendar days of contract award and annually no later than 01 October.&lt;SEP&gt;Annual LST COMM/ELEC PMCS Plan is CDRL 1025 under X001, due within 30 days of contract award and annually by 1 October, referencing SOW 2.C.1.b.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-bee5e6b5db1fe2dc611fc5fc2b227a51&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Respond to NCRs/NCTs">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Respond to NCRs/NCTs</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Respond to NCRs/NCTs is CDRL 1027 under X001, due within 1 business day, referencing SOW 2.C.1.d.(i).(d).</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Risk and Performance Policy">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Risk and Performance Policy</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Risk and Performance Policy is to be developed and submitted by MCMC within specified timelines for alignment with CmdO P5000.11 and ISO 9001 certification.&lt;SEP&gt;Risk and Performance Policy is CDRL 1028 under X001, draft within 30 days of award and final within 60 days of contract award, referencing SOW 2.D.1.b.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-432adfa735f19522f81538c1e139e7a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Quality &amp; Risk Control Plan">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Quality &amp; Risk Control Plan</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Quality &amp; Risk Control Plan is CDRL 1029 under X001, draft within 30 days of award, final within 60 days, and upon revision, referencing SOW 2.D.1.b.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Program Personnel Support Plan">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Program Personnel Support Plan</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Program Personnel Support Plan is defined by the acronym PPSP.&lt;SEP&gt;Program Personnel Support Plan is CDRL 1030 under X001, due semi-annually, referencing SOW 1.H.2.b.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-46778545759b6a3b0240557a9acb9577&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Monthly Staffing Report">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Monthly Staffing Report</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Monthly Staffing Report is CDRL 1031 under X001, due monthly, referencing SOW 1.H.2.c.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Monthly Excess/Deficiency Report">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Monthly Excess/Deficiency Report</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Monthly Excess/Deficiency Report (CDRL 4001) identifies excesses and deficiencies of Military Equipment for specific accounts and is submitted monthly.&lt;SEP&gt;Monthly Excess/Deficiency Report is CDRL 4001 under X002 and X003, due monthly, referencing SOW 4.A.1.a.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8efbcbadad92a347ffdc7b5c1e34b2f7</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MCPP-N/MCPP-PHIL Weekly Class of Supply Report">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MCPP-N/MCPP-PHIL Weekly Class of Supply Report</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MCPP-N/MCPP-PHIL Weekly Class of Supply Report is CDRL 4002 under X002 and X003, due weekly, referencing SOW 4.A.1.a.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Draft TOECR (NAVMC 11355)">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Draft TOECR (NAVMC 11355)</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Draft TOECR (NAVMC 11355) is CDRL 5003 under X002 and X003, due as required, referencing SOW 4.A.1.b.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="SL-3 Deficiency Report">
  <ns0:data key="d0">SL-3 Deficiency Report</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">SL-3 Deficiency Report is provided by the MCMC NLT 14 calendar days prior to the end of the production cycle and includes data elements for SL-3 shortfalls.&lt;SEP&gt;SL-3 Deficiency Report is CDRL 5004 under X002 and X003, due NLT 14 calendar days prior to the end of the production cycle (Px-14), referencing SOW 4.D.6.c.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-22de15a10ae9bfba6096cca855d5f78a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="SECREP Excess and Deficiency Report">
  <ns0:data key="d0">SECREP Excess and Deficiency Report</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">SECREP Excess and Deficiency Report is CDRL 5006 under X002 and X003, due monthly, referencing SOW 4.A.3.a.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="RIP Special Allowance Request">
  <ns0:data key="d0">RIP Special Allowance Request</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">RIP Special Allowance Request is CDRL 5007 under X002 and X003, due monthly, referencing SOW 4.A.3.a.(i).</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Garrison Special Tool Allowance List">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Garrison Special Tool Allowance List</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Garrison Special Tool Allowance List (CDRL 5008) identifies special tool allowances for garrison requirements and is submitted annually.&lt;SEP&gt;Garrison Special Tool Allowance List is CDRL 5008 under X002 and X003, due NLT the fifth business day of July, referencing SOW 4.A.4.&lt;SEP&gt;Garrison Special Tool Allowance List is submitted not later than the fifth business day of July under section 4.A.4 for X002 and X003.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-aa9424078fa723e2caaae8aa59fb4397&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8efbcbadad92a347ffdc7b5c1e34b2f7</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="NTV Priority Procurement List">
  <ns0:data key="d0">NTV Priority Procurement List</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">NTV Priority Procurement List is CDRL 5009 under X002 and X003, due NLT the fifth business day of July, referencing SOW 4.A.5.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="UURI / AAL Authorization Letter">
  <ns0:data key="d0">UURI / AAL Authorization Letter</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">UURI / AAL Authorization Letter is CDRL 5010 under X002 and X003, due annually, referencing SOW 4.A.6.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Supply / Maintenance Annual Spend Plan">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Supply / Maintenance Annual Spend Plan</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Supply / Maintenance Annual Spend Plan is CDRL 5011 under X002 and X003, due annually, referencing SOW 4.A.7.&lt;SEP&gt;Supply / Maintenance Annual Spend Plan is submitted annually under section 4.A.7 for X002 and X003.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-aa9424078fa723e2caaae8aa59fb4397&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Supply / Maintenance Quarterly Spend Plan Update">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Supply / Maintenance Quarterly Spend Plan Update</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Supply / Maintenance Quarterly Spend Plan Update is CDRL 5012 under X002 and X003, due quarterly, referencing SOW 4.A.7.a.&lt;SEP&gt;Supply / Maintenance Quarterly Spend Plan Update is submitted quarterly under section 4.A.7.a for X002 and X003.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-aa9424078fa723e2caaae8aa59fb4397&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="GFE Procurement Request">
  <ns0:data key="d0">GFE Procurement Request</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">GFE Procurement Request is CDRL 5016 under X002 and X003, due as required, referencing SOW 4.B.5.a.(i).</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Physical Inventory Control Plan">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Physical Inventory Control Plan</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Physical Inventory Control Plan is defined by the acronym PICP.&lt;SEP&gt;Physical Inventory Control Plan (PICP) is CDRL 5018 under X002 and X003, due annually, referencing SOW 4.C.1.&lt;SEP&gt;Physical Inventory Control Plan outlines inventory management procedures and is required annually for X002 and X003 under section 4.C.1 and also under section 6.C.4.a.iv for X002.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-46778545759b6a3b0240557a9acb9577&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aa9424078fa723e2caaae8aa59fb4397&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="IMO Load Request">
  <ns0:data key="d0">IMO Load Request</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">IMO Load Request is CDRL 5019 under X002 and X003, due as required, referencing SOW 4.C.2.a.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="RO Nomination Package">
  <ns0:data key="d0">RO Nomination Package</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">RO Nomination Package is CDRL 5020 under X002 and X003, due as required, referencing SOW 4.C.2.b.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="PICP Consumer Level Account Inventory Results Report">
  <ns0:data key="d0">PICP Consumer Level Account Inventory Results Report</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">PICP Consumer Level Account Inventory Results Report is CDRL 5021 under X002 and X003, due as required, referencing SOW 4.C.2.c.(i).</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="PICP Intermediate Level Account Inventory Results Report">
  <ns0:data key="d0">PICP Intermediate Level Account Inventory Results Report</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">PICP Intermediate Level Account Inventory Results Report (CDRL 5022) documents inventory results for intermediate level accounts, including data elements and adjustments.&lt;SEP&gt;PICP Intermediate Level Account Inventory Results Report is CDRL 5022 under X002 and X003, due as required, referencing SOW 4.C.3.a.(ii).</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CLIN X001">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CLIN X001</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">section</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CLIN X001 covers costs for administrative/clerical equipment, supplies, consumables, and personal protective equipment provided by MCMC.&lt;SEP&gt;CLIN X001 encompasses various CDRLs related to maintenance management, inspections, calibration, production, quality, and personnel support.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c12bdd730383e0d5968b0354d37c6d8a</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CLIN X002">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CLIN X002</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">section</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CLIN X002 includes CDRLs for supply reports, deficiency reports, stock levels, and inventory controls under X002 and X003.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CLIN X003">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CLIN X003</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">section</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CLIN X003 shares CDRLs with X002 for supply and maintenance activities.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Crisis Situations">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Crisis Situations</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Crisis situations include events like pandemics, where essential contractor services must continue as directed.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Plans Branch">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Plans Branch</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Plans Branch is responsible for the development and management of all plans related to the Marine Corps Prepositioning Programs, oversees level VI data, and develops guidelines for marking prepositioned assets.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Marine Corps Prepositioning Programs">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Marine Corps Prepositioning Programs</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Marine Corps Prepositioning Programs encompass the development and management of plans for prepositioning assets, including afloat and ashore sites.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="HQMC DC I&amp;L">
  <ns0:data key="d0">HQMC DC I&amp;L</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">HQMC DC I&amp;L leads and manages the Tailoring effort for the MPF program.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="DC PP&amp;O">
  <ns0:data key="d0">DC PP&amp;O</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">DC PP&amp;O approves the Tailoring effort for the Prepositioning Objective in the MPF program.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841060</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Prepositioning Objective">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Prepositioning Objective</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">The Prepositioning Objective is the approved inventory list for MPF and ashore programs, published in NAVMC 2907.&lt;SEP&gt;Prepositioning Objective is a newly approved plan used as the basis for developing Squadron Level Plans in the MPF program.&lt;SEP&gt;Prepositioning Objective (PO) in NAVMC 2907 establishes allowances for MPF, Future Ashore, MCPP-N, and MCPP-PHIL accounts.&lt;SEP&gt;Prepositioning Objective encompasses equipment sets for MPS, MCPP-N, MCPP-PHIL, and future sites, including additions from modernization and stock programs.&lt;SEP&gt;Prepositioning Objective is defined by the acronym PO.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-8efbcbadad92a347ffdc7b5c1e34b2f7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-46778545759b6a3b0240557a9acb9577&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93752a7bd8aca85ef0ce5fea3701dc32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c10c3b1cc4c0a5d44aa2c137a52eaf0b</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MPF MMC">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MPF MMC</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MPF MMC refers to the Maritime Prepositioning Force maintenance cycle involving production and loading of ships.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="TAMCN">
  <ns0:data key="d0">TAMCN</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">TAMCN is the Table of Authorized Materiel Control Number used to track planned quantities of equipment in squadron plans.&lt;SEP&gt;TAMCN is the Table of Authorized Materiel Control Number for identifying equipment in accountability records.&lt;SEP&gt;TAMCN is a data element used in excess/deficiency reports to identify materiel control numbers.&lt;SEP&gt;TAMCN refers to the Table of Authorized Materiel Control Number used to identify specific military equipment items such as parent TAMCN for batteries and nomenclatures like B0060, B0079, and D1001.&lt;SEP&gt;TAMCN is the Table of Assigned Marine Corps Numbers, used in discrepancy reports for identifying items.&lt;SEP&gt;TAMCN is the Table of Authorized Materiel Control Number applied to parent military equipment in SL-3 deficiency reporting.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-13a4841aefad66042f059edb023e607b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-abd2ceb311ce78c8a8c1fe38d11ee4f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8efbcbadad92a347ffdc7b5c1e34b2f7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22de15a10ae9bfba6096cca855d5f78a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Squadron Level Plans">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Squadron Level Plans</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Squadron Level Plans include overviews, rollups of TAMCN quantities, ship distributions, and other listings developed OOA P-180 and posted to MCPIC.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Ship Spread Plan">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Ship Spread Plan</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Ship Spread Plan provides a listing of how squadron planned quantities are distributed to individual ships within the MCPIC Prepositioning Planning System.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Major Subordinate Element Plan">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Major Subordinate Element Plan</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Major Subordinate Element Plan lists how squadron planned quantities are distributed across Major Subordinate Elements.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Capability Set Letter">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Capability Set Letter</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Capability Set Letter lists capabilities and their contents for packaging, packing, marking, and stowing aboard MPS vessels.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Armory Weapons Squadron Plan">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Armory Weapons Squadron Plan</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Armory Weapons Squadron Plan lists weapons or optics quantities stored in armories aboard vessels, broken out by ship.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CMS Container Spread">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CMS Container Spread</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CMS Container Spread lists CCI equipment quantities stored in CMS designated containers or armories, broken out by ship.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Sustainment Blocks">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Sustainment Blocks</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Sustainment Blocks are prepared and managed by MCMC during MMC production, including inventory, inspections, and stock rotation for shipboard sustainment.&lt;SEP&gt;Sustainment Blocks are listings of items and quantities divided by individual blocks such as Petroleum, Oils and Lubricants Block, Battery Block, and Class IV Fortification Block, packaged as single capabilities.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-bd3a05bb896b89de7fd366c654ad4a6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Class I Rations Block">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Class I Rations Block</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Class I Rations Block is a specific sustainment plan for rations due to its unique format.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Container Estimate Worksheet">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Container Estimate Worksheet</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Container Estimate Worksheet tracks, manages, and monitors the number of containers required for specified capabilities, alerting planners to TEU capacity issues.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Load Type Plan">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Load Type Plan</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Load Type Plan lists planned load methods for TAMCN/EC items onto specified ships, including links to Equipment Life Cycle Management.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Association Plan">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Association Plan</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Association Plan provides detailed load and configuration requirements for each TAMCN/EC loaded onto specified ships.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Logistical Set Report">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Logistical Set Report</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Logistical Set Report lists planned Children items stowed away from Parent items.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Naval Support Element Container Plan">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Naval Support Element Container Plan</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Naval Support Element Container Plan provides planned container quantities and packed equipment sets per container for NSE.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="IPACK">
  <ns0:data key="d0">IPACK</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">IPACK is a data system used for entering weighed data on PEIs and containers, and populating elements for ICODES.&lt;SEP&gt;IPACK is a system used by MCMC to produce orders, manage data, and ensure accuracy for UDLs, weights, and other elements in prepositioning.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89b1a9fa6c0722adcd478e665df09141</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CmdBul 3162 Data Standards">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CmdBul 3162 Data Standards</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CmdBul 3162 Data Standards outline requirements for accuracy in item weights, metadata, and other data elements.&lt;SEP&gt;CmdBul 3162 Data Standards outline requirements for data accuracy, including metadata, weights, and IPACK population.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89b1a9fa6c0722adcd478e665df09141</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="USN">
  <ns0:data key="d0">USN</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">USN is the United States Navy, providing support elements like NSE and NCE in prepositioning plans.&lt;SEP&gt;USN is United States Navy, involved in exercise support and prepositioning assets.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="T-AKE">
  <ns0:data key="d0">T-AKE</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">T-AKE is the Dry Cargo/Ammunition Ship used for loading equipment and supplies in the MPF program.&lt;SEP&gt;T-AKE refers to a class of ships using standard perpetual sub-inventories for sustainment blocks.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Capability Set">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Capability Set</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Capability Set consists of prepositioned assets packaged, packed, and marked to achieve specified capabilities, maintained with integrity across containers.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Principle End Items">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Principle End Items</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Principle End Items are TAMCN-controlled items configured with associated equipment including SSRI, CM, and UURI to enhance operational capability.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Meals Ready to Eat">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Meals Ready to Eat</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Meals Ready to Eat are prepositioned in designated quantities, palletized, and loaded into refer containers or break bulk for T-AKE vessels.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Petroleum Oils and Lubricants Block">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Petroleum Oils and Lubricants Block</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Petroleum Oils and Lubricants Block is a sustainment block prepositioned in designated quantities and units of issue.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Class IV Fortification Block">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Class IV Fortification Block</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Class IV Fortification Block includes pressure-treated lumber and fortification materials prepositioned in designated quantities.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Class IX Batteries">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Class IX Batteries</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Class IX Batteries are prepositioned in designated types, quantities, and units of issue, loaded according to hazardous material regulations.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Offload Preparation Party Blocks">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Offload Preparation Party Blocks</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Offload Preparation Party Blocks consist of materials and supplies for preparing equipment for offload, including Marine and Navy versions.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Arrival and Assembly Support Package">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Arrival and Assembly Support Package</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Arrival and Assembly Support Package consists of materials and supplies to prepare containerized assets for issue, not part of MAGTF Table of Equipment.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Unit Deployment Listing">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Unit Deployment Listing</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Unit Deployment Listing is produced accurately in IPACK for all equipment and supplies embarked on MPS, submitted for review NLT E+5.&lt;SEP&gt;Unit Deployment Listing is defined by the acronym UDL.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-46778545759b6a3b0240557a9acb9577&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Dangerous Cargo Manifest">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Dangerous Cargo Manifest</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">The Dangerous Cargo Manifest (DCM) is created in ICODES using specific data elements like NSN, SERIAL NUMBER, DESCRIPTION, WEIGHT, QTY PER CARGO, PKG ID, and UN CODE.&lt;SEP&gt;Dangerous Cargo Manifest is created in ICODES using specific data elements from IPACK NLT E-Day.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89b1a9fa6c0722adcd478e665df09141</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="ICODES">
  <ns0:data key="d0">ICODES</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">ICODES is a system that requires population of specific data elements for creating the Dangerous Cargo Manifest and in accordance with MMC Execution Milestones.&lt;SEP&gt;ICODES is a system used for load and staging plan development and creation of Dangerous Cargo Manifests.&lt;SEP&gt;ICODES is Integrated Computerized Deployment System used for validating and updating deck diagrams.&lt;SEP&gt;ICODES is an information system used by MCMC to populate data elements for cargo manifests and load plans during MMC execution milestones.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38be7e49aefd10e870f45cb648f7d79d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89b1a9fa6c0722adcd478e665df09141&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="IMARK">
  <ns0:data key="d0">IMARK</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">IMARK is a system for registering IUID and pRFID tags on items and managing labels on equipment.&lt;SEP&gt;IMARK is an embarkation data AIS used similarly to MDSS-II for logging portable fire extinguishers.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-13a4841aefad66042f059edb023e607b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Tailoring Effort">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Tailoring Effort</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">event</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Tailoring Effort is led and managed by HQMC DC I&amp;L and approved by DC PP&amp;O to establish the Prepositioning Objective for the MPF program.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Production Day">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Production Day</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">event</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Production Day, denoted as P-Day, serves as a key timeline milestone for completing squadron level plans NLT 180 days prior to the first ship of the MMC.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MCPIC Prepositioning Planning System">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MCPIC Prepositioning Planning System</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MCPIC Prepositioning Planning System is an application within MCPIC used to manage and access specific plans such as the Ship Spread Plan.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Major Subordinate Element">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Major Subordinate Element</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Major Subordinate Element refers to organizational units across which squadron planned quantities for TAMCNs are distributed in prepositioning plans.&lt;SEP&gt;Major Subordinate Element is defined by the acronym MSE.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-46778545759b6a3b0240557a9acb9577&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="NSE Weapons Armory Plan">
  <ns0:data key="d0">NSE Weapons Armory Plan</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">NSE Weapons Armory Plan provides a detailed listing of planned weapons and serial numbers for the Naval Support Element.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="NSE Watercraft Workbook">
  <ns0:data key="d0">NSE Watercraft Workbook</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">NSE Watercraft Workbook provides a detailed listing of planned watercraft for the Naval Support Element.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Navy Battery Block">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Navy Battery Block</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Navy Battery Block is a listing of planned batteries for Navy equipment, included in sustainment planning.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Naval Construction Element">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Naval Construction Element</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Naval Construction Element is supported by OPP Blocks, container plans, and CESE workbooks for prepositioning operations.&lt;SEP&gt;Naval Construction Element is defined by the acronym NCE.&lt;SEP&gt;Naval Construction Element is an equipment ownership group for funding contract efforts.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-386066b546b82c7b89bda0ef90b3a5f2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-46778545759b6a3b0240557a9acb9577</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="NCE OPP Block">
  <ns0:data key="d0">NCE OPP Block</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">NCE OPP Block is a detailed listing of equipment and supplies for Naval Construction Element Offload Preparation Party operations.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="NCE Container Plan">
  <ns0:data key="d0">NCE Container Plan</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">NCE Container Plan provides planned container quantities and packed equipment sets per container for the Naval Construction Element.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CESE Workbook">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CESE Workbook</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CESE Workbook is a detailed Navy-provided document for rolling stock, including mobile load plans, serial numbers, cab configurations, and special stow requirements for NSE and NCE.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CMS Container Plan">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CMS Container Plan</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CMS Container Plan provides a detailed list of all COMSEC material stowed aboard ships in consolidated containers or armories.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Armory Plan">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Armory Plan</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Armory Plan provides a detailed listing of USMC ground weapons to be stowed within a specific ship's armory.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="E00712BA_E00712BD Plan">
  <ns0:data key="d0">E00712BA_E00712BD Plan</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">E00712BA_E00712BD Plan provides detailed installation requirements for different versions of MCTAGS on MTVR and LVSR platforms.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MTVR">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MTVR</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MTVR is a vehicle type requiring operational function tests, filter replacements, and PMCS actions during production periods.&lt;SEP&gt;MTVR is the Medium Tactical Vehicle Replacement platform used for MCTAGS installation in prepositioning configurations.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-c10c3b1cc4c0a5d44aa2c137a52eaf0b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="LVSR">
  <ns0:data key="d0">LVSR</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">LVSR is a vehicle requiring air dryer filter services as part of PMCS functions.&lt;SEP&gt;LVSR is the Logistics Vehicle System Replacement platform used for MCTAGS installation in prepositioning configurations.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-c10c3b1cc4c0a5d44aa2c137a52eaf0b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Association Reference Table">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Association Reference Table</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Association Reference Table is a government-provided resource posted in MCPIC for configuring TAMCN-controlled Principle End Items with associated equipment.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841061</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="SSRI">
  <ns0:data key="d0">SSRI</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">SSRI is a Supply System Responsibility Item associated with Principle End Items to enhance operational capability.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Collateral Material">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Collateral Material</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Collateral Material is equipment associated with Principle End Items, including SSRI and UURI, to support operational capabilities.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="UURI">
  <ns0:data key="d0">UURI</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">UURI is a Using Unit Responsibility Item associated with Principle End Items for prepositioned operations.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Class I Rations Plan">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Class I Rations Plan</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Class I Rations Plan directs the prepositioning of Meals Ready to Eat and First Strike Rations in designated quantities.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Class III Packaged POLs">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Class III Packaged POLs</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Class III Packaged POLs are sustainment consumables prepositioned in designated quantities and mandated units of issue per the Sustainment Blocks plan.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Class IV Engineering Construction Material">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Class IV Engineering Construction Material</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Class IV Engineering Construction Material is prepositioned as part of sustainment blocks for engineering and construction needs.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Class IX Consumables">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Class IX Consumables</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Class IX Consumables are prepositioned in sustainment blocks for operational repair and maintenance.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Class IX Battery Plan">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Class IX Battery Plan</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Class IX Battery Plan directs the prepositioning of batteries in designated types, quantities, and units of issue.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="OPP Plan">
  <ns0:data key="d0">OPP Plan</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">OPP Plan directs the configuration and prepositioning of Marine and Navy Offload Preparation Party Blocks.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="PP&amp;P Plan">
  <ns0:data key="d0">PP&amp;P Plan</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">PP&amp;P Plan directs the assembly and packaging of T-AKE Preservation, Packaging, and Packing Blocks.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MAGTF">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MAGTF</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MAGTF receives issuances of consumables, expendables, and secondary reparables from T-AKE ships during MPF exercises and returns unexpended items.&lt;SEP&gt;MAGTF is the Marine Air-Ground Task Force receiving temporary loans of equipment for exercises and contingencies.&lt;SEP&gt;MAGTF is the Marine Air Ground Task Force that receives MPE/S from MCMC during exercises via the Responsible Officer.&lt;SEP&gt;MAGTF is the Marine Air-Ground Task Force whose Table of Equipment excludes support items like OPP and AASP Blocks.&lt;SEP&gt;MAGTF is the Marine Air-Ground Task Force that receives issued MPE/S and documentation from MCMC during exercises.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-abd2ceb311ce78c8a8c1fe38d11ee4f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f918f57232ad428f5920d4c98f0af702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Meta Data">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Meta Data</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Meta Data refers to technical data files that can be updated via written requests from the MCMC if items are not resident or changes are needed.&lt;SEP&gt;Meta Data in MCPIC is updated for equipment changes such as new fielding, modifications, and stock rotations, complying with data standards.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89b1a9fa6c0722adcd478e665df09141</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Scale House">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Scale House</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">location</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">The Scale House is a facility used for weighing MPE and providing weight tickets for input into IPACK data records.&lt;SEP&gt;Scale House is the facility used for weighing Major Piece of Equipment and generating weight tickets for IPACK data entry.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89b1a9fa6c0722adcd478e665df09141</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="NSN">
  <ns0:data key="d0">NSN</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">NSN is a data element in reports for National Stock Numbers of items.&lt;SEP&gt;NSN is the National Stock Number, a required data element populated in IPACK for ICODES load plans and Dangerous Cargo Manifests.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8efbcbadad92a347ffdc7b5c1e34b2f7</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="ITEM ID">
  <ns0:data key="d0">ITEM ID</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">ITEM ID is a data element associated with load and staging plans, populated in IPACK for ICODES.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="PKG ID">
  <ns0:data key="d0">PKG ID</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">PKG ID is a data element for packaging identification, populated in IPACK for ICODES and Dangerous Cargo Manifests.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="SERIAL NUMBER">
  <ns0:data key="d0">SERIAL NUMBER</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">SERIAL NUMBER is a data element required for Dangerous Cargo Manifest creation in ICODES.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MCTP 13-10D/NTTP 3.02.3M">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MCTP 13-10D/NTTP 3.02.3M</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MCTP 13-10D/NTTP 3.02.3M establishes compliance standards for labeling, legibility, and scanability of equipment.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="NAVMC DIR 3000.18">
  <ns0:data key="d0">NAVMC DIR 3000.18</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">NAVMC DIR 3000.18 directs label legibility, scanability, and replacement for equipment.&lt;SEP&gt;NAVMC DIR 3000.18 is a directive governing labeling and adherence to detailed ship plans.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89b1a9fa6c0722adcd478e665df09141</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="First Strike Rations">
  <ns0:data key="d0">First Strike Rations</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">First Strike Rations are prepositioned in designated quantities, palletized with 48 cases per pallet, and loaded into refer containers or break bulk in support of T-AKE vessels.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CDRL 7001">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CDRL 7001</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CDRL 7001 consists of shipboard reports prepared by MCMC using Microsoft Office programs and submitted to the COR.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Monthly SITREP">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Monthly SITREP</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Monthly SITREP summarizes logistics services, stock checks, maintenance, and issues, submitted NLT the first business day of each month.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="PGP Report">
  <ns0:data key="d0">PGP Report</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">PGP Report lists government personnel aboard ships, including names, billets, days on ship, and remarks, submitted monthly.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Weekly Staffing Report">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Weekly Staffing Report</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Weekly Staffing Report details MCMC shipboard personnel by location, status, vacancies, and hires, submitted NLT COB Tuesday.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="SASU Report">
  <ns0:data key="d0">SASU Report</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">SASU Report includes startup results, battery evaluations, and maintenance plans, submitted 15 business days after semi-annual startup.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Pre-Exercise Status Report">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Pre-Exercise Status Report</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Pre-Exercise Status Report covers equipment serviceability, battery conditions, and open requests for offload equipment.&lt;SEP&gt;Pre-Exercise Status Report is submitted by MCMC using SOW Attachment C.7-5 format, covering equipment serviceability, battery checks, and other topics for exercises.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-f918f57232ad428f5920d4c98f0af702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="PEDL">
  <ns0:data key="d0">PEDL</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">PEDL is the Post Exercise Discrepancy Listing submitted by MCMC detailing equipment damages and deficiencies after exercises.&lt;SEP&gt;PEDL lists equipment damages from offload, exercise, backload, and validation, submitted NLT 10 business days after operations.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-f918f57232ad428f5920d4c98f0af702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Post Exercise Cost Estimate">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Post Exercise Cost Estimate</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Post Exercise Cost Estimate totals costs for supplies and services in support of exercises, submitted NLT 10 business days after completion.&lt;SEP&gt;Post Exercise Cost Estimate is a total cost report for supplies and services delivered electronically by MCMC to COR after exercises.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-f918f57232ad428f5920d4c98f0af702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="120 Day Pre-MMC Report">
  <ns0:data key="d0">120 Day Pre-MMC Report</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">120 Day Pre-MMC Report details maintenance issues, inventories, and turn-in lists prior to ship offload.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Section 7.E">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Section 7.E</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">section</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Section 7.E outlines preventive maintenance requirements for stock checks, fuel management, and refrigerated container inspections.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Section 7.F">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Section 7.F</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">section</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Section 7.F describes corrective maintenance procedures, timelines for priority repairs, and modification instructions for MPE/S.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Section 7.G">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Section 7.G</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">section</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Section 7.G specifies MCMC responsibilities during MPS exercises and contingencies, including planning, issuing assets, and validation.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Section 7.H">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Section 7.H</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">section</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Section 7.H details shipboard reporting requirements, including monthly, weekly, and exercise-specific reports.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Section 7.I">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Section 7.I</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">section</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Section 7.I addresses per diem status for MCMC stranded ashore due to transportation issues.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Section 7.J">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Section 7.J</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">section</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Section 7.J establishes MCMC subordination to ship's master, housekeeping duties, and conduct policies.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Section 7.K">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Section 7.K</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">section</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Section 7.K lists government-furnished services for contractor employees aboard MPS, including baggage authorization.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="After Action Report">
  <ns0:data key="d0">After Action Report</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">After Action Report identifies risks and issues in exercise planning and execution using topic, discussion, and recommendation format.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CDRL 7002">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CDRL 7002</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CDRL 7002 is the Resource and Support Plan proposed by MCMC for approval within 10 business days after receiving the government RFP.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CAL">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CAL</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CAL is the Consolidated Asset Listing used for temporary loans and chain of custody during exercises.&lt;SEP&gt;CAL is the Consolidated Asset Listing used to document issuance of MPE/S to MAGTF, updated and coordinated through COR or TAAT OIC.&lt;SEP&gt;CAL is the Government-issued Consolidated Asset Listing used by MCMC to document issuance of MPE/S to MAGTF during exercises.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-f918f57232ad428f5920d4c98f0af702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841062</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="KMI">
  <ns0:data key="d0">KMI</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">KMI is the Key Management Infrastructure for managing COMSEC and CCI assets, ensuring distribution, control, security, and accountability.&lt;SEP&gt;KMI manages accounts for returning mobile COMSEC materiel and handles shipping and receiving of Controlled Cryptographic Items.&lt;SEP&gt;KMI is the Key Management Infrastructure assets that MCMC issues and recovers during exercises in accordance with Section C.8.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-f918f57232ad428f5920d4c98f0af702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4ef5ed78269155f4369ff9bd9b69ddc8</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="SF153">
  <ns0:data key="d0">SF153</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">SF153 is the form used for transferring COMSEC material, completed and delivered by MCMC for KMI assets.&lt;SEP&gt;SF153 is a form completed by MCMC for delivery to the BICmd KMI manager via the exercise COTR.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-f918f57232ad428f5920d4c98f0af702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="COTR">
  <ns0:data key="d0">COTR</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">person</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">COTR is a government role interacting with designated MCMC quality personnel.&lt;SEP&gt;COTR is the Shipboard Contracting Officer’s Technical Representative who interfaces between MCMC, COR, and Contracting Officer during forward deployments.&lt;SEP&gt;COTR is the Contracting Officer's Technical Representative who receives coordination on CAL changes and other exercise matters.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-f918f57232ad428f5920d4c98f0af702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-432adfa735f19522f81538c1e139e7a3</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="TAAT OIC">
  <ns0:data key="d0">TAAT OIC</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">other</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">TAAT OIC receives draft PEDL upon completion of backload and deck validation.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="GSSS-MC">
  <ns0:data key="d0">GSSS-MC</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">GSSS-MC is the system containing M777 Gun Book data placed in equipment temporary folders as required.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="COMPSRON">
  <ns0:data key="d0">COMPSRON</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">COMPSRON receives a copy of the PGP report from the Squadron Supervisor.&lt;SEP&gt;COMPSRON is the Commander, Maritime Prepositioning Ships Squadron whose staff serves as a coordinating link in prepositioning operations.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-f918f57232ad428f5920d4c98f0af702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="DML">
  <ns0:data key="d0">DML</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">DML is the Deferred Maintenance Listing where non-mission capable equipment is added if maintenance cannot be completed within two business days.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MCMC">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MCMC</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">The Marine Corps Maintenance Contractor (MCMC) serves as a key contractor organization supporting U.S. Navy and Marine Corps operations, particularly under contracts such as the Marine Corps Prepositioning Program (MCPP), MCPP II, MCPP-N, and MCPP-PHIL, as well as Maritime Prepositioning Ships (MPS) and related initiatives. Responsible for a wide array of logistics, maintenance, and sustainment services, MCMC ensures the readiness of prepositioning assets, government-furnished equipment, and military property through comprehensive lifecycle management. This includes irregular hours work, personnel provisioning, surge teams, and dedicated managerial, supervisory, and skilled labor support, often establishing separate Navy elements and nominating armory custodians or providing access nominations to facilitate operations.

In logistics and supply chain management, MCMC handles inventory control, receipt validations, reconciliations, issue management, procurement activities, requisitioning, shelf life management, container management, distribution, transportation, and warehousing for Navy assets, prepositioning programs, and T-AKE ships. It conducts causative research, adjusts property records, manages chain of custody, performs spot checks, storage, handling, and packaging of materials, including ISO containers and COMSEC/cryptographic items. MCMC also oversees container packing, weapons management, and maritime prepositioning inventories, submitting detailed reports on discrepancies, status, and compliance while utilizing various business systems, applications, and information systems for data population, labeling, tagging, and production planning.

Maintenance responsibilities form a core pillar of MCMC's role, encompassing preventive maintenance checks and services (PMCS), corrective maintenance (CM), repairs, inspections, cleaning, high-pressure washing, corrosion control, and coating systems maintenance on a diverse range of assets. This includes Marine Corps and Navy equipment such as Construction Equipment Support Equipment (CESE), Material Handling Equipment (MHE), watercraft, LARCs, Amphibious Beach Lighter Transporters (ABLTS), and prepositioning equipment/supplies (MPE/S). MCMC performs self-help efforts, operational support, testing, and housekeeping aboard MPS, ensures equipment accountability and balance, and conducts Condition of Serviceability Inspection System (COSIS) surveillance in accordance with approved plans. It also manages maintenance production, establishes maintenance centers, produces schedules, and provides licensed crane operators, critical lift plans, battery maintenance, and fire extinger management, all while adhering to DoD, Navy, and Marine Corps orders, standards, and procedures.

Financial oversight and reporting are integral to MCMC's operations, involving complete lifecycle financial management of supply-related actions, fiscal reconciliations, budgeting for travel and other direct costs, invoicing, and delivering comprehensive reports on inventories, logistics, maintenance, metrics, and program status. MCMC develops and updates production plans, participates in meetings, briefings, and reviews, and ensures compliance with quality control plans, risk management policies, internal control procedures, and audit programs. It establishes weight handling programs, handles mobile loads, and reports on improvements, while mitigating organizational conflicts of interest (OCI) through training, agreements for proprietary data, and conflict resolution measures.

Beyond core logistics and maintenance, MCMC provides specialized support services, including environmental management, waste handling, pollution prevention, natural resource protection, safety compliance, and training—such as appointing an Environmental Manager, conducting drills, inspecting safety equipment, and implementing destructive weather plans. In information technology and communications, it offers onsite support, help desk operations, network administration, installation, maintenance, and inventory management for voice, video, and data systems at locations like Blount Island, with flex hours and emergency response capabilities. MCMC also manages Key Management Infrastructure (KMI) operations, exercise support, medical material management, and various prepositioning-related tasks like stock checks and surveillance, ensuring adherence to regulations during base ordering periods and task orders. To fulfill these duties, MCMC maintains specified insurance coverages, provides certifications to the Contracting Officer, and performs quality assurance through inspections, monitoring, and internal assessments, all while avoiding conflicts and promoting efficiency across programs.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-955c2fafc0e5a2a07e97130b42a872b5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-abd2ceb311ce78c8a8c1fe38d11ee4f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c12bdd730383e0d5968b0354d37c6d8a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b825754de20bbf2c5befd6a79730280e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b6f17f0fbf6c678da23e588ab57f6900&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-070bdd3969938da07f8e836e32dfa592&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-68739860c42b764e52f9649ea16ed702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf666a8ded534eb47b7eede4412a01f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-65833c099ebcc7aa1fccc5a1d930a7aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89b1a9fa6c0722adcd478e665df09141&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f6510cadeb544a78c12488882601935c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b8875a30a8284afacba5893b8971b2b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c10c3b1cc4c0a5d44aa2c137a52eaf0b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fce6cd46a0bc9b7bd7d409339addb37d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8a136ea2c9ab7ea9bb718fd0abd010d4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22de15a10ae9bfba6096cca855d5f78a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4ef5ed78269155f4369ff9bd9b69ddc8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d6887833d0f1a6398bb6c8fd6f72d5c8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2fcdd71246fc4a058f5f995cbe6b3531&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0395bdbad90a448875b2a66efe14f948&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8aa129e6fff6d48e4dab5ab9c9d8c169&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a0a00a7bb666b381893da579a6b228c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-13a4841aefad66042f059edb023e607b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2829fe507a5073eafb2e5fb0cc5e85c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-789ddbe0005097425aa3559f9388ad80&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38be7e49aefd10e870f45cb648f7d79d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c2bae9a24e71825050f79fc141b2e181&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e151c7682b4ed7c6cd2fcdc2e29ec22&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-386066b546b82c7b89bda0ef90b3a5f2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-432adfa735f19522f81538c1e139e7a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4c2c73655d1d9f038ea8945f49a05a1f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d89c19e067243fa311d34bfc3fa99c70&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e73c8ab3a0b248cdeedb8496a5c6f8a9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f918f57232ad428f5920d4c98f0af702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8efbcbadad92a347ffdc7b5c1e34b2f7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93752a7bd8aca85ef0ce5fea3701dc32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f736781b685dec5629d8433e71c666e4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2edf7351f7d27be2ca8809d7ac16a11d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd3a05bb896b89de7fd366c654ad4a6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-85b50b451f72c11f155dc39b516d8dd3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bee5e6b5db1fe2dc611fc5fc2b227a51&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7659b0abfc62a3f8f0edbf4a1fee058e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="RFP">
  <ns0:data key="d0">RFP</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">RFP is the Request for Proposal that identifies requirements for support operations and equipment handling.&lt;SEP&gt;RFP is the Request for Proposal document outlining contract requirements for MCMC services.&lt;SEP&gt;RFP is the Request for Proposal provided by the Contracting Officer for each MPS exercise or contingency, containing situation, mission, and timelines.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-f918f57232ad428f5920d4c98f0af702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38be7e49aefd10e870f45cb648f7d79d</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Marine Corps Stock List">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Marine Corps Stock List</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Marine Corps Stock List (S-L-1/2) contains applicable Urgent MI for tactical ground equipment.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Joint Travel Regulations">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Joint Travel Regulations</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Joint Travel Regulations provide the per diem rates for MCMC stranded ashore due to transportation non-availability.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Ship's Master">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Ship's Master</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">person</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Ship's Master is the authority aboard the ship who directs MCMC personnel in navigation, operation, safety, and has removal authority for personnel.&lt;SEP&gt;Ship's Master directs MCMC personnel in navigation, operation, safety, and cargo handling, and verifies per diem claims.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-f918f57232ad428f5920d4c98f0af702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="PICP Consumer Level Account Inventory Results">
  <ns0:data key="d0">PICP Consumer Level Account Inventory Results</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">PICP Consumer Level Account Inventory Results (CDRL 5021) is a report on inventory results broken out by AAC, including causative research and recommended adjustments.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MARCORLOGCOMO 4440.1 PICP">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MARCORLOGCOMO 4440.1 PICP</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MARCORLOGCOMO 4440.1 PICP is an order on prepositioning integrated catalog and inventory procedures.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="NIIN">
  <ns0:data key="d0">NIIN</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">NIIN is the National Item Identification Number used in inventory data elements for tracking materiel.&lt;SEP&gt;NIIN is the National Item Identification Number, included in GCSS-MC vs. MCPIC discrepancy reports.&lt;SEP&gt;NIIN is the National Item Identification Number used to identify components and items in SL-3 reports and requisitions.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-22de15a10ae9bfba6096cca855d5f78a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-abd2ceb311ce78c8a8c1fe38d11ee4f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="SAC">
  <ns0:data key="d0">SAC</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">SAC is the Supply Activity Code or Stock Accounting Category used in inventory reporting.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="U/P">
  <ns0:data key="d0">U/P</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">U/P refers to Unit of Issue or Unit Price in inventory data elements.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="T/P">
  <ns0:data key="d0">T/P</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">T/P refers to Total Quantity or Total Price in inventory comparisons.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="DODAAC">
  <ns0:data key="d0">DODAAC</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">DODAAC is the Department of Defense Activity Address Code used for accounting sub-inventories and transfers.&lt;SEP&gt;DODAAC is the Department of Defense Activity Address Code, reported in container inventory discrepancies.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-abd2ceb311ce78c8a8c1fe38d11ee4f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="RO">
  <ns0:data key="d0">RO</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">RO is the Responsible Officer who signs CMRs and validates accountability.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="FIAR">
  <ns0:data key="d0">FIAR</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">FIAR is Financial Improvement Audit Readiness requirements met through signed CMRs and accountability processes.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CRANE">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CRANE</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CRANE is a system for reporting serialized small arms inventories.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Monthly Afloat Armory Report">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Monthly Afloat Armory Report</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Monthly Afloat Armory Report (CDRL 5025) documents physical inventories of serialized small arms, endorsed by the RO.&lt;SEP&gt;Monthly Afloat Armory Report is submitted monthly under section 4.C.4.b for X002 and X003.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-aa9424078fa723e2caaae8aa59fb4397&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="EATO">
  <ns0:data key="d0">EATO</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">EATO transactions are used for equipment transfers to MAGTF during exercises.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MCSF-BI">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MCSF-BI</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">location</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MCSF-BI is the Marine Corps Support Facility-Blount Island where intermediate level supply accounts and DFSP are located.&lt;SEP&gt;MCSF-BI is the Marine Corps Support Facility Blount Island, serving as a key site for operations and maintenance activities.&lt;SEP&gt;MCSF-BI is a location for retail level inventory accounts.&lt;SEP&gt;MCSF-BI is involved in facility coordination and operations support for MCMC activities.&lt;SEP&gt;MCSF-BI is the Marine Corps Support Facility Blount Island, for which CmdO 5560.1 outlines badge and vehicle registration requirements.&lt;SEP&gt;MCSF-BI maintains the Hazardous Material Management Plan referenced for shelf life extensions and utilization of insufficient shelf life materiel.&lt;SEP&gt;MCSF-BI is a location where maintenance operations occur, with specific notice requirements for QA checks and embarkation procedures.&lt;SEP&gt;MCSF-BI is the Marine Corps Support Facility at Blount Island where watercraft return for POL changes and maintenance.&lt;SEP&gt;MCSF-BI is the Marine Corps Support Facility at Blount Island where crane operations and weight restrictions apply.&lt;SEP&gt;MCSF-BI is the organization overseeing integrated plans for solid waste management, green procurement, pollution prevention, natural resources, and contingency responses at the facility.&lt;SEP&gt;MCSF-BI is the installation where the MCMC operations occur, designated as a Large Quantity Generator for hazardous waste, and subject to specific environmental plans and permits.&lt;SEP&gt;Marine Corps Support Facility Blount Island coordinates facility maintenance, safety, and environmental management in support of BICmd logistics mission.&lt;SEP&gt;MCSF-BI is a tenant organization at Blount Island supported by MCMC for voice, video, and data services under the Marine Corps Prepositioning mission.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-fce6cd46a0bc9b7bd7d409339addb37d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9fdacd5fbf292ea850730c0c323f0873&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c12bdd730383e0d5968b0354d37c6d8a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93752a7bd8aca85ef0ce5fea3701dc32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2edf7351f7d27be2ca8809d7ac16a11d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf666a8ded534eb47b7eede4412a01f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4ef5ed78269155f4369ff9bd9b69ddc8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d6887833d0f1a6398bb6c8fd6f72d5c8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-65833c099ebcc7aa1fccc5a1d930a7aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd3a05bb896b89de7fd366c654ad4a6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0395bdbad90a448875b2a66efe14f948&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7659b0abfc62a3f8f0edbf4a1fee058e</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="STRATIS">
  <ns0:data key="d0">STRATIS</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">STRATIS is the Storage Retrieval Automated Tracking Integrated System used as the warehouse management system complementing GCSS-MC.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="COSIS Surveillance Plan">
  <ns0:data key="d0">COSIS Surveillance Plan</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">COSIS Surveillance Plan is approved by the Government and guides the MCMC's conduct and reporting of COSIS activities.&lt;SEP&gt;COSIS Surveillance Plan (CDRL 5027) outlines processes for in-storage inspections and annual submissions for approval.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-65833c099ebcc7aa1fccc5a1d930a7aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Monthly COSIS Surveillance Plan Update and Status Report">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Monthly COSIS Surveillance Plan Update and Status Report</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Monthly COSIS Surveillance Plan Update and Status Report is submitted by the MCMC no later than the last business day of each month and includes listings of materiel planned and completed for COSIS actions.&lt;SEP&gt;Monthly COSIS Surveillance Plan Update and Status Report (CDRL 5028) provides status on COSIS actions and planned inspections.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-65833c099ebcc7aa1fccc5a1d930a7aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MDMC Albany">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MDMC Albany</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MDMC Albany is the Marine Depot Maintenance Command in Albany, GA, responsible for NDT services on components.&lt;SEP&gt;MDMC Albany is the Marine Depot Maintenance Command providing repair services under the Repair and Return program.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-13a4841aefad66042f059edb023e607b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="DIC">
  <ns0:data key="d0">DIC</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">DIC is the Document Identifier Code used for recommended adjustment transactions in inventory results.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="SUC">
  <ns0:data key="d0">SUC</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">SUC refers to Subordinate Unit Custody accounts requiring quarterly CMR inventories.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="M92502">
  <ns0:data key="d0">M92502</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">M92502 is the Non-Prepositioning/BICmd organic account used for tracking equipment allowances and submitting reports.&lt;SEP&gt;M92502 is the account code for organic ME requiring quarterly CMR reconciliations even when afloat.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8efbcbadad92a347ffdc7b5c1e34b2f7</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CDRL 5024">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CDRL 5024</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CDRL 5024 is the submission of signed CMRs, SECREPs, CLIX, and Sustainment Block listings after each ship's production cycle at E+5.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="SOW Attachment C.4-4">
  <ns0:data key="d0">SOW Attachment C.4-4</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">SOW Attachment C.4-4 is the Government-provided format for the Monthly Afloat Armory Report.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="NEIMS">
  <ns0:data key="d0">NEIMS</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">NEIMS is an automated information system used for reconciling supply data and UICs in monthly reports.&lt;SEP&gt;NEIMS is a system used for monthly file transfers of MCPP-N data to MCPIC.&lt;SEP&gt;NEIMS is a system providing data for initial CALs in the MCPP-N prepositioning program.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-bee5e6b5db1fe2dc611fc5fc2b227a51&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd3a05bb896b89de7fd366c654ad4a6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MCO 4450.15">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MCO 4450.15</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MCO 4450.15 governs the maintenance of the COSIS database and conduct of operational/serviceability checks on SECREPs.&lt;SEP&gt;MCO 4450.15 outlines requirements for care of supplies in storage and operational checks.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-65833c099ebcc7aa1fccc5a1d930a7aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="TM 4700-15/1">
  <ns0:data key="d0">TM 4700-15/1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">TM 4700-15/1 is a technical manual providing guidelines for LTIs, condition codes, and local record folders.&lt;SEP&gt;TM 4700-15/1 is a technical manual providing guidance on calibration control, equipment records, and load lifting certification.&lt;SEP&gt;TM 4700-15/1 outlines procedures for conducting SL-3 inventory on ME and CESE assets during the maintenance induction phase.&lt;SEP&gt;TM 4700-15/1 provides standards for Limited Technical Inspections, including condition codes and repair cost estimates.&lt;SEP&gt;TM 4700-15/1 specifies procedures for operational/serviceability checks on SECREPs and data accuracy in the COSIS database.&lt;SEP&gt;TM 4700-15/1 is a technical manual on operational and serviceability checks for SECREPs.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-13a4841aefad66042f059edb023e607b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-65833c099ebcc7aa1fccc5a1d930a7aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c10c3b1cc4c0a5d44aa2c137a52eaf0b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-432adfa735f19522f81538c1e139e7a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a0a00a7bb666b381893da579a6b228c9</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="SN">
  <ns0:data key="d0">SN</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">SN is the Serial Number, tracked in discrepancy reports and service invoices for fire extinguishers.&lt;SEP&gt;SN is the Serial Number used for tracking materiel in COSIS inspections and reports.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-abd2ceb311ce78c8a8c1fe38d11ee4f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CLIX">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CLIX</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CLIX is Class IX repair parts included in sustainment block listings and sub-inventories.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="NSE">
  <ns0:data key="d0">NSE</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">NSE refers to Navy Support Element, including force modules prioritized for containerized asset production and covered in reports.&lt;SEP&gt;NSE refers to Navy Support Element assets including CESE, containers, watercraft, and weapons managed by MCMC.&lt;SEP&gt;NSE is the Navy Support Element whose RO signs CALs for temporary loans to MAGTF.&lt;SEP&gt;NSE is included in Navy CESE for which MCMC performs PMCS and load banking on generators.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-955c2fafc0e5a2a07e97130b42a872b5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38be7e49aefd10e870f45cb648f7d79d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CBRN">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CBRN</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CBRN refers to Chemical, Biological, Radiological, and Nuclear equipment inspected during sustainment block operations.&lt;SEP&gt;CBRN refers to Chemical, Biological, Radiological, and Nuclear assets or activities included in MCPP production planning by the MCMC.&lt;SEP&gt;CBRN refers to Chemical, Biological, Radiological, and Nuclear assets accounted for in DPAS.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-bd3a05bb896b89de7fd366c654ad4a6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a0a00a7bb666b381893da579a6b228c9</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Non-Standard Equipment">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Non-Standard Equipment</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Non-Standard Equipment includes items like wash racks and floodlights with HQMC-established purchase orders.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CCI">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CCI</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CCI is Controlled Cryptographic Items excluded from exercise transfers.&lt;SEP&gt;CCI is Controlled Cryptographic Items handled, stored, and transported by MCMC in accordance with directives.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-f918f57232ad428f5920d4c98f0af702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841063</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="E+5">
  <ns0:data key="d0">E+5</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">E+5 is the timeline five days after the start of each ship's production cycle for submitting signed listings.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="OH">
  <ns0:data key="d0">OH</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">OH refers to On-Hand inventory quantities compared against APSR records.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MCO 10330.2">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MCO 10330.2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MCO 10330.2 outlines procedures for warehousing and materiel handling.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MCO 4140.5A">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MCO 4140.5A</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MCO 4140.5A addresses security and storage requirements for property.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MMV200">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MMV200</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MMV200 serves as the primary source for replenishing Class III(P), IV, and IX consumables.&lt;SEP&gt;MMV200 is the code for the General Account in retail level inventory.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-abd2ceb311ce78c8a8c1fe38d11ee4f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Exercise Support Letter">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Exercise Support Letter</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">The Exercise Support Letter outlines the scope of exercise support provided at MCSF-BI.&lt;SEP&gt;Exercise Support Letter is a key supporting document for transfers in support of exercises or contingencies.&lt;SEP&gt;Exercise Support Letter provides requirements for MCMC to deliver exercise support including personnel deployment, maintenance, and funding details.&lt;SEP&gt;Exercise Support Letter is a government-provided document specifying requirements for MCMC exercise support, including duration, CLIN allocations, and funding.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-93752a7bd8aca85ef0ce5fea3701dc32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38be7e49aefd10e870f45cb648f7d79d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="DD Form 1348">
  <ns0:data key="d0">DD Form 1348</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">DD Form 1348 is a document used if required for supporting transfers and chain of custody.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Section 4.C.2.d">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Section 4.C.2.d</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">section</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Section 4.C.2.d describes requirements for maintaining chain of custody of ME and SL-3 during shipments to maintenance facilities.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Section 4.C.3">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Section 4.C.3</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">section</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Section 4.C.3 outlines maintenance of materiel accountability for perpetual inventory in MPF and prepositioning programs using GCSS-MC.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Section 4.C.3.a">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Section 4.C.3.a</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">clause</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Section 4.C.3.a requires cyclical physical inventories of perpetual inventory for intermediate level retail accounts.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Section 4.C.3.b">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Section 4.C.3.b</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">clause</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Section 4.C.3.b specifies utilization of perpetual sub-inventories in GCSS-MC for prepositioned stocks.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Section 4.C.3.c">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Section 4.C.3.c</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">clause</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Section 4.C.3.c details loading of prepositioned shipboard sustainment blocks to GCSS-MC sub-inventories.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Section 4.C.4">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Section 4.C.4</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">section</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Section 4.C.4 covers management of physical inventory for MPE/S afloat or ashore.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Section 4.C.4.a">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Section 4.C.4.a</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">clause</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Section 4.C.4.a requires submission of signed CMRs and listings after production cycles.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Section 4.C.4.b">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Section 4.C.4.b</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">clause</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Section 4.C.4.b mandates monthly physical inventories of serialized small arms aboard MPS.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Section 4.C.4.c">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Section 4.C.4.c</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">clause</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Section 4.C.4.c addresses chain of custody during exercise and contingency operations using CALs.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Section 4.C.5">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Section 4.C.5</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">section</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Section 4.C.5 describes storage and warehousing operations for Government-owned property.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Section 4.C.5.a">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Section 4.C.5.a</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">clause</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Section 4.C.5.a requires maintenance of an updated stock location database for retail accounts.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Section 4.C.5.b">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Section 4.C.5.b</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">clause</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Section 4.C.5.b specifies use of STRATIS for warehousing management of General Account stocks.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Section 4.C.5.c">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Section 4.C.5.c</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">clause</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Section 4.C.5.c establishes requirements for the COSIS surveillance program.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
