<ns0:node id="ANSI/ASQ Z1.4-2003">
  <ns0:data key="d0">ANSI/ASQ Z1.4-2003</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">requirement</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">ANSI/ASQ Z1.4-2003 is a standard for quality control measures that the contractor shall employ.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2829fe507a5073eafb2e5fb0cc5e85c9</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="ANSI/ASQ Z1.9-2003">
  <ns0:data key="d0">ANSI/ASQ Z1.9-2003</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">requirement</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">ANSI/ASQ Z1.9-2003 is a standard for quality control measures that the contractor shall employ.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2829fe507a5073eafb2e5fb0cc5e85c9</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Lean Six Sigma">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Lean Six Sigma</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Lean Six Sigma is a set of principles, concepts, and practices recognized as standards by the American Society of Quality that the contractor shall employ.&lt;SEP&gt;Lean Six Sigma is defined by the acronym LSS.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2829fe507a5073eafb2e5fb0cc5e85c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-46778545759b6a3b0240557a9acb9577</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="E-1 Inspection/Monitoring Of Performance">
  <ns0:data key="d0">E-1 Inspection/Monitoring Of Performance</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">section</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">E-1 Inspection/Monitoring Of Performance is a section outlining inspection and monitoring procedures for services under the contract.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2829fe507a5073eafb2e5fb0cc5e85c9</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Statement Of Work">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Statement Of Work</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">statement_of_work</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Attached document detailing tasks, responsibilities, and sections for contract performance including maintenance activities and program management.&lt;SEP&gt;Statement Of Work is a document that specifies technical standards for maintenance, preservation, and inspection.&lt;SEP&gt;Statement Of Work is defined by the acronym SOW.&lt;SEP&gt;Statement Of Work specifies requirements, schedules, and conditions for submitting numerous reports and deliverables, often referenced as the basis for as-required submissions.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2829fe507a5073eafb2e5fb0cc5e85c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-46778545759b6a3b0240557a9acb9577&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aa9424078fa723e2caaae8aa59fb4397&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f0bef8ac155e28eb1ccd0095250383c3</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="BICmd Risk And Performance Manual">
  <ns0:data key="d0">BICmd Risk And Performance Manual</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">BICmd Risk And Performance Manual, designated as CmdO P5000.11, is a manual that the MCMC's Quality Control Plan must align with to comply with ISO Joint Certification requirements.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2829fe507a5073eafb2e5fb0cc5e85c9</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="ISO Joint Certification">
  <ns0:data key="d0">ISO Joint Certification</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">requirement</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">ISO Joint Certification is a requirement that the MCMC's Quality Control Plan must comply with.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2829fe507a5073eafb2e5fb0cc5e85c9</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Quality Management Support System">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Quality Management Support System</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Quality Management Support System is a government-provided system that the MCMC shall use to document all inspection and monitoring of services.&lt;SEP&gt;Quality Management Support System is defined by the acronym QMSS.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2829fe507a5073eafb2e5fb0cc5e85c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-46778545759b6a3b0240557a9acb9577</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Contracting Officer'S Representative">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Contracting Officer'S Representative</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">person</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Contracting Officer's Representative is a government personnel involved in inspection, monitoring, and resolution of issues.&lt;SEP&gt;Role assigned at the task order level to inspect, monitor services, and appoint technical personnel for contract oversight.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2829fe507a5073eafb2e5fb0cc5e85c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e8f1210c8fd617812bffc0e6bfaef07</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Quality Assurance Representatives">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Quality Assurance Representatives</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">person</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Quality Assurance Representatives are government personnel responsible for the inspection and monitoring of equipment, supplies, or processes.&lt;SEP&gt;Quality Assurance Representatives are the QAR personnel appointed to assist COR with quality assurance, inspection, surveillance, and certification of MCMC performance, monitored by COR.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2829fe507a5073eafb2e5fb0cc5e85c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-386066b546b82c7b89bda0ef90b3a5f2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Marine Corps Logistics Command">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Marine Corps Logistics Command</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Marine Corps Logistics Command contracts for logistics services in support of prepositioned assets, including maintenance and supply functions.&lt;SEP&gt;Marine Corps Logistics Command is an organization with cognizant personnel charged with responsibility for the MPS Program, MCPP-N, and MCPP-PHIL.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2829fe507a5073eafb2e5fb0cc5e85c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-73f90f99a53e4953f841f6b0275ecb2f</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MPS Program">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MPS Program</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">other</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MPS Program is the Maritime Prepositioning Ships Program, supported by MCMC for logistics and maintenance during rotations and dry dock periods.&lt;SEP&gt;MPS Program is a program for which Marine Corps Logistics Command and Blount Island Command personnel are responsible.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2829fe507a5073eafb2e5fb0cc5e85c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c12bdd730383e0d5968b0354d37c6d8a</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="E-2 Acceptance">
  <ns0:data key="d0">E-2 Acceptance</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">section</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">E-2 Acceptance is a section specifying the place of acceptance as Blount Island, Jacksonville, Florida, unless otherwise designated.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2829fe507a5073eafb2e5fb0cc5e85c9</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Blount Island">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Blount Island</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">location</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Blount Island is the site of MCSF-BI where MMC activities and prepositioning operations occur.&lt;SEP&gt;Blount Island is a CONUS-based facility where MCMC performs equipment maintenance and materiel management.&lt;SEP&gt;Blount Island is the site of Marine Corps Support Facility where MCMC provides equipment support and management services.&lt;SEP&gt;Blount Island is the place of acceptance for services and supplies, located in Jacksonville, Florida.&lt;SEP&gt;Blount Island is the facility where MCMC supports MCSF-BI, BICmd, and tenant organizations with voice, video, and data services under the Marine Corps Prepositioning mission.&lt;SEP&gt;Blount Island is the site location where participants must travel for the Site Visit, requiring at least one hour for check-in at the main gate.&lt;SEP&gt;Blount Island is the location of the Marine Corps Support Facility and is accessed via a causeway from Heckscher Drive in Jacksonville, Florida.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-33458028830a7ae0043a51d8a7a1e726&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c12bdd730383e0d5968b0354d37c6d8a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2829fe507a5073eafb2e5fb0cc5e85c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93752a7bd8aca85ef0ce5fea3701dc32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf666a8ded534eb47b7eede4412a01f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4ef5ed78269155f4369ff9bd9b69ddc8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f121013aeb8c98e8b0609d68d89b74e5</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Jacksonville, Florida">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Jacksonville, Florida</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">location</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Jacksonville, Florida is the location of the Marine Corps Support Facility Blount Island where primary program efforts are accomplished.&lt;SEP&gt;Jacksonville, Florida is the location of MCSF-BI hosting prepositioning and maintenance activities.&lt;SEP&gt;Jacksonville, Florida is the location of Blount Island where acceptance occurs.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2829fe507a5073eafb2e5fb0cc5e85c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-73f90f99a53e4953f841f6b0275ecb2f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93752a7bd8aca85ef0ce5fea3701dc32</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Section F Deliveries Or Performance">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Section F Deliveries Or Performance</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">section</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Section F Deliveries Or Performance is a section providing delivery information for various CLINs.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2829fe507a5073eafb2e5fb0cc5e85c9</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="USMC Blount Island Command MPF Program">
  <ns0:data key="d0">USMC Blount Island Command MPF Program</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">USMC Blount Island Command MPF Program is the ship-to address for deliveries, located at 5880 Channel View Blvd., Jacksonville, FL 32226-3404.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2829fe507a5073eafb2e5fb0cc5e85c9</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CLIN 0001">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CLIN 0001</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CLIN 0001 has a period of performance from 01-MAY-2027 to 30-APR-2032 and is shipped to USMC Blount Island Command MPF Program with FOB Destination.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2829fe507a5073eafb2e5fb0cc5e85c9</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Destination Government">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Destination Government</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">other</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Destination Government is a repeated term associated with various codes such as 6005, 6006, indicating shipping or delivery designations.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2829fe507a5073eafb2e5fb0cc5e85c9</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="M6700425R0007 Draft RFP">
  <ns0:data key="d0">M6700425R0007 Draft RFP</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">M6700425R0007 Draft RFP is the document containing the clauses, sections, and delivery information.&lt;SEP&gt;M6700425R0007 Draft RFP is the solicitation document containing the sections and clauses outlined.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2829fe507a5073eafb2e5fb0cc5e85c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b6f17f0fbf6c678da23e588ab57f6900</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="DODAAC M38450">
  <ns0:data key="d0">DODAAC M38450</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">other</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">DODAAC M38450 is the Department of Defense Activity Address Code assigned to the USMC Blount Island Command MPF Program for delivery purposes.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2829fe507a5073eafb2e5fb0cc5e85c9</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="FOB Destination">
  <ns0:data key="d0">FOB Destination</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">FOB Destination is the freight on board term specifying delivery responsibilities to the destination for all CLINs under the contract.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2829fe507a5073eafb2e5fb0cc5e85c9</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Third Party Certification Organization">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Third Party Certification Organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Third Party Certification Organization is a government-approved entity responsible for certifying the contractor to ANSI/ISO 9001:2015 within nine months of contract award.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2829fe507a5073eafb2e5fb0cc5e85c9</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Prepositioning Ship">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Prepositioning Ship</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">other</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Prepositioning Ship is the vessel where certain services are performed, subject to inspection by the Master or Officers for compliance with maritime laws and safety.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2829fe507a5073eafb2e5fb0cc5e85c9</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Vessel Master">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Vessel Master</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">person</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Vessel Master is responsible for inspecting methods of performing services on prepositioning ships to ensure conformance with maritime laws, rules, and regulations.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2829fe507a5073eafb2e5fb0cc5e85c9</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="5880 Channel View Blvd">
  <ns0:data key="d0">5880 Channel View Blvd</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">location</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">5880 Channel View Blvd is the address of USMC Blount Island Command in Jacksonville FL 32226.&lt;SEP&gt;5880 Channel View Blvd is the specific street address for the USMC Blount Island Command MPF Program in Jacksonville, FL 32226-3404.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-2829fe507a5073eafb2e5fb0cc5e85c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8aa129e6fff6d48e4dab5ab9c9d8c169</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841064</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Navy Production Assembly and Class IX Inventory Short List">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Navy Production Assembly and Class IX Inventory Short List</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Navy Production Assembly and Class IX Inventory Short List is an attachment (SOW Attachment C.6-013) that MCMC shall deliver within three business days of inventory completion and use for attaining materials.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MPS Production Schedule">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MPS Production Schedule</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MPS Production Schedule outlines timelines for maintenance, operational service checks, container production, and other activities that MCMC shall follow.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Ships PCL">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Ships PCL</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Ship’s PCL provides details for maintenance, packaging, and production that MCMC shall adhere to in coordination with applicable plans.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Navy Containerized Equipment Maintenance Transfer Log">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Navy Containerized Equipment Maintenance Transfer Log</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Navy Containerized Equipment Maintenance Transfer Log (CDRL 6028, SOW Attachment C.6-019) is a log that MCMC shall provide and maintain, delivering it bi-weekly to NAV-P.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Navy Container Contents Packing List">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Navy Container Contents Packing List</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Navy Container Contents Packing List (CDRL 6029, SOW Attachment C.6-014) identifies container contents and is delivered by MCMC to NAV-P within two business days after completion.&lt;SEP&gt;Navy Container Contents Packing List is submitted NLT two business days under section 6.D.5.b for X002.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-aa9424078fa723e2caaae8aa59fb4397&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Navy End of Ship Class II, III, IV, VII, and IX Attainment Percentage Reports">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Navy End of Ship Class II, III, IV, VII, and IX Attainment Percentage Reports</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Navy End of Ship Class II, III, IV, VII, and IX Attainment Percentage Reports (CDRL 6030, SOW Attachment C.6-015) are submitted by MCMC five business days after production period completion.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Navy Assemblies and Class IX Shortage Report">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Navy Assemblies and Class IX Shortage Report</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Navy Assemblies and Class IX Shortage Report (CDRL 6031, SOW Attachment C.6-016) is submitted separately for NSE and NCE by MCMC five business days after production period completion.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Navy INLS, MPFUB, LARC, ABLTS and LCM-8 Class IX Attainment and Shortage Report">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Navy INLS, MPFUB, LARC, ABLTS and LCM-8 Class IX Attainment and Shortage Report</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Navy INLS, MPFUB, LARC, ABLTS and LCM-8 Class IX Attainment and Shortage Report (CDRL 6032, SOW Attachment C.6-017) is submitted by MCMC five business days after production period completion.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Navy End of Production Container Report">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Navy End of Production Container Report</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Navy End of Production Container Report (CDRL 6033, SOW Attachment C.6-012) covers MCPIC designated Navy containers and is submitted by MCMC within five business days after production period completion.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Navy Consolidated Memorandum Receipt">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Navy Consolidated Memorandum Receipt</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Navy Consolidated Memorandum Receipt (CMR, CDRL 6034, SOW Attachment C.6-021) for on-island PEIs is submitted by MCMC by the fifth business day of each quarter.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Navy Calibration Report">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Navy Calibration Report</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Navy Calibration Report (CDRL 6035, SOW Attachment C.6-022) is delivered by MCMC NLT E Day or seven business days after production cycle end.&lt;SEP&gt;Navy Calibration Report is submitted on E-Day or seven business days following EOS production cycle under section 6.D.7 for X002.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-aa9424078fa723e2caaae8aa59fb4397&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="ISO Freight Container">
  <ns0:data key="d0">ISO Freight Container</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">ISO Freight Container requires inventory, maintenance, inspection, recertification, and compliance with standards like ISO Handbook and MIL-STD-3037 by MCMC.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="NCE">
  <ns0:data key="d0">NCE</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">NCE refers to components or elements requiring separate reporting and maintenance coordination by MCMC.&lt;SEP&gt;NCE refers to Navy Cargo Element assets such as containers under specific controls.&lt;SEP&gt;NCE is included in Navy CESE for which MCMC performs PMCS and load banking on generators.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-955c2fafc0e5a2a07e97130b42a872b5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38be7e49aefd10e870f45cb648f7d79d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="EBL">
  <ns0:data key="d0">EBL</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">EBL is Expeditionary Bos’n Locker, a prioritized NSE force module for containerized asset production.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="HFP">
  <ns0:data key="d0">HFP</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">HFP is High Failure Parts Container, a prioritized NSE force module for containerized asset production.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CSM">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CSM</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CSM is Craft Support Module, a prioritized NSE force module for containerized asset production.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="BPM">
  <ns0:data key="d0">BPM</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">BPM is Beach Party Module, a prioritized NSE force module for containerized asset production.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="RRDF">
  <ns0:data key="d0">RRDF</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">RRDF is Roll On/Roll Off Discharge Facility, a prioritized NSE force module for containerized asset production and service life data management.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="EPM">
  <ns0:data key="d0">EPM</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">EPM is Expeditionary Pier Module, a prioritized NSE force module for containerized asset production.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="NSE Headquarters">
  <ns0:data key="d0">NSE Headquarters</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">NSE Headquarters is a prioritized NSE force module for containerized asset production.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="HCM">
  <ns0:data key="d0">HCM</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">HCM is Horizontal Construction Module, a prioritized NSE force module for containerized asset production.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="CRM">
  <ns0:data key="d0">CRM</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">CRM is CESE Regeneration Module, a prioritized NSE force module for containerized asset production.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="EHM">
  <ns0:data key="d0">EHM</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">EHM is Expeditionary Habitability Module, a prioritized NSE force module for containerized asset production.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="EAM">
  <ns0:data key="d0">EAM</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">EAM is Expeditionary Aid Module, a prioritized NSE force module for containerized asset production.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="NAVSUP">
  <ns0:data key="d0">NAVSUP</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">NAVSUP is referenced in NAVSUP P-485, which MCMC shall follow for attaining materials and shortages.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="P-700-CNP">
  <ns0:data key="d0">P-700-CNP</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">P-700-CNP is the Common Naval Packaging standard that MCMC shall adhere to for packaging, inventory sheets, and labeling.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="MCO P4030.21">
  <ns0:data key="d0">MCO P4030.21</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">MCO P4030.21 is a standard for packaging and inventory sheets that MCMC shall follow.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="PEI">
  <ns0:data key="d0">PEI</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">PEI stands for palletized equipment items that must be weighed and have accurate stowed weight data entered into IPACK.&lt;SEP&gt;PEI is Prepositioned Equipment Inventory requiring maintenance and staging.&lt;SEP&gt;PEI refers to Principle End Items that are packed, labeled, registered with IUID, and tagged with pRFID by MCMC.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89b1a9fa6c0722adcd478e665df09141&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="iMark Label">
  <ns0:data key="d0">iMark Label</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">iMark Label is installed on the outside of Navy used containers and inside protective sleeves by MCMC.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="pRFID Tag">
  <ns0:data key="d0">pRFID Tag</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">technology</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">pRFID Tag is a passive RFID tag placed on all Navy PEIs by MCMC.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="DD Form 2282">
  <ns0:data key="d0">DD Form 2282</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">DD Form 2282 is used for CSC decals on ISO containers, valid for at least 60 days at embarkation.&lt;SEP&gt;DD Form 2282 is used for CSC decals on containers, which must be valid for at least 60 days at embarkation.&lt;SEP&gt;DD Form 2282 is the container certification form completed by MCMC prior to packing, use, or shipment, with CSC decal applied.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-abd2ceb311ce78c8a8c1fe38d11ee4f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-30ad74540c8224cf4aff1f3de36d3780&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Service Life Data Sheet">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Service Life Data Sheet</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Service Life Data Sheet is created and completed by MCMC for natural fiber and synthetic lines in specified modules, with copies maintained.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Manila Tag">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Manila Tag</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Manila Tag contains service life information and is placed on all lines by MCMC.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="LTI">
  <ns0:data key="d0">LTI</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">LTI is Limited Technical Inspection performed by MCMC on CESE to determine condition and assign codes.&lt;SEP&gt;LTI is Condition Code Limited Technical Inspection performed by MCMC for Navy CESE shipments, redistribution, and disposal.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-955c2fafc0e5a2a07e97130b42a872b5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Navy Point">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Navy Point</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">location</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Navy Point is the designated location where MCMC shall stow all Navy Containers, except for staging.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Expeditionary Medical Facility">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Expeditionary Medical Facility</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Expeditionary Medical Facility requires PMCS as needed by MCMC.&lt;SEP&gt;Expeditionary Medical Facility is defined by the acronym EMF.&lt;SEP&gt;Expeditionary Medical Facility equipment requires PMCS as needed by MCMC.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-955c2fafc0e5a2a07e97130b42a872b5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-46778545759b6a3b0240557a9acb9577&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="QAR">
  <ns0:data key="d0">QAR</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">person</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">QAR is a government role interacting with designated MCMC quality personnel.&lt;SEP&gt;QAR is the Navy Quality Assurance Representative notified by MCMC 24 to 48 hours before performing equipment operational function tests.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-432adfa735f19522f81538c1e139e7a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="M6700425R0007 Draft Rfp">
  <ns0:data key="d0">M6700425R0007 Draft Rfp</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Draft Request for Proposals identified by solicitation number M6700425R0007, spanning pages 344 to 349 of 425 and including provisions on phase-in requirements and contract clauses.&lt;SEP&gt;M6700425R0007 Draft Rfp is a draft request for proposal dated August 2018 spanning 425 pages and incorporating various DFARS and FAR clauses related to contractor requirements, personnel, and payments.&lt;SEP&gt;M6700425R0007 Draft Rfp is a draft request for proposal document outlining contract requirements, deliverables, and clauses for Navy-related services.&lt;SEP&gt;M6700425R0007 Draft RFP details required reports, forms, and deliverables for supply, maintenance, inventory, financial reporting, and operational activities across various sections of the contract.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-7ab97f6224f9bb5da997102b5a8a397f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-28d6e3bcda588a7e152c62f52269f946&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aa9424078fa723e2caaae8aa59fb4397&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4c6c8cc3b4b40997aa333b8fb93d6c6b</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Nav-P">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Nav-P</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">organization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Nav-P oversees approvals for repairs, receives requested records and reports, and directs certain maintenance and testing activities related to watercraft and equipment.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-aa9424078fa723e2caaae8aa59fb4397</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841065</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Government Furnished Equipment">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Government Furnished Equipment</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Government Furnished Equipment includes non-PO equipment on which MCMC conducts PMCS in accordance with technical manuals and PMCS Roster.&lt;SEP&gt;Government Furnished Equipment, abbreviated as GFE, refers to equipment provided by the government for use in contracts and operations.&lt;SEP&gt;Government Furnished Equipment is defined by the acronym GFE.&lt;SEP&gt;Government Furnished Equipment is utilized by the Contractor for dispensing Government-procured fuel in NTVE and MHE.&lt;SEP&gt;Government Furnished Equipment consists of IT equipment listed in SOW Attachment C.1-2, with MCMC requiring Government approval for any associated peripherals.&lt;SEP&gt;Government Furnished Equipment consists of assets provided by the government that require procurement requests, status reporting, discrepancy notifications, and accountability for losses or damages.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-9fdacd5fbf292ea850730c0c323f0873&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8efbcbadad92a347ffdc7b5c1e34b2f7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-30e4e078d2ff5ac82b96140f8c79e3f2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-46778545759b6a3b0240557a9acb9577&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf666a8ded534eb47b7eede4412a01f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aa9424078fa723e2caaae8aa59fb4397</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841066</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Production Cycle">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Production Cycle</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Production Cycle represents operational phases in the contract, including end points like Px-14, with associated reporting milestones such as E+5, E-1, and EOS for inventory and attainment.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-aa9424078fa723e2caaae8aa59fb4397</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841066</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Quarterly Ga Recommended Stock Levels Report">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Quarterly Ga Recommended Stock Levels Report</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">deliverable</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Quarterly Ga Recommended Stock Levels Report provides recommendations on stock levels and is required quarterly for X002 and X003 under section 4.A.2.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-aa9424078fa723e2caaae8aa59fb4397</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841066</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
