<ns0:node id="Marine Corps Prepositioning Program">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Marine Corps Prepositioning Program</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Marine Corps Prepositioning Program involves providing combat-ready assets, equipment sets, supplies, and sustainment blocks to Operating Forces worldwide.&lt;SEP&gt;The Marine Corps Prepositioning Program involves prepositioning equipment and supplies aboard ships and at land sites to support rapid deployment of Marine Corps forces.&lt;SEP&gt;Marine Corps Prepositioning Program is the program supported by MCMC through personnel, maintenance, and compliance efforts across various locations.&lt;SEP&gt;Marine Corps Prepositioning Program is defined by the acronym MCPP. Use CONCEPT.&lt;SEP&gt;Marine Corps Prepositioning Program is defined by the acronym MCPP.&lt;SEP&gt;Marine Corps Prepositioning Program requires commercial sources for operations, maintenance, and logistics support.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-939c604b9027c9cc38a7fb31f4c86c29&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8efbcbadad92a347ffdc7b5c1e34b2f7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-46778545759b6a3b0240557a9acb9577&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2edf7351f7d27be2ca8809d7ac16a11d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-73f90f99a53e4953f841f6b0275ecb2f</ns0:data>
