<ns0:node id="Quality Assurance Representative">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Quality Assurance Representative</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">person</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">The Quality Assurance Representative provides quality oversight and ensures compliance with contractual requirements.&lt;SEP&gt;Quality Assurance Representative is a trained full-time quality evaluator who provides quality oversight of the contractor and ensures compliance with contractual requirements.&lt;SEP&gt;Quality Assurance Representative is defined by the acronym QAR.&lt;SEP&gt;Quality Assurance Representative contacts are listed for past performance references.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-46778545759b6a3b0240557a9acb9577&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6b04b67f7f379aa858c2a82b29df69a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2edf7351f7d27be2ca8809d7ac16a11d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93752a7bd8aca85ef0ce5fea3701dc32</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841085</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Quality Control">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Quality Control</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Quality Control is defined by the acronym QC.&lt;SEP&gt;Quality Control involves early deficiency detection, trend analysis, and management involvement, with staffing concerns for shipboard and production.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-46778545759b6a3b0240557a9acb9577&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6b04b67f7f379aa858c2a82b29df69a0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841085</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Quality Control Plan">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Quality Control Plan</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">concept</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">The Quality Control Plan is described in Section C.2.D and contains KPIs that describe the state of the MCMC’s quality control program, part of QMSS KPI dashboard.&lt;SEP&gt;Quality Control Plan is defined by the acronym QCP.&lt;SEP&gt;Quality Control Plan must be provided annually by the MCMC no later than 01 November, per SOW C.2.D.1.g.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-bee5e6b5db1fe2dc611fc5fc2b227a51&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-46778545759b6a3b0240557a9acb9577&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-939c604b9027c9cc38a7fb31f4c86c29</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d4">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d5">1759841085</ns0:data>
</ns0:node>
<ns0:node id="Quality Deficiency Report">
  <ns0:data key="d0">Quality Deficiency Report</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d1">document</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d2">Quality Deficiency Report is defined by the acronym QDR.&lt;SEP&gt;Quality Deficiency Report is prepared for problems identified during initial safety inspections of new or reassigned vehicles.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d3">chunk-27cca63c94e6ea85e547a26e12b48a3c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-46778545759b6a3b0240557a9acb9577</ns0:data>
