<ns0:edge source="MCPP-PHIL" target="USINDOPACOM AO">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">MCPP-PHIL services involve work at facilities within USINDOPACOM AO, primarily in Subic Bay Philippines, subject to emerging operational requirements.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">geographic scope,work locations</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-f736781b685dec5629d8433e71c666e4</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841134</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCPP-PHIL" target="Philippines">
  <ns0:data key="d6">5.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">MCPP-PHIL operations are primarily in Subic Bay Philippines, adhering to host nation labor laws and holiday restrictions.&lt;SEP&gt;MCPP-PHIL operations in the Philippines require commercial importer status, CRTE, and coordination with SBMA for equipment shipments.&lt;SEP&gt;MCPP-PHIL operations require Synchronized Predeployment Operational Tracker Letters of Authorization for countries including Philippines.&lt;SEP&gt;MCPP-PHIL involves prepositioned equipment shipped to the Philippines with SKOT validation.&lt;SEP&gt;Philippines is the operational location for MCPP-PHIL where AMALs are maintained, replenished, and refreshed.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">authorization,host nation compliance,import clearance,location association,operations,prepositioning,primary location,program focus,program location,site specificity</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-a9aba44b05f751488f4a50faebf206cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22de15a10ae9bfba6096cca855d5f78a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2edf7351f7d27be2ca8809d7ac16a11d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f736781b685dec5629d8433e71c666e4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-30ad74540c8224cf4aff1f3de36d3780</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841134</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCPP-PHIL" target="MCMC">
  <ns0:data key="d6">8.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">MCMC employees require SPOT LOA for MCPP-PHIL operations in specified countries within USINDOPACOM AO.&lt;SEP&gt;The MCMC procures fuel locally for MCPP-PHIL due to the absence of a supporting DLA fuel facility.&lt;SEP&gt;MCMC supports supply and medical inventory management for MCPP-PHIL, ensuring minimum shelf-life requirements.&lt;SEP&gt;The MCMC establishes and maintains MCPP-PHIL DSI inventories, optimizing levels to meet operational needs.&lt;SEP&gt;MCMC performs 90-day COSIS on PO assets stored indoors as part of MCPP-PHIL specific requirements.&lt;SEP&gt;MCMC ships materiel to MCPP-PHIL with 25 months or greater shelf life remaining.&lt;SEP&gt;MCMC manages operations, import/export, and compliance for MCPP-PHIL in Subic Bay.&lt;SEP&gt;MCMC provides resource plans, equipment validation, and status reports for MCPP-PHIL exercises.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">COSIS,authorization,compliance,exercise support,fuel procurement,inventory,inventory optimization,logistics management,operational support,prepositioning,production period,program support,shelf life,shipment,site-specific operations,support</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-13a4841aefad66042f059edb023e607b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f918f57232ad428f5920d4c98f0af702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c12bdd730383e0d5968b0354d37c6d8a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8a136ea2c9ab7ea9bb718fd0abd010d4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-68739860c42b764e52f9649ea16ed702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f736781b685dec5629d8433e71c666e4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-65833c099ebcc7aa1fccc5a1d930a7aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a0a00a7bb666b381893da579a6b228c9</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841144</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
