</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="UM 4000-125" target="MAGTF">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">UM 4000-125 outlines procedures for issuing supplies to MAGTF during exercises.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">exercise issuance,support procedures</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-abd2ceb311ce78c8a8c1fe38d11ee4f4</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841366</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="UM 4000-125" target="MCMC">
  <ns0:data key="d6">2.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">The MCMC uses UM 4000-125 for calibration, modification control, TAV, equipment records, corrective maintenance, cannibalization, and UUAM procedures.&lt;SEP&gt;MCMC completes calibration services for ME and CESE using UM 4000-125 and records inspections, maintenance, and testing of portable fire extinguishers.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">calibration,guidance reference,program support,recording procedures</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-13a4841aefad66042f059edb023e607b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a0a00a7bb666b381893da579a6b228c9</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841371</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="UM 4000-125" target="Marine Corps Maintenance Coordinator (MCMC)">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">The MCMC prepares and retains transportation documents per UM 4000-125 procedures.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">compliance,documentation</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-30ad74540c8224cf4aff1f3de36d3780</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841406</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="UM 4000-125" target="Limited Technical Inspections (LTIs)">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">LTIs on ME and CESE assets are conducted in accordance with UM 4000-125.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">compliance,procedure</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-432adfa735f19522f81538c1e139e7a3</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841438</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="UM 4000-125" target="GCSS-MC">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">GCSS-MC documentation of maintenance services on TAMCN IT assets is performed in accordance with UM 4000-125.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">documentation compliance</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-cf666a8ded534eb47b7eede4412a01f1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841518</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCPP-N" target="MCMC">
  <ns0:data key="d6">4.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">The MCMC processes confirmations of receipt for materiel at MCPP-N in Norway.&lt;SEP&gt;MCMC ships materiel to MCPP-N with 25 months or greater shelf life remaining.&lt;SEP&gt;MCMC provides services for MCPP-N in the Trondelog region using government facilities and equipment.&lt;SEP&gt;The MCMC provides DSI Authorization Letters for MCPP-N in Norway only if needed for COMM/ELEC equipment.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">conditional DSI,equipment specific,logistics support,operations,receipt processing,shelf life,shipment,site-specific operations</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-65833c099ebcc7aa1fccc5a1d930a7aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-68739860c42b764e52f9649ea16ed702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c12bdd730383e0d5968b0354d37c6d8a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89b1a9fa6c0722adcd478e665df09141</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841206</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCPP-N" target="NEIMS">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">NEIMS provides data for initial CALs in the MCPP-N program prior to exercises.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">CAL generation,data provision</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841243</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCPP-N" target="E-1 Inspection/Monitoring Of Performance">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">The section includes inspection and monitoring related to MCPP-N.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">inspection scope,program monitoring</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-2829fe507a5073eafb2e5fb0cc5e85c9</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841279</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCPP-N" target="Norway">
  <ns0:data key="d6">3.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">MCPP-N operations in Norway involve host nation authority for recertification and prior approvals for equipment transport.&lt;SEP&gt;MCPP-N involves prepositioned equipment stored in Norway requiring MCMC management of weapons.&lt;SEP&gt;Norway is the operational location for MCPP-N where AMALs are maintained, replenished, and refreshed.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">location association,operations,prepositioning,program location,regulatory compliance,site specificity</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-a9aba44b05f751488f4a50faebf206cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22de15a10ae9bfba6096cca855d5f78a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-30ad74540c8224cf4aff1f3de36d3780</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841330</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCPP-N" target="USMC">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">The USMC prepositioned equipment for MCPP-N in Norway including crew served weapons accounted by the MCMC.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">oversight,program execution</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-22de15a10ae9bfba6096cca855d5f78a</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841330</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCPP-N" target="Norway Branch">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">The MCMC coordinates MCPP-N activities, including validations and notifications, with the Norway Branch.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">branch oversight,program coordination</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-a0a00a7bb666b381893da579a6b228c9</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841353</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCPP-N" target="Trondelog Region">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">MCPP-N services are provided in the Trondelog region of Norway.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">location,prepositioning</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-c12bdd730383e0d5968b0354d37c6d8a</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841370</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCPP-N" target="MCPP-N KMI Local Element (LE)">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">MCMC maintains the MCPP-N KMI Local Element subaccount with two-person integrity for COMSEC/CCI.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">integrity,management</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-c12bdd730383e0d5968b0354d37c6d8a</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841371</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCPP-N" target="Program Cost Summary">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">Program Cost Summary collects and reports cost data for MCPP-N program by ship and class.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">data collection,reporting</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-432adfa735f19522f81538c1e139e7a3</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841416</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCPP-N" target="Volume III">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">Volume III manning covers land-based prepositioning at MCPP-N.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">location inclusion,manning</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-6b04b67f7f379aa858c2a82b29df69a0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841423</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCPP-N" target="MCPP">
  <ns0:data key="d6">2.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">MCPP encompasses MCPP-N, where maintenance is limited to COMM/ELEC assets in Norway.&lt;SEP&gt;MCPP-N supports MCPP by prepositioning sensitive equipment in Norwegian storage caves.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">location specific,prepositioning,program extension,program inclusion</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-93752a7bd8aca85ef0ce5fea3701dc32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c10c3b1cc4c0a5d44aa2c137a52eaf0b</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841457</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCPP-N" target="Authorized Medical Allowance List (AMAL)">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">AMALs at MCPP-N are maintained, stored, replenished, and refreshed annually and every third year in Norway.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">maintenance location,replenishment</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-a9aba44b05f751488f4a50faebf206cb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841484</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCPP-N" target="MMV420">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">MCPP-N is associated with the MMV420 account for excess/deficiency reporting and class of supply monitoring.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">account linkage,site association</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-8efbcbadad92a347ffdc7b5c1e34b2f7</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841515</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCPP-N" target="Weekly Class of Supply Report">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">Weekly Class of Supply Report extends to all classes of supply for MCPP-N beyond Military Equipment.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">supply classes,weekly monitoring</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-8efbcbadad92a347ffdc7b5c1e34b2f7</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841516</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="PPSP" target="MCMC">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">The MCMC incorporates anticipated Surge Team utilization into the semi-annual PPSP.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">planning integration,surge utilization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-f736781b685dec5629d8433e71c666e4</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841146</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="PPSP" target="Quality Manager (QM)">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">PPSP identifies and designates Quality Manager, QIs, and PCAs for MCPP quality requirements and government interactions.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">designation,identification</ns0:data>
