  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841492</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="KO" target="MCMC">
  <ns0:data key="d6">3.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">The MCMC notifies the KO for relief from embarked asset responsibilities or for repair arrangements beyond capability.&lt;SEP&gt;The KO issues task orders to the MCMC, approves travel and reimbursements, receives notifications, and manages closeouts and claims releases.&lt;SEP&gt;The KO may terminate the contract with the MCMC for convenience if necessary to avoid an organizational conflict of interest.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">approval authority,asset relief,contract administration,notification requirement,oversight authority,termination rights</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-f736781b685dec5629d8433e71c666e4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d89c19e067243fa311d34bfc3fa99c70&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b6f17f0fbf6c678da23e588ab57f6900</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841146</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="KO" target="COR">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">The COR requests unscheduled fuel deliveries, which are overseen by the KO for approvals.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">coordination,service requests</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-27cca63c94e6ea85e547a26e12b48a3c</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841356</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="KO" target="H-21 Contract Transition Phase-In Phase-Out Plan Requirements">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">The KO resolves disagreements on information exchanges and oversees aspects of the transition plan in H-21 Contract Transition Phase-In Phase-Out Plan Requirements.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">resolution authority,transition oversight</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-b6f17f0fbf6c678da23e588ab57f6900</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841382</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="COR" target="MCMC">
  <ns0:data key="d6">5.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">The MCMC notifies the COR when additional tools or equipment are required to conduct maintenance.&lt;SEP&gt;MCMC coordinates with COR for approvals on lodging, privileges, reports, and exercise support.&lt;SEP&gt;MCMC coordinates accounting data with COR, submits reports, and reports non-conformance instances.&lt;SEP&gt;MCMC informs COR of schedule jeopardies, provides assessments at milestones, and submits Letters of Non-Conformance for deviations.&lt;SEP&gt;The MCMC submits inventory results, sampling plans, and causative research to the COR as part of transition obligations.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">approval,approval process,coordination,equipment needs,notification,notification requirement,reporting,reporting requirement,transition support</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-f918f57232ad428f5920d4c98f0af702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b6f17f0fbf6c678da23e588ab57f6900&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f736781b685dec5629d8433e71c666e4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-85b50b451f72c11f155dc39b516d8dd3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841146</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="COR" target="QCP">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">QCP files are maintained and available to the COR upon request.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">access provision,file availability</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841147</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="COR" target="COTR">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">COTR serves as the interface between MCMC, COR, and Contracting Officer, clarifying requirements during forward deployments.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">coordination,interface</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-f918f57232ad428f5920d4c98f0af702</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841281</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="COR" target="Quality Manager (QM)">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">COR interacts with designated Quality Manager as primary focal point for quality requirements.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">focal point,interaction</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-432adfa735f19522f81538c1e139e7a3</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841418</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="COR" target="MMCT">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">COR approves or rejects MMCT extension requests for maintenance.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">approval,extension</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841491</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCO 3000.17" target="MCMC">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">The MCMC follows MCO 3000.17 for Marine Corps Prepositioning Programs as a supplement to the SOW.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">compliance standard,prepositioning guidance</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-f736781b685dec5629d8433e71c666e4</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
