<ns0:edge source="MCO 3000.17" target="SECTION C.3 – MAINTENANCE ACTIVITIES">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">SECTION C.3 – MAINTENANCE ACTIVITIES requires compliance with MCO 3000.17 for equipment maintenance in support of prepositioning programs.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">compliance,reference</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-432adfa735f19522f81538c1e139e7a3</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841419</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCO 3000.17" target="MCO 4000.58">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">MCO 4000.58 supersedes MCO 3000.17 regarding minimum shelf life requirements for prepositioned materiel.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">policy priority,supersession</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-8a136ea2c9ab7ea9bb718fd0abd010d4</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841445</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="CmdO 4790.1B" target="Maintenance Management">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">Maintenance Management adheres to CmdO 4790.1B for tasks such as appointing MMO, internal inspections, and supply support.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">inspections,procedures</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-89b1a9fa6c0722adcd478e665df09141</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841278</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="CmdO 4790.1B" target="MCMC">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">The MCMC follows CmdO 4790.1B for accounting in DPAS, weekly reconciliations, calibration control, modification control, TAV configuration, publication control, equipment availability reporting, PMCS, corrective maintenance, cannibalization, load lifting, corrosion control, ELMP, and UUAM management.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">procedural adherence,program execution</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-a0a00a7bb666b381893da579a6b228c9</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841370</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="OMMS-NG" target="MCMC">
  <ns0:data key="d6">7.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">MCMC uses OMMS-NG to enter accurate maintenance actions for PMCS and CM, closing out work candidates within 30 days of completion.&lt;SEP&gt;MCMC utilizes the OMMS-NG module for entering and closing out maintenance actions on containers and CESE.&lt;SEP&gt;MCMC provides data entry services into OMMS-NG for external contractors as required by NAV-P.&lt;SEP&gt;MCMC utilizes OMMS-NG for PMCS, corrective maintenance, and work candidates, entering actions accurately and closing out within 30 days.&lt;SEP&gt;MCMC uses OMMS-NG to document corrective maintenance requests, actions, and completions for Navy Watercraft.&lt;SEP&gt;MCMC MMO utilizes OMMS-NG for Ground Support Equipment (GSE).&lt;SEP&gt;MCMC provides OMMS-NG data entry services for external contractors using information from NAV-P via 2K Transmittal Form.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">data entry,data management,documentation,maintenance management,maintenance tracking,support,system utilization,tracking,utilization</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-955c2fafc0e5a2a07e97130b42a872b5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d6887833d0f1a6398bb6c8fd6f72d5c8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5edf02307c6ad1788f6967955fbea6ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-85b50b451f72c11f155dc39b516d8dd3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93c4a54422e967728929a60f73e593e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e73c8ab3a0b248cdeedb8496a5c6f8a9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7659b0abfc62a3f8f0edbf4a1fee058e</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841148</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="OMMS-NG" target="NTCSS">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">NTCSS incorporates OMMS-NG module for inputting maintenance status, recording deficiencies, and managing work candidates for Navy Watercraft.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">maintenance tracking,system integration</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-85b50b451f72c11f155dc39b516d8dd3</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841322</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="GSE" target="MCMC">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">MCMC maintains and operates Navy GSE, including priority levels for critical assets like cranes and hoists.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">maintenance,operation</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841504</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="GSE" target="Link-Belt Crawler Crane">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">Link-Belt Crawler Crane is assigned Priority 1 maintenance under GSE as a critical asset for ship operations.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">criticality,priority assignment</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841504</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="GSE" target="Marine Travel Lift Mobile Boat Hoist">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">Marine Travel Lift Mobile Boat Hoist is assigned Priority 1 maintenance under GSE for watercraft support.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">criticality,priority assignment</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022</ns0:data>
