<ns0:edge source="MPS" target="MCMC">
  <ns0:data key="d6">7.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">MCMC ensures rations and other materiel possess specified shelf life until end at MPS embarkation.&lt;SEP&gt;MCMC processes Confirmation of Receipt in GCSS-MC upon physical receipt of materiel aboard MPS.&lt;SEP&gt;The MCMC applies exemptions for prepositioned ME on afloat MPS but requires reconciliations for organic ME.&lt;SEP&gt;MCMC provides housekeeping, maintenance, and personnel services aboard MPS under the direction of the Ship's Master.&lt;SEP&gt;MCMC performs maintenance and provides housekeeping functions aboard MPS under the ship's master's direction.&lt;SEP&gt;MCMC provides logistics services, surveillance, and maintenance for MPE/S aboard MPS during afloat phase.&lt;SEP&gt;MCMC prepares Navy Watercraft and ABLTS for embarkation and backload on MPS, including operational checks and custody transfers.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">accountability validation,afloat phase,afloat processing,backload,embarkation,exemption application,housekeeping,operational support,operations,personnel assignment,receipt confirmation,shelf life</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-f918f57232ad428f5920d4c98f0af702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48caa545ec007aaf46c9abe9ec8c0c78&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-65833c099ebcc7aa1fccc5a1d930a7aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7659b0abfc62a3f8f0edbf4a1fee058e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-583182dd35a85d121fe43aee2e3cd0eb</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841171</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MPS" target="PMCS">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">PMCS is performed on MPE/S every six months or after MPS backload operations.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">maintenance,semi-annual start-ups</ns0:data>
