<ns0:edge source="CESE" target="MCMC">
  <ns0:data key="d6">5.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">MCMC washes and cleans CESE assets upon completion of production maintenance phase, removing contaminants and ensuring compartments are free of debris.&lt;SEP&gt;MCMC performs operational function tests, cleaning, and maintenance on CESE, notifying Navy QAR in advance.&lt;SEP&gt;MCMC performs limited technical inspections, preventive maintenance, and other services on CESE.&lt;SEP&gt;Navy CESE assets are handled by the MCMC for temporary loans but accounted outside GCSS-MC.&lt;SEP&gt;MCMC issues all NSE and NCE CESE while ensuring compliance with Equipment Density List and Resource Plan.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">cleaning,exclusion handling,inspection,issuance,maintenance,maintenance responsibility,maintenance services,management,non-GCSS accountability,operational testing</ns0:data>
