<ns0:edge source="KMI" target="MCMC">
  <ns0:data key="d6">3.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">MCMC performs KMI support operations including inventory, storage, and reporting for COMSEC and CCI assets.&lt;SEP&gt;MCMC returns mobile COMSEC materiel to parent KMI accounts and handles shipping of CCI to KMI LE.&lt;SEP&gt;MCMC issues and recovers KMI assets during exercises following Section C.8 procedures and completes SF153 for transfer.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">account management,accountability,issuance,management,materiel return,recovery</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-f918f57232ad428f5920d4c98f0af702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4ef5ed78269155f4369ff9bd9b69ddc8</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841263</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="SF153" target="MCMC">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">MCMC completes SF153 for transferring KMI assets in accordance with CMS-1 directives.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">KMI compliance,transfer documentation</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-f918f57232ad428f5920d4c98f0af702</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841302</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="COTR" target="Quality Manager (QM)">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">COTR interacts with designated Quality Manager as primary focal point for quality requirements.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">focal point,interaction</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-432adfa735f19522f81538c1e139e7a3</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841419</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="COMPSRON" target="MCMC">
  <ns0:data key="d6">2.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">MCMC provides a copy of the PGP report to COMPSRON via the Squadron Supervisor.&lt;SEP&gt;COMPSRON Staff acts as a coordinating link between MCMC, Ship Masters, and operational forces drawing MPE/S from MPS.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">coordination,operational link,personnel,reporting</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-f918f57232ad428f5920d4c98f0af702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841265</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="DML" target="MCMC">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">MCMC adds non-mission capable equipment to the DML if repairs cannot be completed due to constraints.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">listing,maintenance deferral</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841263</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCMC" target="CDRL 5021">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">The MCMC provides CDRL 5021 for physical inventory results broken out by AAC.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">inventory results,reporting</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-68739860c42b764e52f9649ea16ed702</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841211</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCMC" target="AASP Plan">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">MCMC configures and prepositions the Arrival and Assembly Support Package as directed by the government-provided AASP Plan, consisting of materials for containerized asset issue outside MAGTF Table of Equipment.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">assembly support,prepositioning</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-5fcb066f3ce0c1cfffc65441135b96e1</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841256</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCMC" target="RFP">
  <ns0:data key="d6">2.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">MCMC adheres to requirements specified in the DRAFT RFP for shipboard and prepositioning operations.&lt;SEP&gt;MCMC receives RFP from Contracting Officer for exercises and responds with Resource and Support Plan.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">contract requirements,exercise preparation,response,service outline</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-f918f57232ad428f5920d4c98f0af702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841264</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCMC" target="Marine Corps Stock List">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">MCMC completes Urgent MI on equipment using instructions from the Marine Corps Stock List.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">modification compliance</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841264</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCMC" target="Joint Travel Regulations">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">MCMC personnel stranded ashore receive per diem payments based on rates in the Joint Travel Regulations.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">per diem eligibility</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841265</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCMC" target="Ship's Master">
  <ns0:data key="d6">2.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">Ship's Master directs MCMC personnel in ship operations, safety, and has authority to remove personnel for violations.&lt;SEP&gt;MCMC personnel are subject to the Ship's Master's direction for ship safety and operations, and the Ship's Master verifies per diem claims.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">authority,personnel management,subordination,verification</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-f918f57232ad428f5920d4c98f0af702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d0f24c6dd1ff5486bfe7491203ea801</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841265</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCMC" target="PICP Consumer Level Account Inventory Results">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">The MCMC provides PICP Consumer Level Account Inventory Results to include causative research and adjustments.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">deliverable submission,inventory reporting</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841266</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCMC" target="Monthly Afloat Armory Report">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">The MCMC conducts monthly inventories of serialized small arms and submits RO-endorsed Monthly Afloat Armory Reports.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">RO endorsement,inventory conduct</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841268</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCMC" target="STRATIS">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">The MCMC utilizes STRATIS for warehousing operations of General Account stocks, ensuring records match GCSS-MC.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">inventory matching,warehouse management</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841269</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCMC" target="COSIS Surveillance Plan">
  <ns0:data key="d6">2.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">MCMC conducts and reports COSIS status in accordance with the Government-approved COSIS Surveillance Plan.&lt;SEP&gt;The MCMC submits COSIS Surveillance Plan for Government approval within 60 days and annually.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">annual review,compliance,execution,plan submission</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-65833c099ebcc7aa1fccc5a1d930a7aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841270</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCMC" target="Monthly COSIS Surveillance Plan Update and Status Report">
  <ns0:data key="d6">2.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">MCMC submits the Monthly COSIS Surveillance Plan Update and Status Report no later than the last business day of each month.&lt;SEP&gt;The MCMC submits monthly updates on COSIS actions, including planned and completed inspections.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">action tracking,status reporting,submission</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-65833c099ebcc7aa1fccc5a1d930a7aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841270</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCMC" target="MDMC Albany">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">MDMC Albany provides repair services under the Repair and Return program coordinated by the MCMC.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">repair coordination,service provision</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841271</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCMC" target="DIC">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">The MCMC includes DIC in physical inventory results for recommended adjustments to APSR records.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">adjustment recommendation,transaction identification</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841271</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCMC" target="SUC">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">The MCMC conducts quarterly CMR inventories for all SUCs except afloat ME PO assets.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">inventory reconciliation,quarterly conduct</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841271</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCMC" target="M92502">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">The MCMC maintains quarterly CMR reconciliations for M92502 organic ME afloat on MPS.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">account management,quarterly requirement</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841272</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCMC" target="CDRL 5024">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">The MCMC submits signed CMRs, SECREPs, CLIX, and Sustainment Block listings as CDRL 5024 at E+5.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">RO signature,listing submission</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841272</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCMC" target="MCO 4450.15">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">The MCMC conducts operational/serviceability checks on SECREPs per MCO 4450.15.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">COSIS checks,compliance</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841273</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCMC" target="CBRN">
  <ns0:data key="d6">3.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">MCMC conducts serviceability inspections of CBRN equipment in sustainment blocks and records results in the CBRN Inspection Log.&lt;SEP&gt;The MCMC creates production plans for CBRN as part of MCPP maintenance activities.&lt;SEP&gt;CBRN assets are tracked by the MCMC using DPAS during prepositioning program operations.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">DPAS accountability,activity planning,asset tracking,inspection,prepositioned support,recording</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-bd3a05bb896b89de7fd366c654ad4a6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a0a00a7bb666b381893da579a6b228c9</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841273</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCMC" target="Non-Standard Equipment">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">Non-Standard Equipment with HQMC-established POs is managed by the MCMC for accountability.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">HQMC direction,PO establishment</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-67bad1bd73dd9a9a7549acb855ae5e55</ns0:data>
