<ns0:edge source="MCMC" target="IMARK Labels">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">The MCMC removes and replaces faded or worn IMARK Labels, MSE, and other labels NLT approved staging date per specified orders.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">compliance,label maintenance</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-89b1a9fa6c0722adcd478e665df09141</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841292</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCMC" target="Maintenance Management">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">The MCMC executes the Marine Corps ground equipment maintenance management program, managing eight functional areas including administration and supply support.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">oversight,program execution</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-89b1a9fa6c0722adcd478e665df09141</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841292</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCMC" target="Maintenance Management Office Manager">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">The MCMC appoints a Maintenance Management Office Manager responsible for all maintenance officer duties per MCO 4790.2 and CmdO 4790.1B.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">appointment,responsibility</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-89b1a9fa6c0722adcd478e665df09141</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841292</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCMC" target="UND">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">The MCMC maintains a UND “A” and “B” Delegation of Authority Letter (CDRL 1004) submitted NLT specified days after award or new hires.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">authority delegation,submission</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-89b1a9fa6c0722adcd478e665df09141</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841293</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCMC" target="Supply Support">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">The MCMC manages Supply Support including equipment fielding, warranty coordination, CLS items, repair parts in layettes, and DSI inventories.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">functional area,procedures</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-89b1a9fa6c0722adcd478e665df09141</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841293</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCMC" target="DSI">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">The MCMC manages DSI inventories for On-Island, Shipboard, and MCPP-PHIL locations using GCSS-MC, with DSI Authorization Letters (CDRL 1008) submitted for approval.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">authorization,inventory management</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-89b1a9fa6c0722adcd478e665df09141</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841294</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCMC" target="MCO 4410.28">
  <ns0:data key="d6">2.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">The MCMC places, registers, and associates IUID and pRFID tags in accordance with MCO 4410.28.&lt;SEP&gt;MCMC complies with MCO 4410.28 for IUID and RFID tag association and application.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">compliance,governance,tagging procedures</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-89b1a9fa6c0722adcd478e665df09141&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841294</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCMC" target="MCPIC Data Standards">
  <ns0:data key="d6">1.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">The MCMC registers IUID and pRFID tags in IMARK according to MCPIC Data Standards upon item receipt at DMO.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">data standards adherence,registration</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-89b1a9fa6c0722adcd478e665df09141</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841295</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCMC" target="MCTP 13-10D">
  <ns0:data key="d6">2.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">The MCMC removes and replaces labels NLT staging date in compliance with MCTP 13-10D.&lt;SEP&gt;MCMC complies with MCTP 13-10D for removing labels and stickers from equipment.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">compliance,label replacement,labeling</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-89b1a9fa6c0722adcd478e665df09141&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f808346dbf233cd47e4c673a7cf87022</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d10">M6700425R0007 MCPP II DRAFT RFP 23 MAY 25.pdf</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d11">1759841295</ns0:data>
</ns0:edge>
<ns0:edge source="MCMC" target="SOUM">
  <ns0:data key="d6">2.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">MCMC performs special maintenance actions for ME and CESE in accordance with published SOUM, MAM, MIM, and GPM/A via official communications.&lt;SEP&gt;The MCMC accurately updates GCSS-MC based on information from Safety of Use Messages.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">safety compliance,safety messaging,special maintenance,update requirement</ns0:data>
