<ns0:edge source="Employee Compensation Plan" target="Service Contract Labor Standards">
  <ns0:data key="d6">2.0</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d7">The Employee Compensation Plan must align with Service Contract Labor Standards, including Area Wage Determinations and Collective Bargaining Agreements, to be deemed reasonable.&lt;SEP&gt;Employee Compensation Plan aligns with Service Contract Labor Standards, including area wage determinations and variances explanations.</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d8">benefit requirements,legal compliance,wage alignment</ns0:data>
  <ns0:data key="d9">chunk-3478ab61c9462db63588376af8a45cd2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b912387d0abf83a18f9cd19906dc41e</ns0:data>
