tion Instructions to Offerors" target="Factor D"><data key="d3">GUIDES</data><data key="d4">0.8</data><data key="d5">L-4 instructions cover the preparation of Volume V, which is explicitly evaluated under Factor D for Past Performance. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e301" source="L-4 Proposal Preparation Instructions to Offerors" target="Factor E"><data key="d3">GUIDES</data><data key="d4">0.8</data><data key="d5">L-4 instructions include requirements for cost/price volumes, guiding the evaluation under Factor E for Cost/Price. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e302" source="L-4 Proposal Preparation Instructions to Offerors" target="Factor F"><data key="d3">GUIDES</data><data key="d4">0.8</data><data key="d5">L-4 instructions include small business participation requirements, guiding the evaluation under Factor F for Small Business Participation and Subcontracting. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e303" source="Cost/Price" target="Factor E"><data key="d3">GUIDES</data><data key="d4">0.95</data><data key="d5">Cost/Price submission instructions detail support for reasonableness, completeness, and realism using cost models, directly aligning with Factor E's evaluation of proposed costs and prices. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e304" source="Cost/Price" target="Cost/Price Factor"><data key="d3">GUIDES</data><data key="d4">0.95</data><data key="d5">The instructions require certified cost data and narratives on assumptions, guiding the Cost/Price Factor's assessment of completeness, reasonableness, and realism. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e305" source="Summary Descriptions and Narrative" target="Cost/Price Factor"><data key="d3">GUIDES</data><data key="d4">0.9</data><data key="d5">Provides descriptions of estimating systems and cost reductions for major elements, supporting the Cost/Price Factor's analysis of cost realism and business systems. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e306" source="Summary and Supporting Schedules" target="Cost/Price Factor"><data key="d3">GUIDES</data><data key="d4">0.9</data><data key="d5">Mandates pricing schedules for optional periods, guiding the evaluation of cost completeness and reasonableness in the Cost/Price Factor. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e307" source="Proposal Summary" target="Cost/Price Factor"><data key="d3">GUIDES</data><data key="d4">0.9</data><data key="d5">Requires summaries of CLINs and SLINs using the cost model, directly informing the Cost/Price Factor's review of proposed costs. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e308" source="Cost Breakout and Supporting Data" target="Cost/Price Factor"><data key="d3">GUIDES</data><data key="d4">0.9</data><data key="d5">Correlates cost breakouts for labor, materials, and other elements to the proposal summary, guiding the Cost/Price Factor's evaluation of cost details. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e309" source="Cost Reimbursable Material, Travel and Overtime" target="Cost/Price Factor"><data key="d3">GUIDES</data><data key="d4">0.9</data><data key="d5">Details reimbursable costs and compliance with DFARS, supporting the Cost/Price Factor's assessment of cost realism for materials, travel, and overtime. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e310" source="Segregation of Costs by ACRN/Funding Sources" target="Cost/Price Factor"><data key="d3">GUIDES</data><data key="d4">0.85</data><data key="d5">Demonstrates cost segregation by funding sources with narratives, aiding the Cost/Price Factor's review of cost allocation and completeness. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e311" source="Fee Structure" target="Cost/Price Factor"><data key="d3">GUIDES</data><data key="d4">0.9</data><data key="d5">Applies FAR and DFARS fee limitations, guiding the Cost/Price Factor's evaluation of proposed fees within the 10% maximum. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e312" source="Other Information" target="Cost/Price Factor"><data key="d3">GUIDES</data><data key="d4">0.8</data><data key="d5">Includes details on estimating, accounting, and purchasing systems, as well as forward pricing rates, which inform the Cost/Price Factor's analysis of business systems. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e313" source="Small Business Participation" target="Factor F"><data key="d3">GUIDES</data><data key="d4">0.95</data><data key="d5">Discusses small business participation and commitment levels, directly guiding the evaluation under Factor F for Small Business Participation and Subcontracting. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e314" source="Small Business Participation" target="Small Business Participation and Subcontracting Factor"><data key="d3">GUIDES</data><data key="d4">0.95</data><data key="d5">Addresses identification and extent of small business utilization, aligning with the factor's assessment of subcontracting plans rated from Outstanding to Unacceptable. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e315" source="Oral Presentations" target="Factor D"><data key="d3">GUIDES</data><data key="d4">0.85</data><data key="d5">Oral Presentations assess past performance relevant to requirements, guiding the evaluation of Past Performance under Factor D from Volume V. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e316" source="Past Performance Questionnaires" target="Factor D"><data key="d3">GUIDES</data><data key="d4">0.85</data><data key="d5">Questionnaires collect past performance data from sources, guiding the evaluation under Factor D for relevance and quality of prior efforts. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e317" source="Past Performance Questionnaires" target="Past Performance Relevancy Ratings"><data key="d3">GUIDES</data><data key="d4">0.7</data><data key="d5">Provide data on effort complexity, scope, and period, which inform the relevancy ratings of Very Relevant to Not Relevant in past performance evaluation. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e318" source="Past Performance Questionnaires" target="Past Performance Confidence Assessments"><data key="d3">GUIDES</data><data key="d4">0.7</data><data key="d5">Collect performance records used to rate confidence levels from Substantial to No Confidence, guiding the assessment of ability to perform. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e319" source="Solicitation Submission" target="Evaluation Factors for Award"><data key="d3">GUIDES</data><data key="d4">0.6</data><data key="d5">Requires inclusion of documents and exceptions in Volume VIII, ensuring complete submissions for evaluation under all factors. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e320" source="Distribution Submission Proposal Volumes" target="Evaluation Factors for Award"><data key="d3">GUIDES</data><data key="d4">0.6</data><data key="d5">Provides procedures for sending copies and marking envelopes, guiding proper submission to enable fair evaluation. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e321" source="Proposal Due Date Schedule" target="Evaluation Factors for Award"><data key="d3">GUIDES</data><data key="d4">0.5</data><data key="d5">Specifies due dates for proposals except oral presentations, ensuring timely submissions for evaluation processing. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e322" source="Exceptions to Terms and Conditions" target="Evaluation Factors for Award"><data key="d3">GUIDES</data><data key="d4">0.5</data><data key="d5">Requires identification and rationale for exceptions, which impacts overall proposal compliance and evaluation. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e323" source="Program Management" target="Factor A"><data key="d3">EVALUATED_BY</data><data key="d4">0.9</data><data key="d5">Program Management directly aligns with Management Methodology evaluated in Factor A from Volume II, sharing concepts of risk management and SOW compliance. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e324" source="Quality Assurance" target="Factor A"><data key="d3">EVALUATED_BY</data><data key="d4">0.85</data><data key="d5">Quality Assurance involves inspection and acceptance processes central to management methodology in Factor A. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e325" source="ISO 9001:2015" target="Factor A"><data key="d3">EVALUATED_BY</data><data key="d4">0.8</data><data key="d5">ISO 9001:2015 certification and CPI program implementation relate to quality management standards assessed in Factor A. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e326" source="ISO 9001:2015 Internal Audit Program" target="Factor A"><data key="d3">EVALUATED_BY</data><data key="d4">0.75</data><data key="d5">Internal audit program maintenance ties into overall quality management methodology in Factor A. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e327" source="ANSI/ISO 9001:2015" target="Factor A"><data key="d3">EVALUATED_BY</data><data key="d4">0.8</data><data key="d5">Compliance and certification to ANSI/ISO 9001:2015 is a core quality management requ